<h2 id="reviews"><a href="/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/">Reviews</a></h2>
<div class="grid-split">
  <section id="critic-reviews">
    <h4>Critics</h4>
    <p>
      
      Average score: 94% <span class="text-muted">(based on 190 ratings)</span>
      
    </p>
    <critic-reviews :reviews='[{"citation": "Portal 2 \u00e8 un vero capolavoro che ogni appassionato di belle esperienze dovrebbe inserire nella propria collezione. Il team di sviluppo \u00e8 riuscito nella difficile impresa di far crescere nel migliore dei modi un\u0027idea gi\u00e0 eccezionale, superando anche la pi\u00f9 rosea delle previsioni. Se avete una PS3, una Xbox 360, un PC o un Mac, c\u0027\u00e8 solo una cosa che potete dire prima di andare ad acquistare questo gioiello: grazie, Valve!", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45737969", "grade": null, "id": 218788, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218788", "language": "it", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "it", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f5b5804-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 12, "name": "Italy"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257796", "first_year": 2008, "id": 1163, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1163/eurogamerit/", "languages": [{"code": "it", "id": 64, "name": "Italian", "ordering": 640}], "last_year": null, "name": "Eurogamer.it", "num_reviews": 695, "url": "http://www.eurogamer.it/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.eurogamer.it/articles/2011-04-19-portal-2-recensione"}, {"citation": "Quite simply, Portal 2 is a masterpiece. A lesson to every other developer out there on how to tell a story in a video game whilst executing every gameplay mechanic to perfection. Masterful writing, engaging characters, wonderful music, and so forward-thinking that it even includes cross-platform, cloud-saving play between Steam and the PlayStation 3. Utterly essential in every way, Portal 2 is going to be in everyone\u2019s game of the year discussion when the time comes, and it damn well deserves every ounce of praise lavished upon it. Buy Portal 2, you deserve it.", "date": "2011-05-04", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45640406", "grade": null, "id": 215812, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-215812", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "uk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f7e9f08-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 22, "name": "United Kingdom"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257617", "first_year": 2009, "id": 1548, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1548/god-is-a-geek/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "God is a Geek", "num_reviews": 1458, "url": "http://www.godisageek.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.godisageek.com/2011/05/portal-2-review/"}, {"citation": "Yet, Portal 2\u2019s biggest innovation is in its cooperative play. Undoubtedly a revolution in multiplayer; you take control of two spritely robots entrusted with a portal gun each. Naturally it heightens the difficulty (although a gradual learning curve is pleasingly implemented), but it also fuels the most actively collaborative gameplay we\u2019ve come to experience. And as the multiplayer provides as many twists and turns to this hilarious tale as the solo campaign, every inch of Portal 2 feels significant. Simply, it\u2019s the game of the year.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=4299187686", "grade": null, "id": 657412, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-657412", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254206", "first_year": 2003, "id": 779, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/779/empireonlinecom/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "EmpireOnline.com", "num_reviews": 140, "url": "http://www.empireonline.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 1121630, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/1121630/rocket55/", "name": "Rocket"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "https://www.empireonline.com/gaming/reviews/portal-2-review/"}, {"citation": "I don\u2019t think Portal 2 will end up being the watershed \u201cah ha!\u201d moment that Portal was. There was a certain magic to the first game that will never be recaptured. That being said, Portal 2 is better in just about every way possible. The puzzles are more intricate, the writing is better than most movies or TV shows I\u2019ve seen, and the production value is everything you\u2019ve come to expect from the guys that brought you Half-Life. Portal 2 certainly isn\u2019t a perfect (no game is) but it is one that I can\u2019t recommend enough.", "date": "2011-04-18", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45669136", "grade": null, "id": 218865, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218865", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259512", "first_year": 2010, "id": 1522, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1522/inside-gaming/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Inside Gaming", "num_reviews": 70, "url": "http://www.insidegamingdaily.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://blog.machinima.com/insidegaming/2011/04/18/portal-2-review/"}, {"citation": "Despite being so much bigger than the original, I actually felt a little melancholy once Portal 2 was over, simply because it\u0027s so rare to find a game this smart, this funny, and this rich with detail. It elevates Portal from an odd, memorable experiment to one of the most significant series in Valve\u0027s stable with a unique voice and an incredible level of quality that all developers should aspire to.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45737948", "grade": null, "id": 218680, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218680", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257710", "first_year": 2008, "id": 839, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/839/giant-bomb/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Giant Bomb", "num_reviews": 1066, "url": "http://www.giantbomb.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://www.giantbomb.com/portal-2/61-21662/reviews/"}, {"citation": "When it comes to making video games, a strong argument can be made that Valve is among the best out there. They are like the Pixar of the videogame industry, setting the standard for others, never disappointing, and delivering product on a consistent, predictable schedule. That last fact actually only applies to Pixar, but you get the idea. Portal 2 is an absolutely worthy successor to the original, and it is, objectively, a better game. Nothing will ever replace the first time you solved a puzzle in the original Portal, or when GLaDOS began to serenade you during the end credits, but you will find yourself just as absorbed into the world and congratulating yourself on your personal genius every few minutes. Portal 2 is a perfect example of what video games should be, and there is no reason to pass it up.", "date": "2011-04-26", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45507235", "grade": null, "id": 218827, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218827", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257853", "first_year": 2005, "id": 522, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/522/gamernode/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gamernode", "num_reviews": 531, "url": "http://www.gamernode.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://gamernode.com/reviews/10487-portal-2-review/index.html"}, {"citation": "All these minor triumphs are a credit to Valve\u2019s subtle but potent marriage of writing and game design. If there was ever any doubt that Portal could be expanded into a big, narrative experience with all the bells and whistles of a mainstream gaming hit, have no fear. Valve solved that puzzle with Portal 2.", "date": "2011-04-25", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45670717", "grade": "A", "id": 219049, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-219049", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 100.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259574", "first_year": 2005, "id": 564, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/564/av-club-the/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "A.V. Club, The", "num_reviews": 438, "url": "http://www.avclub.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 4, "name": "Letter Grade"}, "url": "http://origin.avclub.com/articles/portal-2,55020/"}, {"citation": "Exception faite d\u0027un second acte un peu en retrait, Portal 2 impose une aventure d\u0027une saveur incomparable, impeccablement mise en sc\u00e8ne et bourr\u00e9e d\u0027autant d\u0027humour que d\u0027ing\u00e9niosit\u00e9. Les nombreuses nouvelles m\u00e9caniques renouvellent les puzzles, la dur\u00e9e de vie exc\u00e8de nos espoirs, le mode Coop\u00e9ratif se d\u00e9guste en ligne ou en local avec d\u00e9lectation, et m\u00eame si la fin ne saurait \u00eatre aussi savoureuse que celle du premier, elle conclut un rollercoaster de sensations pures et de trouvailles de g\u00e9nie qui forcent le respect.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45739758", "grade": null, "id": 218860, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218860", "language": "fr", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "fr", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f4ebb9e-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 8, "name": "France"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252458", "first_year": 2006, "id": 1465, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1465/gameblogfr/", "languages": [{"code": "fr", "id": 42, "name": "French", "ordering": 420}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gameblog.fr", "num_reviews": 1092, "url": "http://www.gameblog.fr/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://www.gameblog.fr/test_923_portal-2-360-ps3-pc-mac"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is the best Valve release to date, and one of the most refreshing, exciting and innovative games we\u0027ve ever played. There\u0027s no doubt in our minds that numerous Game of the Year awards have now already been shotgunned, and with mighty good reason. If you thought the original Portal was a masterpiece, prepare to have your mind blown.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45737947", "grade": null, "id": 218679, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218679", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "hr", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/e956ef22-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 6, "name": "Croatia"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257789", "first_year": 2002, "id": 94, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/94/gamewatcher-strategy-informer/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "GameWatcher / Strategy Informer", "num_reviews": 908, "url": "http://www.gamewatcher.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.strategyinformer.com/xbox360/portal2/1464/review.html"}, {"citation": "I don\u2019t think Portal 2 will end up being the watershed \u201cah ha!\u201d moment that Portal was. There was a certain magic to the first game that will never be recaptured. That being said, Portal 2 is better in just about every way possible. The puzzles are more intricate, the writing is better than most movies or TV shows I\u2019ve seen, and the production value is everything you\u2019ve come to expect from the guys that brought you Half-Life. Portal 2 certainly isn\u2019t a perfect (no game is) but it is one that I can\u2019t recommend enough.", "date": "2011-04-18", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45737988", "grade": null, "id": 218866, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218866", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259512", "first_year": 2010, "id": 1522, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1522/inside-gaming/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Inside Gaming", "num_reviews": 70, "url": "http://www.insidegamingdaily.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://blog.machinima.com/insidegaming/2011/04/18/portal-2-review/"}, {"citation": "Impatience aside, Portal 2 is an exceptionally well-crafted, intelligent, entertaining, humorous game. You will laugh. You will feel like a freaking genius. You will want more. And yes, you will probably be hearing quotes from Portal 2 for the next three years.", "date": "2011-04-22", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667782", "grade": "A", "id": 218845, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218845", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 100.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258085", "first_year": 1996, "id": 4, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/4/game-revolution/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Game Revolution", "num_reviews": 3224, "url": "http://www.gamerevolution.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 4, "name": "Letter Grade"}, "url": "http://www.gamerevolution.com/review/ps3/portal-2"}, {"citation": "On s\u0027attendait certes \u00e0 une claque, mais Portal 2 s\u0027av\u00e8re un authentique chef-d\u0027\u0153uvre, une le\u00e7on de game design \u00e0 l\u0027usage de l\u0027industrie. Alliant la pratique d\u0027un gameplay profond \u00e0 un fort attachement au r\u00e9cit, l\u0027aventure solo est le fruit d\u0027une alchimie rarissime entre ludisme et narration qui suffirait d\u00e9j\u00e0 \u00e0 justifier l\u0027engouement. L\u0027ajout d\u0027un mode multijoueur captivant finit de nous convaincre : \u00e0 tous points de vue, il s\u0027agit bien de cet immense jeu cach\u00e9 dans les replis du premier \u00e9pisode, qui n\u0027a jamais tant fait figure d\u0027introduction. Gamers de tous bords, r\u00e9jouissez-vous : Portal 2 rejoint le rang des meilleurs jeux de tous les temps.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45705865", "grade": null, "id": 226717, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-226717", "language": "fr", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "fr", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f4ebb9e-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 8, "name": "France"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254926", "first_year": 2001, "id": 1178, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1178/jeuxvideofr/", "languages": [{"code": "fr", "id": 42, "name": "French", "ordering": 420}], "last_year": null, "name": "Jeuxvideo.fr", "num_reviews": 258, "url": "http://www.jeuxvideo.fr/"}, "submitter": {"id": 183114, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/183114/alsy/", "name": "Alsy"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.jeuxvideo.fr/jeux/portal-2/preview-test-portal-2.html"}, {"citation": "Really, there isn\u0027t anything more that can be said about Portal 2, it\u0027s is simply one of the best games ever released. People may find the campaign to be a bit short for their money, but I can give you a few examples of other games that were equally as short and completely worth their asking price as well, such as Ico or Dead Space 2. The quality you get from this shorter experience far outweighs the fluff a lot of other games would throw out there, plus you\u0027ll want to play Portal 2 at least two more times to find the easter eggs and to listen to the developer commentary. The initial experience alone is worth the asking price, everything after that just seriously felt like a bonus. If you can play through Portal 2 and find reasons not to like it, then I think you might need another medium of entertainment. Because seriously, I don\u0027t see it getting any better than this for quite some time. Bravo Valve on creating something truly magical with Portal 2.", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45670674", "grade": "A+", "id": 219031, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-219031", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 100.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259524", "first_year": 2002, "id": 289, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/289/gaming-nexus/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gaming Nexus", "num_reviews": 1250, "url": "http://www.gamingnexus.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 4, "name": "Letter Grade"}, "url": "http://www.gamingnexus.com/Article/Portal-2/Item3042.aspx"}, {"citation": "Overall, Portal 2 is among the best video games ever made. Fans of adventure or puzzle games must not miss out on this gem of a game. The story is amazing, the graphics are great, and the gameplay is rewarding. Unfortunately, Portal 2 does not feature an Advanced Chambers mode akin to that in the \u003cmoby game=\"Portal\" platform=\"windows\"\u003eoriginal Portal\u003c/moby\u003e. Aside from this singular criticism, the game is as close to perfect as it can possibly get. In my eyes, Portal 2 is a definite contender for the best game of the year.", "date": "2012-11-15", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45940488", "grade": null, "id": 247824, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-247824", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "ca", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9fa117cc-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 5, "name": "Canada"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257896", "first_year": 1996, "id": 155, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/155/adventure-classic-gaming/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Adventure Classic Gaming", "num_reviews": 523, "url": "http://www.adventureclassicgaming.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 172183, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/172183/mrmamen/", "name": "MrMamen"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://www.adventureclassicgaming.com/index.php/site/reviews/681/"}, {"citation": "Van \u00e9\u00e9n ding heb ik echter spijt: dat Portal 2 geen oneindige cyclus kent zoals de Portal Gun toelaat. Het hele plot is namelijk zo een indrukwekkende achtbaanrit dat het voorbij is voor je het beseft. Des te imposanter is dat gegeven door het feit dat we hier te maken hebben met een uiterst vermakelijke puzzelgame. Dankzij memorabele personages, sterke dialogen en een gelijkwaardige co-op campaign zal de hele ervaring voor een zeer lange tijd in het geheugen ge\u00ebtst blijven. Of Portal 3 ooit het daglicht zal zien, hangt in het ongewisse, maar voor mij staat het vast: GLaDOS, als Eurogamer Benelux mij ooit de laan uitstuurt, mag je mij als proefkonijn gebruiken in je su\u00efcidale testkamers. Zolang ik nadien maar taart krijg.", "date": "2011-04-24", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667689", "grade": null, "id": 218786, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218786", "language": "nl", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "nl", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/c4f2d308-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 16, "name": "The Netherlands"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257822", "first_year": 2008, "id": 1142, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1142/eurogamernl/", "languages": [{"code": "nl", "id": 34, "name": "Dutch", "ordering": 340}], "last_year": null, "name": "Eurogamer.nl", "num_reviews": 44, "url": "http://www.eurogamer.nl/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.eurogamer.nl/articles/2011-04-24-portal-2-review_1"}, {"citation": "Von der ersten bis zur letzten Minute schafft das Spiel eine ganz eigene Atmosph\u00e4re und ein ihm allein geh\u00f6rendes, fantastisch abgerundetes Spielgef\u00fchl, dass man angesichts dessen Dankbarkeit empfindet, das Hobby der Videospiele f\u00fcr sich gew\u00e4hlt zu haben. Danke, Valve.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667676", "grade": null, "id": 218784, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218784", "language": "de", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "de", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f8eb00a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 9, "name": "Germany"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257763", "first_year": 2006, "id": 487, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/487/eurogamerde/", "languages": [{"code": "de", "id": 47, "name": "German", "ordering": 470}], "last_year": null, "name": "Eurogamer.de", "num_reviews": 996, "url": "http://www.eurogamer.de/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.eurogamer.de/articles/2011-04-19-portal-2-test"}, {"citation": "When it comes to making video games, a strong argument can be made that Valve is among the best out there. They are like the Pixar of the videogame industry, setting the standard for others, never disappointing, and delivering product on a consistent, predictable schedule. That last fact actually only applies to Pixar, but you get the idea. Portal 2 is an absolutely worthy successor to the original, and it is, objectively, a better game. Nothing will ever replace the first time you solved a puzzle in the original Portal, or when GLaDOS began to serenade you during the end credits, but you will find yourself just as absorbed into the world and congratulating yourself on your personal genius every few minutes. Portal 2 is a perfect example of what video games should be, and there is no reason to pass it up.", "date": "2011-04-26", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45745387", "grade": null, "id": 218825, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218825", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257853", "first_year": 2005, "id": 522, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/522/gamernode/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gamernode", "num_reviews": 531, "url": "http://www.gamernode.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://gamernode.com/reviews/10486-portal-2-review/index.html"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is something special, it has amazing presentation, graphics are sublime, gameplay is balanced, the characters are memorable, it has plot twists, puzzles that drive a story along and a big finish. It is a game that is amazing because of the sum of its parts. It is unfair to pigeon hole it as a puzzle game, an action game or anything really. Portal 2 is a wonderful mix genres and a great advert for gaming, There is no such thing as perfection, no matter how much we strive for it, therefore a couple of minor niggles do not distract from a top score. Portal 2 is the Game of the Year so far, it will take something special for it not to take that accolade. Sometimes the anticipation of a games release can leave the final thing feeling a little flat. That is not the case here as Portal 2 lives up to all expectations and then some.", "date": "2011-04-27", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45670668", "grade": null, "id": 219021, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-219021", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "uk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f7e9f08-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 22, "name": "United Kingdom"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259350", "first_year": 2001, "id": 322, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/322/gamestyle/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gamestyle", "num_reviews": 652, "url": "http://gamestyle.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://gamestyle.com/reviews/2095/portal-2/"}, {"citation": "In the end, it\u2019s hard to think of anything Portal 2 does wrong. It\u2019s hard enough to think of anything it doesn\u2019t do as well as it could have. Valve has taken the original premise and shown what they can do with a longer development time and a more polished, full-featured release. Portal 2 no longer relies on the same \u201cshort but sweet\u201d simplicity that helped make the original such a classic, but it doesn\u2019t need it. The sequel keeps varying both the style of the obstacles and the environments in which the puzzles are set at just the right intervals, so it never feels like you\u2019re doing the same thing over and over. All the while, the consistent display of impressive voice acting and some of the funniest game writing ever leaves a lasting impression of these memorable characters and Chell\u2019s ordeal. The addition of the superbly designed co-op campaign just adds yet another layer of brilliance on top of an already spectacular single-player experience.", "date": "2011-04-29", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45555356", "grade": null, "id": 211093, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-211093", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "ie", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/c50c95f4-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 37, "name": "Ireland"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254204", "first_year": 1999, "id": 66, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/66/adventure-gamers/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Adventure Gamers", "num_reviews": 2022, "url": "http://www.adventuregamers.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 55856, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/55856/scaryfun/", "name": "Scaryfun"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://www.adventuregamers.com/article/id,1307"}, {"citation": "This was one sequel that was both worth the wait, and everything it was cracked up to be. Even with the minor gameplay tick for accessibility mentioned above, it still averaged out to a 5-gem game, which it fully deserves. By the way, I believe a statement was issued that this was to be the last Valve title to offer an exclusive single-player experience. I hope this isn\u0027t the case, because I was about to start the \"We want our Portal 3\" chant.", "date": "2011-06-29", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45514969", "grade": null, "id": 218974, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218974", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259381", "first_year": 1998, "id": 220, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/220/game-industry-news-gin/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Game industry News (GiN)", "num_reviews": 664, "url": "http://www.gameindustry.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://www.gameindustry.com/review/item.asp?id=1370"}, {"citation": "Sporting some of the best writing and voice work in years (as well as some deviously designed puzzles), Portal 2\u0027s single-player campaign is superior to its predecessor in every way. It\u0027s the co-op mode, however, that makes this 2011\u0027s first must-play game -- even for those gamers that don\u0027t like first-person or puzzle games.", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667640", "grade": null, "id": 218761, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218761", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257678", "first_year": 1996, "id": 10, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/10/gamespy/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": 2013, "name": "GameSpy", "num_reviews": 4936, "url": "http://www.gamespy.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://ps3.gamespy.com/playstation-3/portal-2/1163551p1.html"}, {"citation": "One more word of caution, Portal 2 is a huge time suck.  The sense of accomplishment you get when beating a puzzle will cause you on more than one occasion to utter those famous last words, \"just one more and then I\u0027ll be done.\"  You\u0027ll end up beating the game in a minimal amount of time that way (it is a longer campaign than the last one), but the rest of the world may fall by the wayside for a little while.  You won\u0027t regret your choice to continue, but those around you may get frustrated.", "date": "2011-04-20", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667639", "grade": null, "id": 218759, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218759", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258086", "first_year": 2005, "id": 948, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/948/blogcritics-magazine/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "BlogCritics Magazine", "num_reviews": 40, "url": "http://blogcritics.org/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://blogcritics.org/gaming/article/playstation-3-review-portal-2/"}, {"citation": "Valve delivered; the sequel is much bigger, plays better and has more features that will keep fans testing with Aperture Science for a long time.", "date": "2016-08-27", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=4299187118", "grade": null, "id": 657395, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-657395", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=3901672473", "first_year": 2016, "id": 2794, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/2794/god-minded-games/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "God Minded Games", "num_reviews": 22, "url": "https://www.godmindedgaming.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 1121630, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/1121630/rocket55/", "name": "Rocket"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "https://www.godmindedgaming.com/reviews/portal_2.html"}, {"citation": "Genius is an often overused word but Valve\u0027s work on Portal 2 is genius in the truest sense. The studio has exhibited exceptional creativity in the game, even compared to some of its other masterpieces. If we could give it 11/10, we would.", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45737019", "grade": null, "id": 218665, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218665", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259534", "first_year": 1996, "id": 100, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/100/totalvideogames-tvg/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "TotalVideoGames (TVG)", "num_reviews": 359, "url": "http://www.totalvideogames.net/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.totalvideogames.com/Portal-2/review-16411.html"}, {"citation": "While Valve still refuses to give me closure to Half Life, it is games like Poral 2 that not only regains my love for this team of developers, but keeps my little fingers nimble for the infamous day when Dr. Gordon Freeman makes his triumphant return. Let\u0027s just hope that the Portal gun and GLaDOS find their way into my Half Life universe and not via mods on the PC. Whether you love Half Life, the original Portal, or have never played but wondered what the fuss was about, you owe it to yourself to play this wonder of gaming technology. Portal 2 has enough appeal to welcome any gamer no matter what type they claim themselves to be. The end result is a gaming experience you will not soon forget.", "date": "2011-05-02", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45745378", "grade": "A", "id": 218707, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218707", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 100.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258009", "first_year": 1997, "id": 18, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/18/gaming-age/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gaming Age", "num_reviews": 2467, "url": "http://www.gaming-age.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 4, "name": "Letter Grade"}, "url": "http://www.gaming-age.com/review/ps3/portal2"}, {"citation": "Despite rarely holding us up for long, single-player mode provided hours of gameplay. In a couple of places, the plot feels like it\u2019s been stretched out over more levels than are needed to comfortably explain it, but that\u2019s a minor niggle. Even when you\u2019re done with that, the game\u2019s not over. As well as tons of hidden areas, Portal 2 has what is easily one of the most entertaining co-op modes we\u2019ve played, requiring genuine ingenuity and teamwork as you and a friend take on two-player puzzles as test droids P-body and Atlas. Between that and a recently released toolset that lets you build your own levels, we expect to keep coming back until Portal 3 comes out.", "date": "2011-06-05", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=4299187380", "grade": null, "id": 657403, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-657403", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "uk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f7e9f08-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 22, "name": "United Kingdom"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=180051095", "first_year": 2009, "id": 2954, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/2954/expert-reviews/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Expert Reviews", "num_reviews": 6, "url": "https://www.expertreviews.co.uk/"}, "submitter": {"id": 1121630, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/1121630/rocket55/", "name": "Rocket"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "https://www.expertreviews.co.uk/technology/gaming/portal-2-review"}, {"citation": "Truly, Portal 2 is a highly enjoyable first-person puzzler with a healthy dose of humor and sci-fi to keep you glued to the screen for many hours on end.", "date": "2011", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=4299187468", "grade": null, "id": 657406, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-657406", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259542", "first_year": 2001, "id": 434, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/434/common-sense-media/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Common Sense Media", "num_reviews": 732, "url": "http://www.commonsensemedia.org/"}, "submitter": {"id": 1121630, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/1121630/rocket55/", "name": "Rocket"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "https://web.archive.org/web/20110616134106/http://www.commonsensemedia.org/game-reviews/portal-2"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is, without a doubt, one of the best games ever made. It\u0027s a game that not only seamlessly blends puzzle and adventure elements together, but makes a name for itself as a true \"comedy\" game, where witty dialog and laugh-out-loud concepts have been given an equal billing with the gameplay itself. It\u0027s funny, it\u0027s challenging, it\u0027s inventive, and it boasts memorable moments that will stick in your mind and make your hair stand on end every time you think about them. Gaming simply does not get much better.", "date": "2011-05-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45492031", "grade": null, "id": 218669, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218669", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259382", "first_year": 2007, "id": 654, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/654/destructoid/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Destructoid", "num_reviews": 2327, "url": "http://www.destructoid.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.destructoid.com/review-portal-2-199302.phtml"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is the full-course meal after Portal\u2019s appetizer.  While it suffers from a distinct lack of replayability in all of its modes, this is a title that all gamers should experience, and definitely stands as one of the best games of 2011. Just play it... you monster.", "date": "2011-04-26", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=4299186889", "grade": null, "id": 657391, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-657391", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "ww", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/d74880f2-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.png", "id": 56, "name": "Worldwide"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252452", "first_year": 2008, "id": 1694, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1694/co-optimus/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Co-Optimus", "num_reviews": 91, "url": "http://www.co-optimus.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 1121630, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/1121630/rocket55/", "name": "Rocket"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "https://www.co-optimus.com/review/749/page/2/portal-2-co-op-review.html"}, {"citation": "The reward of \u201cfinding\u201d the story by listening to the voices of GLaDOS, Cave, and Wheatley and finding information in the environment makes for a very satisfying experience. Pile on the \u201cOh, yes!\u201d moments of solving some really great puzzles, and there\u2019s every reason to start thinking about Game of the Year accolades. It\u2019s that good.", "date": "2011-04-28", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45555369", "grade": null, "id": 211094, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-211094", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257868", "first_year": 1999, "id": 174, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/174/armchair-empire/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Armchair Empire", "num_reviews": 1074, "url": "http://www.armchairempire.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 55856, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/55856/scaryfun/", "name": "Scaryfun"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.armchairempire.com/Reviews/PC%20Games/portal-2.htm"}, {"citation": "There\u0027s probably not too much replay value to the game \u2013 once the puzzles have been solved, they\u0027ve been solved and the only thing that may motivate you to go back and do them again is to sweep up any missed achievements. In the case of Portal 2 it doesn\u0027t really matter that much that the game will probably only provide a single play-through before you\u0027re done with it because you\u0027ll have so much fun with that play-through. Portal 2 is really a worthy successor to Portal, and is a great example of a very well-designed, well-implemented game. I recommend it highly. I don\u0027t give out many 100s, but if this game doesn\u0027t deserve that score than none of the other games that I\u0027ve given it to do.", "date": "2011-05-06", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45670663", "grade": null, "id": 219026, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-219026", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 100.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259468", "first_year": 1999, "id": 223, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/223/gamers-temple-the/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gamers\u0027 Temple, The", "num_reviews": 767, "url": "http://www.gamerstemple.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamerstemple.com/vgreview.asp?r=6345"}, {"citation": "Despite being so much bigger than the original, I actually felt a little melancholy once Portal 2 was over, simply because it\u0027s so rare to find a game this smart, this funny, and this rich with detail. It elevates Portal from an odd, memorable experiment to one of the most significant series in Valve\u0027s stable with a unique voice and an incredible level of quality that all developers should aspire to.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45663163", "grade": null, "id": 218681, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218681", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257710", "first_year": 2008, "id": 839, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/839/giant-bomb/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Giant Bomb", "num_reviews": 1066, "url": "http://www.giantbomb.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://www.giantbomb.com/portal-2/61-21662/reviews/"}, {"citation": "Valve has created a masterpiece in Portal 2. The depth of content, the mind-bending mechanics and fantastic experience are almost certain to satisfy ardent fans of the first game; and to all newcomers to the series, it\u0027s as simple as this: prepare to have your mind blown. Over and over again.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45670722", "grade": null, "id": 219054, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-219054", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "uk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f7e9f08-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 22, "name": "United Kingdom"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254573", "first_year": 2000, "id": 1598, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1598/guardian-the/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Guardian, The", "num_reviews": 524, "url": "http://www.guardian.co.uk/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://www.guardian.co.uk/technology/gamesblog/2011/apr/19/portal-2-game-review"}, {"citation": "I think you knew all along this was going to be great. Fantastic, even. All the same, I don\u0027t think you\u0027ll be prepared for it being this good. I may have buttoned my lip in terms of concrete spoilers, but a mere ten minutes here will yield more memorable moments than you\u0027re likely to squeeze out of the entirety of most other games this year. In all aspects of its design, Portal 2 is genius.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667552", "grade": null, "id": 218687, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218687", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259424", "first_year": 2001, "id": 611, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/611/videogamercom/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "videogamer.com", "num_reviews": 1394, "url": "http://www.videogamer.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.videogamer.com/ps3/portal_2/review.html"}, {"citation": "There\u0027s so much I want to share with people, as well as so many things left to talk about, but doing so would spoil so much of the surprise and fun that is in this game. Suffice to say, Valve has managed to create a game that bests its predecessor in nearly every regard, and has demonstrated to the world that they still have what it takes to create a game that deserves the hype surrounding it. While it\u0027s unclear if we\u0027ll ever see GLaDOS or Chell again, this much is certain: Portal 2 is one of the best games of this generation.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667546", "grade": "A+", "id": 218674, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218674", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 100.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257831", "first_year": 2000, "id": 6, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/6/1up-usa/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": 2013, "name": "1UP (USA)", "num_reviews": 2415, "url": "http://1up.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 4, "name": "Letter Grade"}, "url": "http://www.1up.com/reviews/portal-2-review"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 couldn\u0027t be Portal, but it\u0027s the next best thing. It\u0027s a longer, funnier, more emotional plummet through Aperture\u0027s perplexing laboratory, and its meticulous detail, perfect pacing, and kinetic, mind-expanding puzzles make it a blazingly memorable experience. It\u0027s so damn memorable, already feel nostalgic about it.", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667545", "grade": null, "id": 218673, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218673", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259547", "first_year": 2000, "id": 9, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/9/gamesradar/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "GamesRadar", "num_reviews": 1473, "url": "http://www.gamesradar.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamesradar.com/ps3/portal-2/review/portal-2-super-review/a-2011042116115133889771/g-20100308124746224008"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 a su garder les forces de son pr\u00e9d\u00e9cesseur tout en portant l\u2019efficacit\u00e9 du jeu \u00e0 un niveau sup\u00e9rieur et ferait presque passer son a\u00een\u00e9 pour un brouillon. Aussi bien r\u00e9ussi dans son level design que dans son \u00e9criture, on assiste \u00e0 un jeu brillant et bourr\u00e9 d\u2019humour avec des personnages attachants. Une r\u00e9ussite g\u00e9n\u00e9rale, que ce soit pour le solo ou le coop. Ce dernier \u00e9tant une r\u00e9elle valeur ajout\u00e9e pour ce titre qui figurera sans aucun doute comme l\u2019un des meilleurs jeux de l\u2019ann\u00e9e.", "date": "2011-05-01", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45640307", "grade": null, "id": 214336, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-214336", "language": "fr", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "fr", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f4ebb9e-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 8, "name": "France"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258098", "first_year": 2006, "id": 1544, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1544/xboxygen/", "languages": [{"code": "fr", "id": 42, "name": "French", "ordering": 420}], "last_year": null, "name": "Xboxygen", "num_reviews": 303, "url": "http://www.xboxygen.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://www.xboxygen.com/Tests/Tests-Xbox-360/Test-Portal-2"}, {"citation": "To talk about the game anymore would simply ruin the experience for those who haven\u2019t played yet, but I think you get the idea. Despite the lack of challenges that were so prominent in the first game, Portal 2 packs a lot of content for the price. It\u2019s everything the first game was and more, with very inspired level design, some ingenious puzzles, and some of the best writing you\u2019ll ever see in a video game. It might just be Valve\u2019s best game yet.", "date": "2011-04-25", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667530", "grade": null, "id": 218663, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218663", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259493", "first_year": 2002, "id": 439, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/439/snackbar-gamescom/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Snackbar-Games.com", "num_reviews": 233, "url": "http://www.snackbar-games.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.snackbar-games.com/reviews/playstation-3/portal-2/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is the best Valve release to date, and one of the most refreshing, exciting and innovative games we\u0027ve ever played. There\u0027s no doubt in our minds that numerous Game of the Year awards have now already been shotgunned, and with mighty good reason. If you thought the original Portal was a masterpiece, prepare to have your mind blown.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667490", "grade": null, "id": 218678, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218678", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "hr", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/e956ef22-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 6, "name": "Croatia"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257789", "first_year": 2002, "id": 94, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/94/gamewatcher-strategy-informer/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "GameWatcher / Strategy Informer", "num_reviews": 908, "url": "http://www.gamewatcher.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.strategyinformer.com/ps3/portal2/1463/review.html"}, {"citation": "Impatience aside, Portal 2 is an exceptionally well-crafted, intelligent, entertaining, humorous game. You will laugh. You will feel like a freaking genius. You will want more. And yes, you will probably be hearing quotes from Portal 2 for the next three years.", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45555370", "grade": "A", "id": 211095, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-211095", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 100.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258085", "first_year": 1996, "id": 4, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/4/game-revolution/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Game Revolution", "num_reviews": 3224, "url": "http://www.gamerevolution.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 55856, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/55856/scaryfun/", "name": "Scaryfun"}, "type": {"id": 4, "name": "Letter Grade"}, "url": "http://www.gamerevolution.com/review/pc/portal-2"}, {"citation": "When you review, you need to think about your predilections and your preconceptions. I admit I am a gamer who loves strategy - I am happiest when I am being mentally challenged by my games, and I strive to be smarter and faster than everyone else. I put more value in beating someone in Starcraft than I ever did in my kill/death ratio. However, I can say that while Portal 2 may not be for absolutely everyone, it undeniably deserves a place among the greatest games of all time. Mass Effect, Half-Life, Oblivion, KOTOR, Starcraft, Okami, Diablo, Ico, Bioshock, Doom, Grand Theft Auto, The Legend of Zelda: the list is long, and it has a new member. I am honored to have reviewed Portal 2, and look forward to playing it again tomorrow.", "date": "2011-04-18", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45666126", "grade": null, "id": 218682, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218682", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257792", "first_year": 2002, "id": 162, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/162/g4-tv-x-play/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": 2022, "name": "G4 TV: X-Play", "num_reviews": 748, "url": "http://www.g4tv.com/xplay"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.g4tv.com/games/ps3/64028/portal-2/review/"}, {"citation": "If the start of this review didn\u0027t convince you, hopefully these words will, but I\u0027ll say it again: buy this game. Do not hesitate, do not wait for feedback from friends (they\u0027ll all tell you the same thing, and may spoil things), just trust me on this. There aren\u0027t many things as sure as this purchase, and to dawdle now would only be cheating yourself out of one of the best experiences ever created in this still-burgeoning medium. What an incredible accomplishment. Bravo, Valve.", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45664654", "grade": null, "id": 218763, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218763", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254954", "first_year": 2000, "id": 262, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/262/totalplaystation/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "TotalPlayStation", "num_reviews": 300, "url": "http://www.totalplaystation.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://totalplaystation.com/ps3/portal-2/reviews/9828/"}, {"citation": "There\u0027s so much I want to share with people, as well as so many things left to talk about, but doing so would spoil so much of the surprise and fun that is in this game. Suffice to say, Valve has managed to create a game that bests its predecessor in nearly every regard, and has demonstrated to the world that they still have what it takes to create a game that deserves the hype surrounding it. While it\u0027s unclear if we\u0027ll ever see GLaDOS or Chell again, this much is certain: Portal 2 is one of the best games of this generation.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667543", "grade": "A+", "id": 218675, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218675", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 100.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257831", "first_year": 2000, "id": 6, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/6/1up-usa/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": 2013, "name": "1UP (USA)", "num_reviews": 2415, "url": "http://1up.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 4, "name": "Letter Grade"}, "url": "http://www.1up.com/reviews/portal-2-review"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 couldn\u0027t be Portal, but it\u0027s the next best thing. It\u0027s a longer, funnier, more emotional plummet through Aperture\u0027s perplexing laboratory, and its meticulous detail, perfect pacing, and kinetic, mind-expanding puzzles make it a blazingly memorable experience. It\u0027s so damn memorable, already feel nostalgic about it.", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667544", "grade": null, "id": 218672, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218672", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259547", "first_year": 2000, "id": 9, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/9/gamesradar/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "GamesRadar", "num_reviews": 1473, "url": "http://www.gamesradar.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamesradar.com/xbox360/portal-2/review/portal-2-super-review/a-2011042116105775360108/g-2010030812471136034"}, {"citation": "By concentrating on iteration rather than re-design, Valve have created a sequel that improves upon the original and yet stays true to its memory. The puzzles, the story and the expert way in which players are taught to use the new tools all combine to create what is very possibly the most absorbing game the puzzle genre has ever seen.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667567", "grade": null, "id": 218691, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218691", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259442", "first_year": 2009, "id": 1216, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1216/pc-invasion-inc-gamers/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "PC Invasion (INC Gamers)", "num_reviews": 476, "url": "http://www.pcinvasion.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.incgamers.com/Reviews/1172/portal-2-review"}, {"citation": "With a thrilling single-player quest and one of the best cooperative experiences ever seen to date in a video game, Portal 2 is an all encompassing, mind-blowing gaming experience. It\u0027s got action, intrigue, mystery, personality, another wonderfully addicting ending score, and the best puzzle solving I\u0027ve ever encountered. If you have yet to experience the series, first tackle Portal and then treat yourself to Portal 2. Hands down it\u0027s one of the most original, engaging, and incredible gaming experiences we\u0027ll see this year.", "date": "2011-05-26", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45664652", "grade": null, "id": 218739, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218739", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259461", "first_year": 2009, "id": 1454, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1454/pixlbit/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "PixlBit", "num_reviews": 137, "url": "http://www.pixlbit.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://www.pixlbit.com/reviews?action=showReview\u0026reviewId=320"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 doesn\u2019t have the visual fidelity of a Gears of War or Killzone, but its clean sharp lines and exemplary art design more than make up for any minor deficiencies in the ageing graphics engine. It may not blow you away with its graphics, but Portal 2 was never going to be a visual showcase. Instead, it once again highlights what can be achieved by a team of imaginative, technically brilliant and clearly very intelligent game designers working at the very top of their game. Portal 2 may not have the wow factor of its predecessor, but it delivers just about everything else you would hope from a sequel to a perfect game.", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45655833", "grade": null, "id": 217169, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-217169", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "uk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f7e9f08-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 22, "name": "United Kingdom"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259567", "first_year": 2010, "id": 1481, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1481/brash-games/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Brash Games", "num_reviews": 402, "url": "http://www.brashgames.co.uk/"}, "submitter": {"id": 185943, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/185943/usefulranger/", "name": "Paul Ryan"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.brashgames.co.uk/2011/04/21/portal-2-ps3-review/"}, {"citation": "Okay, complaint time is over. I\u2019ll accept those flaws in exchange for the recorded lunatic rants of Aperture founder Cave Johnson, for Wheatley\u2019s charming stupidity, for a brief glimpse of the human woman who became GLaDOS, and for GLaDOS spending the bulk of the game as a potato.\n \nOh, and the puzzles. I\u0027ll accept the issues for the puzzles.  As a plot-delaying device, they\u2019re pretty awesome. So is it worth those 60 bucks? Hell yes!", "date": "2011-05-04", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667635", "grade": null, "id": 218760, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218760", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258086", "first_year": 2005, "id": 948, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/948/blogcritics-magazine/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "BlogCritics Magazine", "num_reviews": 40, "url": "http://blogcritics.org/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://blogcritics.org/gaming/article/xbox-360-review-portal-2/"}, {"citation": "Sporting some of the best writing and voice work in years (as well as some deviously designed puzzles), Portal 2\u0027s single-player campaign is superior to its predecessor in every way. It\u0027s the co-op mode, however, that makes this 2011\u0027s first must-play game -- even for those gamers that don\u0027t like first-person or puzzle games.", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667636", "grade": null, "id": 218762, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218762", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257678", "first_year": 1996, "id": 10, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/10/gamespy/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": 2013, "name": "GameSpy", "num_reviews": 4936, "url": "http://www.gamespy.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://xbox360.gamespy.com/xbox-360/portal-2/1163500p1.html"}, {"citation": "Quite simply, Portal 2 is a masterpiece. A lesson to every other developer out there on how to tell a story in a video game whilst executing every gameplay mechanic to perfection. Masterful writing, engaging characters, wonderful music, and so forward-thinking that it even includes cross-platform, cloud-saving play between Steam and the PlayStation 3. Utterly essential in every way, Portal 2 is going to be in everyone\u2019s game of the year discussion when the time comes, and it damn well deserves every ounce of praise lavished upon it. Buy Portal 2, you deserve it.", "date": "2011-05-04", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45640409", "grade": null, "id": 215811, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-215811", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "uk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f7e9f08-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 22, "name": "United Kingdom"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257617", "first_year": 2009, "id": 1548, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1548/god-is-a-geek/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "God is a Geek", "num_reviews": 1458, "url": "http://www.godisageek.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.godisageek.com/2011/05/portal-2-review/"}, {"citation": "On s\u0027attendait certes \u00e0 une claque, mais Portal 2 s\u0027av\u00e8re un authentique chef-d\u0027\u0153uvre, une le\u00e7on de game design \u00e0 l\u0027usage de l\u0027industrie. Alliant la pratique d\u0027un gameplay profond \u00e0 un fort attachement au r\u00e9cit, l\u0027aventure solo est le fruit d\u0027une alchimie rarissime entre ludisme et narration qui suffirait d\u00e9j\u00e0 \u00e0 justifier l\u0027engouement. L\u0027ajout d\u0027un mode multijoueur captivant finit de nous convaincre : \u00e0 tous points de vue, il s\u0027agit bien de cet immense jeu cach\u00e9 dans les replis du premier \u00e9pisode, qui n\u0027a jamais tant fait figure d\u0027introduction. Gamers de tous bords, r\u00e9jouissez-vous : Portal 2 rejoint le rang des meilleurs jeux de tous les temps.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45705846", "grade": null, "id": 226718, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-226718", "language": "fr", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "fr", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f4ebb9e-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 8, "name": "France"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254926", "first_year": 2001, "id": 1178, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1178/jeuxvideofr/", "languages": [{"code": "fr", "id": 42, "name": "French", "ordering": 420}], "last_year": null, "name": "Jeuxvideo.fr", "num_reviews": 258, "url": "http://www.jeuxvideo.fr/"}, "submitter": {"id": 183114, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/183114/alsy/", "name": "Alsy"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.jeuxvideo.fr/jeux/portal-2/preview-test-portal-2.html"}, {"citation": "When you review, you need to think about your predilections and your preconceptions. I admit I am a gamer who loves strategy - I am happiest when I am being mentally challenged by my games, and I strive to be smarter and faster than everyone else. I put more value in beating someone in Starcraft than I ever did in my kill/death ratio. However, I can say that while Portal 2 may not be for absolutely everyone, it undeniably deserves a place among the greatest games of all time. Mass Effect, Half-Life, Oblivion, KOTOR, Starcraft, Okami, Diablo, Ico, Bioshock, Doom, Grand Theft Auto, The Legend of Zelda: the list is long, and it has a new member. I am honored to have reviewed Portal 2, and look forward to playing it again tomorrow.", "date": "2011-04-18", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45666119", "grade": null, "id": 218683, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218683", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257792", "first_year": 2002, "id": 162, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/162/g4-tv-x-play/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": 2022, "name": "G4 TV: X-Play", "num_reviews": 748, "url": "http://www.g4tv.com/xplay"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.g4tv.com/games/pc/50487/portal-2/review/"}, {"citation": "On s\u0027attendait certes \u00e0 une claque, mais Portal 2 s\u0027av\u00e8re un authentique chef-d\u0027\u0153uvre, une le\u00e7on de game design \u00e0 l\u0027usage de l\u0027industrie. Alliant la pratique d\u0027un gameplay profond \u00e0 un fort attachement au r\u00e9cit, l\u0027aventure solo est le fruit d\u0027une alchimie rarissime entre ludisme et narration qui suffirait d\u00e9j\u00e0 \u00e0 justifier l\u0027engouement. L\u0027ajout d\u0027un mode multijoueur captivant finit de nous convaincre : \u00e0 tous points de vue, il s\u0027agit bien de cet immense jeu cach\u00e9 dans les replis du premier \u00e9pisode, qui n\u0027a jamais tant fait figure d\u0027introduction. Gamers de tous bords, r\u00e9jouissez-vous : Portal 2 rejoint le rang des meilleurs jeux de tous les temps.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45705854", "grade": null, "id": 226719, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-226719", "language": "fr", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 74, "name": "Macintosh"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "fr", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f4ebb9e-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 8, "name": "France"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254926", "first_year": 2001, "id": 1178, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1178/jeuxvideofr/", "languages": [{"code": "fr", "id": 42, "name": "French", "ordering": 420}], "last_year": null, "name": "Jeuxvideo.fr", "num_reviews": 258, "url": "http://www.jeuxvideo.fr/"}, "submitter": {"id": 183114, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/183114/alsy/", "name": "Alsy"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.jeuxvideo.fr/jeux/portal-2/preview-test-portal-2.html"}, {"citation": "Exception faite d\u0027un second acte un peu en retrait, Portal 2 impose une aventure d\u0027une saveur incomparable, impeccablement mise en sc\u00e8ne et bourr\u00e9e d\u0027autant d\u0027humour que d\u0027ing\u00e9niosit\u00e9. Les nombreuses nouvelles m\u00e9caniques renouvellent les puzzles, la dur\u00e9e de vie exc\u00e8de nos espoirs, le mode Coop\u00e9ratif se d\u00e9guste en ligne ou en local avec d\u00e9lectation, et m\u00eame si la fin ne saurait \u00eatre aussi savoureuse que celle du premier, elle conclut un rollercoaster de sensations pures et de trouvailles de g\u00e9nie qui forcent le respect.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45669124", "grade": null, "id": 218858, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218858", "language": "fr", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 74, "name": "Macintosh"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "fr", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f4ebb9e-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 8, "name": "France"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252458", "first_year": 2006, "id": 1465, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1465/gameblogfr/", "languages": [{"code": "fr", "id": 42, "name": "French", "ordering": 420}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gameblog.fr", "num_reviews": 1092, "url": "http://www.gameblog.fr/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://www.gameblog.fr/test_923_portal-2-360-ps3-pc-mac"}, {"citation": "Impatience aside, Portal 2 is an exceptionally well-crafted, intelligent, entertaining, humorous game. You will laugh. You will feel like a freaking genius. You will want more. And yes, you will probably be hearing quotes from Portal 2 for the next three years.", "date": "2011-04-22", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667784", "grade": "A", "id": 218847, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218847", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 74, "name": "Macintosh"}, "score": 100.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258085", "first_year": 1996, "id": 4, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/4/game-revolution/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Game Revolution", "num_reviews": 3224, "url": "http://www.gamerevolution.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 4, "name": "Letter Grade"}, "url": "http://www.gamerevolution.com/review/mac/portal-2"}, {"citation": "When it comes to making video games, a strong argument can be made that Valve is among the best out there. They are like the Pixar of the videogame industry, setting the standard for others, never disappointing, and delivering product on a consistent, predictable schedule. That last fact actually only applies to Pixar, but you get the idea. Portal 2 is an absolutely worthy successor to the original, and it is, objectively, a better game. Nothing will ever replace the first time you solved a puzzle in the original Portal, or when GLaDOS began to serenade you during the end credits, but you will find yourself just as absorbed into the world and congratulating yourself on your personal genius every few minutes. Portal 2 is a perfect example of what video games should be, and there is no reason to pass it up.", "date": "2011-04-26", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667743", "grade": null, "id": 218826, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218826", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 74, "name": "Macintosh"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257853", "first_year": 2005, "id": 522, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/522/gamernode/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gamernode", "num_reviews": 531, "url": "http://www.gamernode.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://gamernode.com/reviews/10487-portal-2-review/index.html"}, {"citation": "Impatience aside, Portal 2 is an exceptionally well-crafted, intelligent, entertaining, humorous game. You will laugh. You will feel like a freaking genius. You will want more. And yes, you will probably be hearing quotes from Portal 2 for the next three years.", "date": "2011-04-22", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667780", "grade": "A", "id": 218846, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218846", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 100.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258085", "first_year": 1996, "id": 4, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/4/game-revolution/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Game Revolution", "num_reviews": 3224, "url": "http://www.gamerevolution.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 4, "name": "Letter Grade"}, "url": "http://www.gamerevolution.com/review/xbox360/portal-2"}, {"citation": "So do we need Portal 2? Do I need it? Maybe not, but I\u0027m sure as hell glad it exists. The portal aspect has probably reached its zenith in Portal 2, and given the way the game ends I don\u0027t think there\u0027s much room for a Portal 3. Indeed, I would say it\u0027s time for portals to branch their physics-defying awesomeness into other genres. Think of it\u2014someday we critics might snarkily dismiss \"run of the mill portals\" as a mundane, outdated mechanic like key fetch quests or unskippable cut-scenes. However, in the meantime we can give Portal 2 the jubilant praise it so rightly deserves.", "date": "2011-05-07", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667525", "grade": null, "id": 218662, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218662", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252576", "first_year": 1998, "id": 19, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/19/gamecriticscom/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "GameCritics.com", "num_reviews": 1250, "url": "http://www.gamecritics.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamecritics.com/richard-naik/portal-2-review"}, {"citation": "In conclusion, Portal 2 is a textbook example of how to make a great game, but nothing more. Its narrative focus robs the game of its predecessor\u2019s quirky charm, but gives players a much stronger sense of purpose \u2013 medium-term objectives roll by at a steady pace, like Half-Life 2 without the boring bits \u2013 and there is still plenty of scope in discussing the psycho-sexual imagery of splattering a level with gel. Is this the last we will hear of GLaDOS? I doubt it, but I\u2019m hoping she\u2019ll now take some time out from her solo career to provide backing vocals in Half-Life 2: Episode 3.", "date": "2011-04-22", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667537", "grade": null, "id": 218670, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218670", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "uk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f7e9f08-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 22, "name": "United Kingdom"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259406", "first_year": 2001, "id": 121, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/121/darkzero/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "DarkZero", "num_reviews": 914, "url": "http://darkzero.co.uk/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://darkzero.co.uk/game-reviews/portal-2-pc-ps3-xbox-360-mac/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 couldn\u0027t be Portal, but it\u0027s the next best thing. It\u0027s a longer, funnier, more emotional plummet through Aperture\u0027s perplexing laboratory, and its meticulous detail, perfect pacing, and kinetic, mind-expanding puzzles make it a blazingly memorable experience. It\u0027s so damn memorable, already feel nostalgic about it.", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667538", "grade": null, "id": 218671, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218671", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259547", "first_year": 2000, "id": 9, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/9/gamesradar/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "GamesRadar", "num_reviews": 1473, "url": "http://www.gamesradar.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamesradar.com/pc/portal-2/review/portal-2-super-review/a-20110420104940949003/g-20100308124447849051"}, {"citation": "There\u0027s so much I want to share with people, as well as so many things left to talk about, but doing so would spoil so much of the surprise and fun that is in this game. Suffice to say, Valve has managed to create a game that bests its predecessor in nearly every regard, and has demonstrated to the world that they still have what it takes to create a game that deserves the hype surrounding it. While it\u0027s unclear if we\u0027ll ever see GLaDOS or Chell again, this much is certain: Portal 2 is one of the best games of this generation.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667539", "grade": "A+", "id": 218676, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218676", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 100.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257831", "first_year": 2000, "id": 6, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/6/1up-usa/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": 2013, "name": "1UP (USA)", "num_reviews": 2415, "url": "http://1up.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 4, "name": "Letter Grade"}, "url": "http://www.1up.com/reviews/portal-2-review"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is the best Valve release to date, and one of the most refreshing, exciting and innovative games we\u0027ve ever played. There\u0027s no doubt in our minds that numerous Game of the Year awards have now already been shotgunned, and with mighty good reason. If you thought the original Portal was a masterpiece, prepare to have your mind blown.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667540", "grade": null, "id": 218677, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218677", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "hr", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/e956ef22-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 6, "name": "Croatia"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257789", "first_year": 2002, "id": 94, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/94/gamewatcher-strategy-informer/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "GameWatcher / Strategy Informer", "num_reviews": 908, "url": "http://www.gamewatcher.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.strategyinformer.com/pc/portal2/1462/review.html"}, {"citation": "I think you knew all along this was going to be great. Fantastic, even. All the same, I don\u0027t think you\u0027ll be prepared for it being this good. I may have buttoned my lip in terms of concrete spoilers, but a mere ten minutes here will yield more memorable moments than you\u0027re likely to squeeze out of the entirety of most other games this year. In all aspects of its design, Portal 2 is genius.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667547", "grade": null, "id": 218685, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218685", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259424", "first_year": 2001, "id": 611, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/611/videogamercom/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "videogamer.com", "num_reviews": 1394, "url": "http://www.videogamer.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.videogamer.com/pc/portal_2/review.html"}, {"citation": "Exception faite d\u0027un second acte un peu en retrait, Portal 2 impose une aventure d\u0027une saveur incomparable, impeccablement mise en sc\u00e8ne et bourr\u00e9e d\u0027autant d\u0027humour que d\u0027ing\u00e9niosit\u00e9. Les nombreuses nouvelles m\u00e9caniques renouvellent les puzzles, la dur\u00e9e de vie exc\u00e8de nos espoirs, le mode Coop\u00e9ratif se d\u00e9guste en ligne ou en local avec d\u00e9lectation, et m\u00eame si la fin ne saurait \u00eatre aussi savoureuse que celle du premier, elle conclut un rollercoaster de sensations pures et de trouvailles de g\u00e9nie qui forcent le respect.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45697275", "grade": null, "id": 218859, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218859", "language": "fr", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "fr", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f4ebb9e-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 8, "name": "France"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252458", "first_year": 2006, "id": 1465, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1465/gameblogfr/", "languages": [{"code": "fr", "id": 42, "name": "French", "ordering": 420}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gameblog.fr", "num_reviews": 1092, "url": "http://www.gameblog.fr/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://www.gameblog.fr/test_923_portal-2-360-ps3-pc-mac"}, {"citation": "Genius is an often overused word but Valve\u0027s work on Portal 2 is genius in the truest sense. The studio has exhibited exceptional creativity in the game, even compared to some of its other masterpieces. If we could give it 11/10, we would.", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45697274", "grade": null, "id": 218666, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218666", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259534", "first_year": 1996, "id": 100, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/100/totalvideogames-tvg/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "TotalVideoGames (TVG)", "num_reviews": 359, "url": "http://www.totalvideogames.net/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.totalvideogames.com/Portal-2/review-16411.html"}, {"citation": "Sporting some of the best writing and voice work in years (as well as some deviously designed puzzles), Portal 2\u0027s single-player campaign is superior to its predecessor in every way. It\u0027s the co-op mode, however, that makes this 2011\u0027s first must-play game -- even for those gamers that don\u0027t like first-person or puzzle games.", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45555371", "grade": null, "id": 211096, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-211096", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257678", "first_year": 1996, "id": 10, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/10/gamespy/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": 2013, "name": "GameSpy", "num_reviews": 4936, "url": "http://www.gamespy.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 55856, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/55856/scaryfun/", "name": "Scaryfun"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://pc.gamespy.com/pc/portal-2/1163550p1.html"}, {"citation": "Is Portal 2 a worthy successor to one of the most surprisingly lovable games in recent memory? I\u0027ve tried to figure out a way to answer that simple question with any response other than a resounding \"yes\", but I\u0027m completely incapable of it. With this sequel, Valve has ramped up the brain-cramping puzzle elements and expanded the cast with immensely lovable characters, and they did it just enough to make sure the whole thing feels fresh and interesting for the longer campaign. I think it\u0027s very likely that you\u0027ll come away with a huge smile on your face once you\u0027re done. Some PC gamers will wait until the inevitable Steam sale hits, but no matter what you pay for it, I\u0027m betting that Portal 2 will completely pull you into its charming world and make you lose track of time for hours on end. Frankly, not many recent games have been doing that.", "date": "2011-04-20", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45555382", "grade": null, "id": 211097, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-211097", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254221", "first_year": 2001, "id": 379, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/379/atomic-gamer/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Atomic Gamer", "num_reviews": 367, "url": "http://www.atomicgamer.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 55856, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/55856/scaryfun/", "name": "Scaryfun"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.atomicgamer.com/articles/1237/portal-2-review"}, {"citation": "On s\u0027attendait certes \u00e0 une claque, mais Portal 2 s\u0027av\u00e8re un authentique chef-d\u0027\u0153uvre, une le\u00e7on de game design \u00e0 l\u0027usage de l\u0027industrie. Alliant la pratique d\u0027un gameplay profond \u00e0 un fort attachement au r\u00e9cit, l\u0027aventure solo est le fruit d\u0027une alchimie rarissime entre ludisme et narration qui suffirait d\u00e9j\u00e0 \u00e0 justifier l\u0027engouement. L\u0027ajout d\u0027un mode multijoueur captivant finit de nous convaincre : \u00e0 tous points de vue, il s\u0027agit bien de cet immense jeu cach\u00e9 dans les replis du premier \u00e9pisode, qui n\u0027a jamais tant fait figure d\u0027introduction. Gamers de tous bords, r\u00e9jouissez-vous : Portal 2 rejoint le rang des meilleurs jeux de tous les temps.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45704966", "grade": null, "id": 226716, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-226716", "language": "fr", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "fr", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f4ebb9e-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 8, "name": "France"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254926", "first_year": 2001, "id": 1178, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1178/jeuxvideofr/", "languages": [{"code": "fr", "id": 42, "name": "French", "ordering": 420}], "last_year": null, "name": "Jeuxvideo.fr", "num_reviews": 258, "url": "http://www.jeuxvideo.fr/"}, "submitter": {"id": 183114, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/183114/alsy/", "name": "Alsy"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.jeuxvideo.fr/jeux/portal-2/preview-test-portal-2.html"}, {"citation": "Portal is perfect. Portal 2 is not. It\u0027s something better than that. It\u0027s human: hot-blooded, silly, poignant, irreverent, base, ingenious and loving. It\u0027s never less than a pure video game, but it\u0027s often more, and it will no doubt stand as one of the best entertainments in any medium at the end of this year. It\u0027s a masterpiece.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45556712", "grade": null, "id": 211098, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-211098", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "uk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f7e9f08-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 22, "name": "United Kingdom"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259334", "first_year": 1999, "id": 13, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/13/eurogamernet-uk/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Eurogamer.net (UK)", "num_reviews": 5556, "url": "http://www.eurogamer.net/"}, "submitter": {"id": 55856, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/55856/scaryfun/", "name": "Scaryfun"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2011-04-19-portal-2-review"}, {"citation": "That\u0027s Portal 2, a game that gleefully throws new ideas at a core concept and makes them stick. For sheer design, its only competition is Super Mario Galaxy 2. In the same way that Nintendo build playgrounds around Mario, Portal 2 crafts its world so that the star is always that piece of equipment in your hands. A diverse piece of engineering that opens up staggering possibilities, sometimes supplemented by just a box, a button and a door. Then Valve wrap it all up in their astute understanding of video game storytelling, providing a world and characters that stick in the mind even after those credits roll. Funny, clever, mentally stimulating and always good honest fun, Portal 2 effortlessly represents the medium at its very best.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45670721", "grade": null, "id": 219053, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-219053", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "uk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f7e9f08-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 22, "name": "United Kingdom"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257841", "first_year": 2008, "id": 1504, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1504/telegraph-the/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Telegraph, The", "num_reviews": 164, "url": "http://www.telegraph.co.uk/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.telegraph.co.uk/technology/video-games/8458871/Portal-2-review.html"}, {"citation": "Genius is an often overused word but Valve\u0027s work on Portal 2 is genius in the truest sense. The studio has exhibited exceptional creativity in the game, even compared to some of its other masterpieces. If we could give it 11/10, we would.", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45491531", "grade": null, "id": 218664, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218664", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259534", "first_year": 1996, "id": 100, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/100/totalvideogames-tvg/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "TotalVideoGames (TVG)", "num_reviews": 359, "url": "http://www.totalvideogames.net/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.totalvideogames.com/Portal-2/review-16411.html"}, {"citation": "If you had any interest in the first Portal, or if you just enjoy having your puzzler puzzled and your funny bone tickled, you owe it to yourself to play Portal 2.", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=4295242131", "grade": null, "id": 479886, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-479886", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "au", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/b24379d8-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 3, "name": "Australia"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=1935980690", "first_year": 2009, "id": 2245, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/2245/capsule-computers/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Capsule Computers", "num_reviews": 1269, "url": "http://www.capsulecomputers.com.au/"}, "submitter": {"id": 65110, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/65110/tim-janssen/", "name": "Tim Janssen"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "https://www.capsulecomputers.com.au/portal-2-review/"}, {"citation": "I don\u2019t think Portal 2 will end up being the watershed \u201cah ha!\u201d moment that Portal was. There was a certain magic to the first game that will never be recaptured. That being said, Portal 2 is better in just about every way possible. The puzzles are more intricate, the writing is better than most movies or TV shows I\u2019ve seen, and the production value is everything you\u2019ve come to expect from the guys that brought you Half-Life. Portal 2 certainly isn\u2019t a perfect (no game is) but it is one that I can\u2019t recommend enough.", "date": "2011-04-18", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45669146", "grade": null, "id": 218864, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218864", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259512", "first_year": 2010, "id": 1522, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1522/inside-gaming/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Inside Gaming", "num_reviews": 70, "url": "http://www.insidegamingdaily.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://blog.machinima.com/insidegaming/2011/04/18/portal-2-review/"}, {"citation": "When it comes to making video games, a strong argument can be made that Valve is among the best out there. They are like the Pixar of the videogame industry, setting the standard for others, never disappointing, and delivering product on a consistent, predictable schedule. That last fact actually only applies to Pixar, but you get the idea. Portal 2 is an absolutely worthy successor to the original, and it is, objectively, a better game. Nothing will ever replace the first time you solved a puzzle in the original Portal, or when GLaDOS began to serenade you during the end credits, but you will find yourself just as absorbed into the world and congratulating yourself on your personal genius every few minutes. Portal 2 is a perfect example of what video games should be, and there is no reason to pass it up.", "date": "2011-04-27", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45739767", "grade": null, "id": 218823, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218823", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257853", "first_year": 2005, "id": 522, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/522/gamernode/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gamernode", "num_reviews": 531, "url": "http://www.gamernode.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://gamernode.com/reviews/10478-portal-2-review/index.html"}, {"citation": "Valve\u0027s stated ambition was to leave you wanting more, and in this it\u0027s just a bit too successful: while it\u0027s far bigger than the original, an experienced pair of players will still be able to burn through the entire package in a weekend. While it\u0027s worth replaying to catch the dialogue you missed the first time round - a spectacular rarity in any game - and to hunt out the hidden Rat Man rooms, there isn\u0027t enough variety in the way you solve puzzles to sustain repeat runthroughs. We\u0027re going to need DLC, and plenty of it, to keep our co-op partnership going. Still, it seems unreasonable to penalise a game for being so good you want to keep playing it. While you won\u0027t spend as long on Portal 2 as the infinite online of, say, CoD, its shorter, more concentrated high is irresistible.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45739780", "grade": null, "id": 219016, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-219016", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "uk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f7e9f08-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 22, "name": "United Kingdom"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257937", "first_year": 2003, "id": 318, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/318/official-xbox-magazine-uk/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Official Xbox Magazine (UK)", "num_reviews": 172, "url": "http://www.oxm.co.uk/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.oxm.co.uk/27634/portal-2-review-xbox-360/"}, {"citation": "I think you knew all along this was going to be great. Fantastic, even. All the same, I don\u0027t think you\u0027ll be prepared for it being this good. I may have buttoned my lip in terms of concrete spoilers, but a mere ten minutes here will yield more memorable moments than you\u0027re likely to squeeze out of the entirety of most other games this year. In all aspects of its design, Portal 2 is genius.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45737950", "grade": null, "id": 218686, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218686", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259424", "first_year": 2001, "id": 611, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/611/videogamercom/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "videogamer.com", "num_reviews": 1394, "url": "http://www.videogamer.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.videogamer.com/xbox360/portal_2/review.html"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 \u00e9 s\u00f3 aquele jogo. Entra de imediato para a estreita margem dos imperd\u00edveis. Um cl\u00e1ssico imediato, um propulsor de originalidade e inova\u00e7\u00e3o, onde tudo est\u00e1 longe de acabar \u00e0 lei da bala, mas dentro dos limites da f\u00edsica. Espica\u00e7ando a mente humana, revela todos os seus atributos num esquema de puzzles t\u00e3o satisfat\u00f3rios e plenos de incertezas como leg\u00edtimos. \u00c9 certo que este jogo encerra uma sequ\u00eancia, mas \u00e9 muito mais engenhoso, rigoroso e admir\u00e1vel.", "date": "2011-05-13", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45665987", "grade": null, "id": 218785, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218785", "language": "pt", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 10.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "pt", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f68e8ac-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 18, "name": "Portugal"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252466", "first_year": 2008, "id": 1065, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1065/eurogamerpt/", "languages": [{"code": "pt", "id": 113, "name": "Portuguese", "ordering": 1130}], "last_year": null, "name": "Eurogamer.pt", "num_reviews": 287, "url": "http://www.eurogamer.pt/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.eurogamer.pt/articles/2011-05-13-portal-2-analise"}, {"citation": "Exception faite d\u0027un second acte un peu en retrait, Portal 2 impose une aventure d\u0027une saveur incomparable, impeccablement mise en sc\u00e8ne et bourr\u00e9e d\u0027autant d\u0027humour que d\u0027ing\u00e9niosit\u00e9. Les nombreuses nouvelles m\u00e9caniques renouvellent les puzzles, la dur\u00e9e de vie exc\u00e8de nos espoirs, le mode Coop\u00e9ratif se d\u00e9guste en ligne ou en local avec d\u00e9lectation, et m\u00eame si la fin ne saurait \u00eatre aussi savoureuse que celle du premier, elle conclut un rollercoaster de sensations pures et de trouvailles de g\u00e9nie qui forcent le respect.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45669118", "grade": null, "id": 218857, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218857", "language": "fr", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "fr", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f4ebb9e-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 8, "name": "France"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252458", "first_year": 2006, "id": 1465, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1465/gameblogfr/", "languages": [{"code": "fr", "id": 42, "name": "French", "ordering": 420}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gameblog.fr", "num_reviews": 1092, "url": "http://www.gameblog.fr/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://www.gameblog.fr/test_923_portal-2-360-ps3-pc-mac"}, {"citation": "When you review, you need to think about your predilections and your preconceptions. I admit I am a gamer who loves strategy - I am happiest when I am being mentally challenged by my games, and I strive to be smarter and faster than everyone else. I put more value in beating someone in Starcraft than I ever did in my kill/death ratio. However, I can say that while Portal 2 may not be for absolutely everyone, it undeniably deserves a place among the greatest games of all time. Mass Effect, Half-Life, Oblivion, KOTOR, Starcraft, Okami, Diablo, Ico, Bioshock, Doom, Grand Theft Auto, The Legend of Zelda: the list is long, and it has a new member. I am honored to have reviewed Portal 2, and look forward to playing it again tomorrow.", "date": "2011-04-18", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45737949", "grade": null, "id": 218684, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218684", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 100.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 5.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257792", "first_year": 2002, "id": 162, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/162/g4-tv-x-play/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": 2022, "name": "G4 TV: X-Play", "num_reviews": 748, "url": "http://www.g4tv.com/xplay"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.g4tv.com/games/xbox-360/63787/Portal-2/review/"}, {"citation": "En resumen, si eres una persona que no necesita matar algo cada cinco segundos para divertirse y adem\u00e1s cuentas con un cerebro m\u00ednimamente desarrollado y un amor por el medio, no hay absolutamente ninguna raz\u00f3n por la cual no debas darle tu dinero duramente ganado a Valve. Si por el contrario no te gusta usar el cerebro y prefieres disparar ciegamente... pues no s\u00e9 c\u00f3mo has llegado hasta esta parte del art\u00edculo. Ah, espera, que ven\u00edas a mirar la nota y est\u00e1s leyendo esto de rebote, \u00bfno? Pues mira qu\u00e9 notaza, mira. Es mejor que todos los juegos que te gustan.", "date": "2011-04-30", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45690576", "grade": null, "id": 218692, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218692", "language": "es", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 98.0, "platform": {"id": 74, "name": "Macintosh"}, "score": 98.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "es", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f789a9a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 20, "name": "Spain"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257812", "first_year": 2003, "id": 496, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/496/viciojuegoscom-uvejuegoscom/", "languages": [{"code": "es", "id": 133, "name": "Spanish", "ordering": 1330}], "last_year": null, "name": "VicioJuegos.com / uVeJuegos.com", "num_reviews": 738, "url": "http://www.viciojuegos.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.viciojuegos.com/analisis/Portal-2/Las-puertas-de-la-ciencia/5793/39690"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is a game of two unexpected halves, a brilliant single player campaign that proves that the proof of concept nature of the original game can be fleshed out into a much larger, varied, and consequently more memorable experience. And a second half that proves that the Portal gameplay can also provide a great multiplayer experience through the introduction of a co-op campaign as lengthy as the single player campaign, and one that somehow though the introduction of a another player manages to elevate the gameplay as opposed to hamper it. Portal 2 is a triumph in every sense of the word, a wonderful experience from start to finish and one that you won\u2019t soon forget.", "date": "2011-04-22", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45648086", "grade": null, "id": 216505, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-216505", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 98.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.8, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "au", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/b24379d8-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 3, "name": "Australia"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252470", "first_year": 2007, "id": 1555, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1555/ausgamers/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "AusGamers", "num_reviews": 440, "url": "http://www.ausgamers.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.ausgamers.com/games/portal-2/review/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 may be the best game of 2011. It may be the best game of all-time. It is certainly the best game you can play right now. I loved every moment I spent with Portal 2. I\u2019m even enjoying looking at the game sitting on my shelf knowing how much fun I will have again someday when I revisit Aperture Science, alone or hopefully with a friend who may not have played the game. Portal 2 proves that you don\u2019t have to kill things to make a great game and more importantly\u2026science is fun!", "date": "2011-04-25", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45514488", "grade": null, "id": 218966, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218966", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 98.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.8, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259516", "first_year": 1998, "id": 108, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/108/game-chronicles/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Game Chronicles", "num_reviews": 2355, "url": "http://www.gamechronicles.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamechronicles.com/reviews/pc/portal2/portal2.htm"}, {"citation": "Without a doubt, Portal 2, if not the best game of 2011, will be amongst the top of the heap when the year closes out. The fantastic story, excellent pacing, interesting and engaging puzzles and other incredible facets to the game make it one that people should experience at any cost. If you know anyone who has never seen Portal in action, put them in front of a monitor or TV screen and let them see even just one puzzle; if they aren\u2019t impressed, then I\u2019d recommend getting new friends.", "date": "2011-04-26", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45670655", "grade": null, "id": 219019, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-219019", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 97.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.7, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "ca", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9fa117cc-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 5, "name": "Canada"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259377", "first_year": 2001, "id": 920, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/920/gamefocus/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "GameFocus", "num_reviews": 395, "url": "http://www.gamefocus.ca/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamefocus.ca/?nav=reviewCard\u0026fid=9791"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is daarom ook de game waar gamers al sinds de eerste Portal op zitten te wachten. Portal wordt volgens velen al gezien als een perfecte game, maar Portal 2 is gewoon op ieder vlak verbeterd en vernieuwd. Het is meer, het is beter en het is de droom van iedere gamer. Met geweldige humor en boeiende personages sleept de game je mee en laat je niet meer los. Valve bewijst maar weer eens een geweldige ontwikkelaar te zijn en levert met Portal 2 wellicht de beste game af die deze generatie ooit heeft gekend.", "date": "2011-04-27", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667754", "grade": null, "id": 218838, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218838", "language": "nl", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 97.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.7, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "nl", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/c4f2d308-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 16, "name": "The Netherlands"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257794", "first_year": 2007, "id": 1154, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1154/xgn/", "languages": [{"code": "nl", "id": 34, "name": "Dutch", "ordering": 340}], "last_year": null, "name": "XGN", "num_reviews": 631, "url": "http://www.xgn.nl/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.xgn.nl/pc/review/26547/portal-2/"}, {"citation": "After completing Portal 2, it\u0027s great that Valve have continued on their original premise because this is the perfect game for those gamers caught in the doldrums of endless first person shooters, racers and sport games. Originality is the key here and Valve have succeeded on just about every surreal and cerebral level with its puzzles. The introduction of new characters into the story plus the wit and sarcasm of both Wheatley and my favourite AI creation in existence, GLaDOS truly create one of the most unique gaming experiences of 2011. Just make sure you leave your gun at the door when you play this one. Just be warned that this is the most frustrating game that I have ever played as well.", "date": "2011-04", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667752", "grade": null, "id": 218834, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218834", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 97.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score":