code": "nl", "id": 34, "name": "Dutch", "ordering": 340}], "last_year": null, "name": "XGN", "num_reviews": 631, "url": "http://www.xgn.nl/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.xgn.nl/360/review/26547/portal-2/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is daarom ook de game waar gamers al sinds de eerste Portal op zitten te wachten. Portal wordt volgens velen al gezien als een perfecte game, maar Portal 2 is gewoon op ieder vlak verbeterd en vernieuwd. Het is meer, het is beter en het is de droom van iedere gamer. Met geweldige humor en boeiende personages sleept de game je mee en laat je niet meer los. Valve bewijst maar weer eens een geweldige ontwikkelaar te zijn en levert met Portal 2 wellicht de beste game af die deze generatie ooit heeft gekend.", "date": "2011-04-27", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667753", "grade": null, "id": 218836, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218836", "language": "nl", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 97.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.7, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "nl", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/c4f2d308-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 16, "name": "The Netherlands"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257794", "first_year": 2007, "id": 1154, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1154/xgn/", "languages": [{"code": "nl", "id": 34, "name": "Dutch", "ordering": 340}], "last_year": null, "name": "XGN", "num_reviews": 631, "url": "http://www.xgn.nl/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.xgn.nl/ps3/review/26547/portal-2/"}, {"citation": "Without a doubt, Portal 2, if not the best game of 2011, will be amongst the top of the heap when the year closes out. The fantastic story, excellent pacing, interesting and engaging puzzles and other incredible facets to the game make it one that people should experience at any cost. If you know anyone who has never seen Portal in action, put them in front of a monitor or TV screen and let them see even just one puzzle; if they aren\u2019t impressed, then I\u2019d recommend getting new friends.", "date": "2011-04-25", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667755", "grade": null, "id": 218840, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218840", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 97.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.7, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "ca", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9fa117cc-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 5, "name": "Canada"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259377", "first_year": 2001, "id": 920, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/920/gamefocus/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "GameFocus", "num_reviews": 395, "url": "http://www.gamefocus.ca/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamefocus.ca/reviews/9790.html"}, {"citation": "Having not released a game in almost two years, Valve had to come out with something special and Portal 2 really hits the spot. There is an almost immeasurable amount of polish on this game and we should expect nothing less from the developer that brought us Half-Life 2. Playing Portal 2 is fun beyond comparison delivering an experience unlike any other available in gaming. Complete the single player mode and you will most certainly feel smarter for it, not to mention laugh your socks off in to the bargain. Portal 2 is not only the feel good hit of the summer but the feel good hit of the year.", "date": "2011-04-26", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45670664", "grade": null, "id": 219027, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-219027", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 97.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 97.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "uk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f7e9f08-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 22, "name": "United Kingdom"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257798", "first_year": 2001, "id": 79, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/79/playtm/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Play.tm", "num_reviews": 1010, "url": "http://play.tm/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.play.tm/review/33394/portal-2/"}, {"citation": "With Portal 2, Valve willfully defied common logic by creating an exceptionally detailed yet mainstream friendly experience out of, essentially, a puzzle game.  While a dozen identical shooters try and seize the hardcore and casual crapfests prey on the weak, Portal 2 sneaks in and goes for both with exceptional characters, hilarious writing, and genuinely inspired puzzles - all through the affable lens of a first person perspective. Or, in other words, Valve brought a novelty size calculator to a gun show and confidently managed first prize. Again.", "date": "2011-04-22", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45670666", "grade": null, "id": 219030, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-219030", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 96.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.6, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259380", "first_year": 2008, "id": 860, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/860/digital-chumps/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Digital Chumps", "num_reviews": 888, "url": "http://digitalchumps.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://digitalchumps.com/game-reviews/34-360/7280-portal-2.html"}, {"citation": "Es dif\u00edcil explicar muchas de las virtudes de Portal 2 sin estropear sorpresas que aparecen en el segundo tercio de la historia, y no queremos hacerlo. Arranca algo lento y es f\u00e1cil tener la sensaci\u00f3n de \"esto ya lo he jugado\", como si se tratase de una expansi\u00f3n con unos gr\u00e1ficos algo mejores, pero la \u00faltima obra de Valve guarda muchos momentos \u00e9picos en sus entra\u00f1as y Aperture Science es algo m\u00e1s que salas de test para conejillos de indias. Quiz\u00e1s la naturaleza del g\u00e9nero hace que el valor de rejugabilidad sea reducido, una vez conoces todas las soluciones terminar el juego m\u00e1s r\u00e1pidamente o desbloquear todos los logros y trofeos se convierte en el objetivo principal, juego cooperativo aparte. En definitiva, no alcanza la perfecci\u00f3n, pero Valve se acerca peligrosamente a ella.", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667572", "grade": null, "id": 218701, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218701", "language": "es", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 96.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.6, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "es", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f789a9a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 20, "name": "Spain"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258061", "first_year": 2000, "id": 813, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/813/vandal-online/", "languages": [{"code": "es", "id": 133, "name": "Spanish", "ordering": 1330}], "last_year": null, "name": "Vandal Online", "num_reviews": 1500, "url": "http://www.vandal.net/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.vandal.net/analisis/pc/portal-2/8775"}, {"citation": "It\u0027s hard to sum up a game like Portal 2. It doesn\u2019t have enough shooting to be a shooter, but it\u0027s not abstract enough to be a puzzle game. It\u0027s unique and challenging enough to attract the hardcore, but its offbeat humor and intuitive design will make it a hit with casual players. I\u0027ll forget about categories and call it what it is: the most original game in years (a big accomplishment for a sequel). It\u0027s also Valve\u0027s biggest console success. The game looks great on PC, Mac, Xbox 360, and PS3, but the proverbial cake goes to the PS3 version, which comes with a free computer copy. On top of that, Portal 2 is that rare game with crossover multiplayer support, meaning PS3 players and computer gamers can portal it up together. That means if you have a laptop and a PS3, there\u2019s no reason to play in cramped split-screen mode. That is, unless the PSN is still down by the time this goes up.", "date": "2011-05-03", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45499833", "grade": null, "id": 218690, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218690", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 96.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.6, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259420", "first_year": 1999, "id": 187, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/187/gaming-target/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gaming Target", "num_reviews": 1237, "url": "http://www.gamingtarget.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamingtarget.com/article.php?artid=12364\u0026gameid=6668"}, {"citation": "Disregarding the Robot Enrichment center \u2013 and I am actively disregarding it \u2013 Portal 2 has some of the most entertaining writing and voice acting of any videogame, ever. It has some of the most innovative and rewarding puzzles, ever. And it contains one of the best co-op experiences, ever. That is a lot of superlatives for one game \u2013 and all are seemingly unrelated. What a bizarre amalgamation. I mean, good writing, innovative puzzles, and engaging co-op \u2013 have those three things ever been in a game together? Good writing is only supposed to exist in role-playing games and the occasional first-person shooter. Innovative puzzles? Well, those are reserved for budget indie titles. And we typically only see engaging co-op in shooters, mostly violent ones. But Portal 2 has it all and is, simply put, phenomenal.", "date": "2011-04-23", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45500861", "grade": null, "id": 218702, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218702", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 96.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.6, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257800", "first_year": 2005, "id": 697, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/697/hooked-gamers/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Hooked Gamers", "num_reviews": 2431, "url": "http://www.hookedgamers.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.hookedgamers.com/pc/portal_2/review/article-707.html"}, {"citation": "Sentido del humor, rompecabezas tremendamente ingeniosos y h\u00e1bil mezcla de destreza cerebral con habilidad... \u00bfImposible de combinar? En absoluto. Valve demuestra una vez m\u00e1s su incre\u00edble maestr\u00eda con uno de los mejores videojuegos en lo que va de a\u00f1o. Portal 2 es, al mismo tiempo, imaginativo, estimulante, adictivo y cargado de momentos hilarantes, y como tal puede ser recomendado a cualquier tipo de p\u00fablico (sin importar edad ni condici\u00f3n) con la seguridad del acierto.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667487", "grade": null, "id": 218698, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218698", "language": "es", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 96.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.6, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "es", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f789a9a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 20, "name": "Spain"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257761", "first_year": 2004, "id": 444, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/444/3d-juegos/", "languages": [{"code": "es", "id": 133, "name": "Spanish", "ordering": 1330}], "last_year": null, "name": "3D Juegos", "num_reviews": 1031, "url": "http://www.3djuegos.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.3djuegos.com/juegos/analisis/3524/0/portal-2/"}, {"citation": "En definitiva, c\u00f3mprate de una vez Portal 2 y deja de leer an\u00e1lisis como este porque todos te dir\u00e1n lo mismo: es una obra maestra. Valve ha creado un juego \u00fanico que supera en todo a su antecesor, del que toma los mecanismos b\u00e1sicos para explotarlos hasta l\u00edmites que te sorprender\u00e1n. Ni los m\u00e1s optimistas esperaban una continuaci\u00f3n tan formidable.", "date": "2011-05-26", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667571", "grade": null, "id": 218695, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218695", "language": "es", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 96.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 96.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "es", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f789a9a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 20, "name": "Spain"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257812", "first_year": 2003, "id": 496, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/496/viciojuegoscom-uvejuegoscom/", "languages": [{"code": "es", "id": 133, "name": "Spanish", "ordering": 1330}], "last_year": null, "name": "VicioJuegos.com / uVeJuegos.com", "num_reviews": 738, "url": "http://www.viciojuegos.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.viciojuegos.com/analisis/Portal-2/log2---Clase-maestra-sobre-continuaciones/5797/41453"}, {"citation": "It\u0027s hard to sum up a game like Portal 2. It doesn\u2019t have enough shooting to be a shooter, but it\u0027s not abstract enough to be a puzzle game. It\u0027s unique and challenging enough to attract the hardcore, but its offbeat humor and intuitive design will make it a hit with casual players. I\u0027ll forget about categories and call it what it is: the most original game in years (a big accomplishment for a sequel). It\u0027s also Valve\u0027s biggest console success. The game looks great on PC, Mac, Xbox 360, and PS3.", "date": "2011-05-03", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667566", "grade": null, "id": 218689, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218689", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 96.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.6, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259420", "first_year": 1999, "id": 187, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/187/gaming-target/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gaming Target", "num_reviews": 1237, "url": "http://www.gamingtarget.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamingtarget.com/article.php?artid=12364\u0026gameid=6669"}, {"citation": "Es dif\u00edcil explicar muchas de las virtudes de Portal 2 sin estropear sorpresas que aparecen en el segundo tercio de la historia, y no queremos hacerlo. Arranca algo lento y es f\u00e1cil tener la sensaci\u00f3n de \"esto ya lo he jugado\", como si se tratase de una expansi\u00f3n con unos gr\u00e1ficos algo mejores, pero la \u00faltima obra de Valve guarda muchos momentos \u00e9picos en sus entra\u00f1as y Aperture Science es algo m\u00e1s que salas de test para conejillos de indias. Quiz\u00e1s la naturaleza del g\u00e9nero hace que el valor de rejugabilidad sea reducido, una vez conoces todas las soluciones terminar el juego m\u00e1s r\u00e1pidamente o desbloquear todos los logros y trofeos se convierte en el objetivo principal, juego cooperativo aparte. En definitiva, no alcanza la perfecci\u00f3n, pero Valve se acerca peligrosamente a ella.", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45737952", "grade": null, "id": 218700, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218700", "language": "es", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 96.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.6, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "es", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f789a9a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 20, "name": "Spain"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258061", "first_year": 2000, "id": 813, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/813/vandal-online/", "languages": [{"code": "es", "id": 133, "name": "Spanish", "ordering": 1330}], "last_year": null, "name": "Vandal Online", "num_reviews": 1500, "url": "http://www.vandal.net/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.vandal.net/analisis/x360/portal-2/12160"}, {"citation": "No se trata de un juego perfecto. Pero casi. Como obra de entretenimiento sobrepasa el valor de su adquisici\u00f3n. Eso es irrefutable. Despu\u00e9s llegar\u00e1n jugadores que no le encuentre la gracia o que tiren de la soluci\u00f3n grabada por terceros. Ellos se lo pierden. Portal 2 se basa en el mismo fundamento que hicieron grande a las aventuras gr\u00e1ficas de Lucas Arts y reventar esa magia s\u00f3lo consigue arruinar la experiencia. \u00bfQu\u00e9 dura poco? De media lo mismo que cualquier shooter de esos gen\u00e9ricos que salen cada poco tiempo. Despu\u00e9s queda el cooperativo, ese homenaje al gordo y al flaco que pone en liza hasta cuatro portales diferentes de manera simult\u00e1nea. El doble de dif\u00edcil, el doble de divertido. Claro que el ritmo de narraci\u00f3n se diluye, pero ah\u00ed queda GLaDOS para que en esta modalidad no echemos de menos su viperina lengua mec\u00e1nica. Paradojas, critiqueos y mucha venganza. Y es que en este universo de opereta rob\u00f3tica las traiciones y los asesinatos se recuerdan en c\u00f3digo binario.", "date": "2011-05-04", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667568", "grade": null, "id": 218694, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218694", "language": "es", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 96.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 96.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "es", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f789a9a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 20, "name": "Spain"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257812", "first_year": 2003, "id": 496, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/496/viciojuegoscom-uvejuegoscom/", "languages": [{"code": "es", "id": 133, "name": "Spanish", "ordering": 1330}], "last_year": null, "name": "VicioJuegos.com / uVeJuegos.com", "num_reviews": 738, "url": "http://www.viciojuegos.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.viciojuegos.com/analisis/Portal-2/Quod-erat-demonstrandum/5802/39678"}, {"citation": "Es dif\u00edcil explicar muchas de las virtudes de Portal 2 sin estropear sorpresas que aparecen en el segundo tercio de la historia, y no queremos hacerlo. Arranca algo lento y es f\u00e1cil tener la sensaci\u00f3n de \"esto ya lo he jugado\", como si se tratase de una expansi\u00f3n con unos gr\u00e1ficos algo mejores, pero la \u00faltima obra de Valve guarda muchos momentos \u00e9picos en sus entra\u00f1as y Aperture Science es algo m\u00e1s que salas de test para conejillos de indias. Quiz\u00e1s la naturaleza del g\u00e9nero hace que el valor de rejugabilidad sea reducido, una vez conoces todas las soluciones terminar el juego m\u00e1s r\u00e1pidamente o desbloquear todos los logros y trofeos se convierte en el objetivo principal, juego cooperativo aparte. En definitiva, no alcanza la perfecci\u00f3n, pero Valve se acerca peligrosamente a ella.", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45745375", "grade": null, "id": 218699, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218699", "language": "es", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 96.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.6, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "es", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f789a9a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 20, "name": "Spain"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258061", "first_year": 2000, "id": 813, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/813/vandal-online/", "languages": [{"code": "es", "id": 133, "name": "Spanish", "ordering": 1330}], "last_year": null, "name": "Vandal Online", "num_reviews": 1500, "url": "http://www.vandal.net/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.vandal.net/analisis/ps3/portal-2/12806"}, {"citation": "It\u0027s hard to sum up a game like Portal 2. It doesn\u2019t have enough shooting to be a shooter, but it\u0027s not abstract enough to be a puzzle game. It\u0027s unique and challenging enough to attract the hardcore, but its offbeat humor and intuitive design will make it a hit with casual players. I\u0027ll forget about categories and call it what it is: the most original game in years (a big accomplishment for a sequel). It\u0027s also Valve\u0027s biggest console success. The game looks great on PC, Mac, Xbox 360, and PS3, but the proverbial cake goes to the PS3 version, which comes with a free computer copy. On top of that, Portal 2 is that rare game with crossover multiplayer support, meaning PS3 players and computer gamers can portal it up together. That means if you have a laptop and a PS3, there\u2019s no reason to play in cramped split-screen mode. That is, unless the PSN is still down by the time this goes up.", "date": "2011-05-03", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667570", "grade": null, "id": 218688, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218688", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 96.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.6, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259420", "first_year": 1999, "id": 187, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/187/gaming-target/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gaming Target", "num_reviews": 1237, "url": "http://www.gamingtarget.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamingtarget.com/article.php?artid=12364\u0026gameid=7012"}, {"citation": "How Portal evolved from a simple student-born concept in 2007 into a character-rich, hilarious, intelligent, 15-plus-hour wonder in 2011 is a testament to this sequel\u2019s impeccable, deft design. A less consumer-minded developer might\u2019ve split Portal 2\u2019s contents into a trilogy \u2014 one game revolving around gels, a follow-up with funnels, and a third title with light bridges and a co-op mode \u2014 and they probably would\u2019ve gotten away with it, but Valve\u2019s kitchen-sink package proves they deserve the fan adoration they receive. Portal 2 isn\u2019t dessert \u2014 it\u2019s a delectable multi-course meal at a five-star restaurant. Make your reservation now.", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45741362", "grade": null, "id": 219015, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-219015", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258103", "first_year": 2001, "id": 45, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/45/official-xbox-magazine/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Official XBox Magazine", "num_reviews": 243, "url": "http://www.oxmonline.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.oxmonline.com/article/reviews/xbox-360/m-r/portal-2"}, {"citation": "Portal 2\u2019s high points rival \u201cthe cake is a lie,\u201d though they\u2019re perhaps less quotable (which is honestly fine \u2013 repeating GLaDOS lines stopped being funny a long time ago). You\u2019ll never forget the moments that accompany some of the achievements/trophies. The game\u2019s quality stays consistently outstanding throughout; there isn\u2019t a minute of filler content to be found anywhere in single-player or co-op. I would have loved to see something unique done with the story, which doesn\u2019t end anywhere interesting despite a reasonably satisfying ending. I would adore seeing Portal stretch its wings beyond being a series of puzzles that almost always have one correct solution waiting to be found. That said, the next game I want to play is a second run through of Portal 2, because the existing formula is excellent and brilliantly executed.", "date": "2011-04-18", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45739757", "grade": null, "id": 218853, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218853", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258109", "first_year": 1991, "id": 47, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/47/game-informer-magazine/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Game Informer Magazine", "num_reviews": 5963, "url": "http://www.gameinformer.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gameinformer.com/games/portal_2/b/xbox360/archive/2011/04/18/the-sequel-you-were-hoping-for.aspx"}, {"citation": "Algunos conceptos como la repetici\u00f3n de determinados puzles y exigencias o pocas opciones en cooperativo no le dejan convertirse en la obra maestra que los m\u00e1s seguidores de Valve no tardar\u00e1n en ver en \u00e9l. Pese a esto, es un juego estilizado y absoluto como pocos, un ejemplo m\u00e1s de que la diversi\u00f3n que propone esta industria a veces llega a cotas inimaginables, aternativas a la marea de juegos habitual y aptas para todos los p\u00fablicos. Uno de los nombres del a\u00f1o que ha conseguido hacer de la marca Portal un fetiche rotundo en la industria y una demostraci\u00f3n de c\u00f3mo enfrentarse a un proyecto que desde siempre ha usado su propuesta diferente como el arma principal capaz de dotarle del \u00e9xito que ha acabado consiguiendo y que no es m\u00e1s que un regalo para sus seguidores y todos los jugadores en general.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45508174", "grade": null, "id": 218869, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218869", "language": "es", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "es", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f789a9a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 20, "name": "Spain"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252540", "first_year": 1997, "id": 295, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/295/meristation/", "languages": [{"code": "es", "id": 133, "name": "Spanish", "ordering": 1330}], "last_year": null, "name": "Meristation", "num_reviews": 1525, "url": "https://as.com/meristation/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.meristation.com/v3/des_analisis.php?pic=PC\u0026idj=cw4b9152291871a\u0026id=cw4daeac2f17e67"}, {"citation": "I thought Valve would have a tough time making this something other than Portal with a bunch of different levels, but I was very wrong. Without having the player fire a single bullet, it has produced one of the best FPS\u2019s to date.", "date": "2011-04-26", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45508175", "grade": null, "id": 218870, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218870", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "uk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f7e9f08-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 22, "name": "United Kingdom"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259520", "first_year": 2006, "id": 917, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/917/middle-east-gamers-megamers/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Middle East Gamers (MEgamers)", "num_reviews": 133, "url": "http://tbreak.com/megamers"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://tbreak.com/megamers/25904/reviews/portal-2-review/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 pr\u00e4sentiert ein Spielprinzip, dass so in der Computerspielewelt einzigartig ist. Das Spiel wurde mit so viel Liebe zum Detail, so viel herzerw\u00e4rmendem Humor und so viel Kreativit\u00e4t zum bersten gef\u00fcllt, dass wir vor Freude und Ehrfurcht auf die Knie fallen wollen. Jedem Abschnitt merkt man an, wie sorgsam die R\u00e4tsel entworfen wurden, wie genau es Valve mit perfektem, fehlerfreiem Spiel nimmt. Portal 2 \u00fcbertrifft seinen Vorg\u00e4nger um L\u00e4ngen, ohne dabei die eigenen Tugenden au\u00dfer Acht zu lassen. Alles, was ihr am ersten Teil geliebt habt, bekommt ihr jetzt wieder, in gr\u00f6\u00dfer, besser und lustiger. Wir k\u00f6nnen jedem Spieler, der den ersten Teil ins Herz geschlossen hat (und all jenen, die endlich mal wieder etwas neues, anderes ausprobieren m\u00f6chten!) dieses Meisterwerk an Erz\u00e4hlkunst und Humor nur ans Herz legen. Ein sch\u00f6neres, kreativeres und lustigeres Spielejuwel werdet ihr 2011 nicht in die Finger bekommen.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45514387", "grade": null, "id": 218878, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218878", "language": "de", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 95.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "de", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f8eb00a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 9, "name": "Germany"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257669", "first_year": 1992, "id": 40, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/40/pc-games-germany/", "languages": [{"code": "de", "id": 47, "name": "German", "ordering": 470}], "last_year": null, "name": "PC Games (Germany)", "num_reviews": 6509, "url": "http://www.pcgames.de/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.pcgames.de/Portal-2-PC-213930/Tests/Portal-2-Ein-grossartiges-Spiele-Meisterwerk-Von-Anfang-bis-Ende-ein-tolles-Erlebnis-820632/"}, {"citation": "\u0415\u0441\u043b\u0438 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u044b\u0439 Portal \u0431\u044b\u043b \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0431\u043d\u044b\u043c \u0448\u0430\u0440\u043e\u043c, \u0432\u044b\u0431\u0438\u0432\u0448\u0438\u043c \u0441\u0