": "ru", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "ru", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/b1f886a8-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 19, "name": "Russia"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259439", "first_year": 2006, "id": 1520, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1520/gamesmailru/", "languages": [{"code": "ru", "id": 119, "name": "Russian", "ordering": 1190}], "last_year": null, "name": "games.mail.ru", "num_reviews": 35, "url": "http://games.mail.ru/pc/"}, "submitter": {"id": 108912, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/108912/latvian_nomad/", "name": "Evgenii Andzhe"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://games.mail.ru/pc/articles/review/901"}, {"citation": "Some say it took them only 4 hours to complete the single-player portion of Portal 2, while others say it lasted upwards of 8-10 and refuse to believe it could\u2019ve been done any faster than 6. I finished in about 5 hours, and while I didn\u2019t spend excess time poking around for easter eggs, I wasn\u2019t rushing at all and enjoyed it immensely. The co-op levels were great fun, as well, offering 3 hours of diversion for myself and a capable partner. Just don\u2019t expect much of a story from the co-op, or any real reason to play through that again until you forget how to solve the puzzles. Not only is Portal 2 well worth the price of admission, it\u2019s the best game released so far this year and a serious contender for GOTY 2011. Just steer clear of the in-game storefront that wants to charge you $5 for a hat or $7.50 for glasses to wear on your co-op robot.", "date": "2011-04-27", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45556714", "grade": null, "id": 211099, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-211099", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 95.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257711", "first_year": 1998, "id": 11, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/11/firingsquad/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "FiringSquad", "num_reviews": 231, "url": "http://www.firingsquad.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 55856, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/55856/scaryfun/", "name": "Scaryfun"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://firingsquad.com/games/Portal_2_PC_Review/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2\u2019s high points rival \u201cthe cake is a lie,\u201d though they\u2019re perhaps less quotable (which is honestly fine \u2013 repeating GLaDOS lines stopped being funny a long time ago). You\u2019ll never forget the moments that accompany some of the achievements/trophies. The game\u2019s quality stays consistently outstanding throughout; there isn\u2019t a minute of filler content to be found anywhere in single-player or co-op. I would have loved to see something unique done with the story, which doesn\u2019t end anywhere interesting despite a reasonably satisfying ending. I would adore seeing Portal stretch its wings beyond being a series of puzzles that almost always have one correct solution waiting to be found. That said, the next game I want to play is a second run through of Portal 2, because the existing formula is excellent and brilliantly executed.", "date": "2011-04-18", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45556735", "grade": null, "id": 211100, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-211100", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258109", "first_year": 1991, "id": 47, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/47/game-informer-magazine/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Game Informer Magazine", "num_reviews": 5963, "url": "http://www.gameinformer.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 55856, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/55856/scaryfun/", "name": "Scaryfun"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gameinformer.com/games/portal_2/b/pc/archive/2011/04/18/the-sequel-you-were-hoping-for.aspx"}, {"citation": "The original Portal benefitted from its brevity. It had a concise story paired with inventive first-person puzzle mechanics that challenged you to be creative while pulling the trigger. Portal 2 makes the original look like the prototype it was. It\u0027s filled with a larger cast of characters vividly brought to life through brilliant writing and some of the best voice acting in video games. Its puzzles are challenging without being unreasonable, and, once you\u0027re finished with the single-player mode, one of the best co-operative experiences on the market awaits. Valve cuts no corners and finds ways to make you care about everything from the major characters to the cubes used to solve puzzles. From the beginning of the single-player story to the end of the co-op mode, Portal 2 is a novel, unforgettable experience.", "date": "2011-04-18", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45616413", "grade": null, "id": 210088, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-210088", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252812", "first_year": 1996, "id": 2, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/2/ign/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "IGN", "num_reviews": 13592, "url": "https://www.ign.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 42009, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/42009/jaxen/", "name": "jaXen"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://uk.ps3.ign.com/articles/116/1162428p1.html"}, {"citation": "Dans ses m\u00e9caniques autant que dans son \u00e9criture, Portal 2 est tout simplement brillant, intelligent et terriblement dr\u00f4le. Un constat qui vaut aussi bien pour son mode solo que pour son mode coop qui convertira m\u00eame les allergiques au multijoueur. Un titre r\u00e9solument incontournable dot\u00e9 d\u0027un gameplay sans cesse renouvel\u00e9 et de r\u00e9pliques qui ne tarderont pas \u00e0 devenir cultes.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45616411", "grade": null, "id": 210090, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-210090", "language": "fr", "max_score": 20.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 19.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "fr", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f4ebb9e-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 8, "name": "France"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257699", "first_year": 1997, "id": 142, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/142/jeuxvideocom/", "languages": [{"code": "fr", "id": 42, "name": "French", "ordering": 420}], "last_year": null, "name": "Jeuxvideo.com", "num_reviews": 14578, "url": "http://www.jeuxvideo.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 42009, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/42009/jaxen/", "name": "jaXen"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.jeuxvideo.com/articles/0001/00014721-portal-2-test.htm"}, {"citation": "The original Portal benefitted from its brevity. It had a concise story paired with inventive first-person puzzle mechanics that challenged you to be creative while pulling the trigger. Portal 2 makes the original look like the prototype it was. It\u0027s filled with a larger cast of characters vividly brought to life through brilliant writing and some of the best voice acting in video games. Its puzzles are challenging without being unreasonable, and, once you\u0027re finished with the single-player mode, one of the best co-operative experiences on the market awaits. Valve cuts no corners and finds ways to make you care about everything from the major characters to the cubes used to solve puzzles. From the beginning of the single-player story to the end of the co-op mode, Portal 2 is a novel, unforgettable experience.", "date": "2011-04-18", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45616412", "grade": null, "id": 210092, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-210092", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252812", "first_year": 1996, "id": 2, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/2/ign/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "IGN", "num_reviews": 13592, "url": "https://www.ign.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://pc.ign.com/articles/116/1162215p1.html"}, {"citation": "The very short duration and lack of multiplayer were the most important shortcomings signaled by the community regarding its predecessor, so Portal 2 came to directly solve these problems, while at the same time further evolving the gameplay that was so beloved by millions of fans. If Portal was an experiment, a child who didn\u2019t know if he\u2019ll reach adulthood, Portal 2 can be seen as the teen years of the series. And if the evolution will continue in the same manner, I can\u2019t wait to see what it will look like when he\u2019ll be all grown up.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45616420", "grade": null, "id": 210094, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-210094", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 95.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "ro", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/b2514bd0-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 48, "name": "Romania"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254916", "first_year": 1984, "id": 58, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/58/computergamesro/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}, {"code": "ro", "id": 117, "name": "Romanian", "ordering": 1170}], "last_year": null, "name": "ComputerGames.ro", "num_reviews": 298, "url": "http://www.computergames.ro/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://computergames.ro/en/games/viewitem/id/2188/article/1219/name/portal-2/section/review.html"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 d\u00fcrfte eines der besten Spiele dieses Jahres sein, wie unser Test verr\u00e4t. Das Spiel hat uns \u00fcberragend gefallen, Kritikpunkte musste man mit der Lupe suchen.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45745389", "grade": null, "id": 218843, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218843", "language": "de", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "de", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f8eb00a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 9, "name": "Germany"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258053", "first_year": 2006, "id": 600, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/600/games-aktuell/", "languages": [{"code": "de", "id": 47, "name": "German", "ordering": 470}], "last_year": null, "name": "Games Aktuell", "num_reviews": 47, "url": "http://www.gamesaktuell.de/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamesaktuell.de/Portal-2-PC-213930/Tests/Portal-2-im-Test-fuer-PC-PS3-und-Xbox-360-Das-beste-Valve-Spiel-aller-Zeiten-820597/"}, {"citation": "Overall, Portal 2 manages to act as a worthy successor to the original Portal, retaining its core mechanics while adding quite a lot of new things and other great additions that enrich the puzzle solving experience. Portal 2 has a top notch story, an extremely smooth gameplay, from the single-player campaign to the co-op multiplayer, and will no doubt be regarded as a serious contender for the game of the year award at the end of 2011.", "date": "2011-04-22", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45625275", "grade": null, "id": 214273, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-214273", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "ro", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/b2514bd0-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 48, "name": "Romania"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257882", "first_year": 2005, "id": 640, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/640/softpedia/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Softpedia", "num_reviews": 875, "url": "http://www.softpedia.com/reviews/games/"}, "submitter": {"id": 183114, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/183114/alsy/", "name": "Alsy"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.softpedia.com/reviews/games/pc/Portal-2-Review-196590.shtml"}, {"citation": "Uiteraard is ook de audio weer van hoog niveau. De voice-acting is ijzersterk en past perfect bij de aanwezige personages. Dan is er ook nog een soundtrack die lekker futuristisch klinkt en regelmatig de kop op steekt om het sfeervolle geheel te voorzien van nog meer sfeer. Kortom, het is eigenlijk een hele simpele conclusie. Op alle aspecten scoort de game goed en we hebben eigenlijk geen minpunten kunnen constateren inhoudelijk. Het enige wat een beetje stoort zijn de vele laadschermen die je keer op keer moet doorstaan. Ze zijn weliswaar niet al te lang, maar toch is het wat jammer. Desondanks, Portal 2, een briljante game. E\u00e9n van de beste games van 2011, nu al!", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45745386", "grade": null, "id": 218821, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218821", "language": "nl", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 95.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "nl", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/c4f2d308-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 16, "name": "The Netherlands"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257667", "first_year": 2009, "id": 1258, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1258/psfocus/", "languages": [{"code": "nl", "id": 34, "name": "Dutch", "ordering": 340}], "last_year": null, "name": "PSFocus", "num_reviews": 59, "url": "http://www.psfocus.nl/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://psfocus.nl/4_22435_Portal_2.aspx"}, {"citation": "Overall, Portal 2 is (yet another) milestone pinnacle in design. It\u2019s a near-perfect example of how an old dog can learn new tricks. I only hope that Valve can continue this level of professionalism with Half-Life 3 because a sequel to Portal 2 is implausible and unnecessary. Which is exactly what I said at the end of Portal 1.", "date": "2011-05-03", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45640426", "grade": null, "id": 220262, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-220262", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259555", "first_year": 2004, "id": 1568, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1568/omgn-online-multiplayer-games-network/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "OMGN: Online Multiplayer Games Network", "num_reviews": 195, "url": "http://www.omgn.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.omgn.com/review/2011/05/03/portal-2-review"}, {"citation": "As much as people want to joke on how long Valve takes to make a game, you have to hand it to them; they do rise to the occasion and make the game worth the wait. Portal 2 is everything that fans wanted, more of everything while keeping the feel of the original game. That\u2019s an incredible feat by a very talented bunch of developers.", "date": "2011-05-05", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45745376", "grade": null, "id": 218706, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218706", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254956", "first_year": 2008, "id": 1099, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1099/original-gamer/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Original Gamer", "num_reviews": 69, "url": "http://www.original-gamer.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.original-gamer.com/?action=article\u0026id=2383"}, {"citation": "Sentido del humor, rompecabezas tremendamente ingeniosos y h\u00e1bil mezcla de destreza cerebral con habilidad... \u00bfImposible de combinar? En absoluto. Valve demuestra una vez m\u00e1s su incre\u00edble maestr\u00eda con uno de los mejores videojuegos en lo que va de a\u00f1o. Portal 2 es, al mismo tiempo, imaginativo, estimulante, adictivo y cargado de momentos hilarantes, y como tal puede ser recomendado a cualquier tipo de p\u00fablico (sin importar edad ni condici\u00f3n) con la seguridad del acierto.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45745371", "grade": null, "id": 218696, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218696", "language": "es", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "es", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f789a9a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 20, "name": "Spain"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257761", "first_year": 2004, "id": 444, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/444/3d-juegos/", "languages": [{"code": "es", "id": 133, "name": "Spanish", "ordering": 1330}], "last_year": null, "name": "3D Juegos", "num_reviews": 1031, "url": "http://www.3djuegos.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.3djuegos.com/juegos/analisis/9016/0/portal-2/"}, {"citation": "We can\u2019t ignore that Portal 2 does have a few tiny issues, because it does and they are there. At the same time, we can\u2019t focus on them too much. Portal 2 is a truly fantastic game, a worthy sequel in almost every way and a joy to play. It may not pack the surprise-factor of the original game \u2013 a fact which deprives GlaDOS especially of much of her early power \u2013 but it\u2019s still just as fun, fast, funny and fantastic as we\u2019d expect a second Portal game to be. It\u2019s a game you should own and one you won\u2019t regret picking up.", "date": "2011-04-20", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667584", "grade": null, "id": 218708, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218708", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 95.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "uk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f7e9f08-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 22, "name": "United Kingdom"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259550", "first_year": 2005, "id": 338, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/338/bit-tech/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Bit-Tech", "num_reviews": 152, "url": "http://www.bit-tech.net/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.bit-tech.net/gaming/pc/2011/04/20/portal-2-review/"}, {"citation": "Overall, Portal 2 is (yet another) milestone pinnacle in design. It\u2019s a near-perfect example of how an old dog can learn new tricks. I only hope that Valve can continue this level of professionalism with Half-Life 3 because a sequel to Portal 2 is implausible and unnecessary. Which is exactly what I said at the end of Portal 1.", "date": "2011-05-03", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45680178", "grade": null, "id": 220260, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-220260", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259555", "first_year": 2004, "id": 1568, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1568/omgn-online-multiplayer-games-network/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "OMGN: Online Multiplayer Games Network", "num_reviews": 195, "url": "http://www.omgn.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.omgn.com/review/2011/05/03/portal-2-review"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is an absolutely amazing title. Everyone was disappointed when Portal 2 was delayed earlier this year, but it was more than worth the wait. Portal 2 is a masterpiece that I can see myself playing for years. The only downside for console gamers is that Valve seems to have put more into the PC version. The PC version allows you to customize your co-op bots by buying them different gear, gestures and things of that nature. It should be noted that the gestures PC players purchase will not be seen by Playstation 3 gamers if a PS3 gamer is playing co op with a PC gamer. Additionally, there is an interactive \"trailer\" for an upcoming game. It would have been nice to see these features on the console versions as well. Portal 2 is one of those titles that needs to be in every gamer\u0027s library. You owe it to yourself to experience this masterpiece and revel in the joy that is brought about by playing it. I can\u0027t wait to see what Valve comes up with next within the Portal universe.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45669301", "grade": null, "id": 218978, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218978", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "ww", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/d74880f2-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.png", "id": 56, "name": "Worldwide"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257788", "first_year": 2005, "id": 777, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/777/totally-gaming-network/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Totally Gaming Network", "num_reviews": 245, "url": "http://www.totallygn.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.totallygn.com/2011/04/19/portal-2-review/"}, {"citation": "It\u0027s an excellent game. It is clearly a product of people who wanted to do more with the elements from the first title, and succeeded in every way. The world of Portal has expanded, the characters are given more depth, and the story pulls you back and forth in many unexpected ways with a climactic finale that might leave you breathless. Fantastic writing, excellent gameplay, and a level of polish and playtesting so high that you know it\u0027s got to be a Valve title, Portal 2 is simply a game that can not be missed.", "date": "2011-05-04", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45669171", "grade": null, "id": 218881, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218881", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "ca", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9fa117cc-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 5, "name": "Canada"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258088", "first_year": 2000, "id": 222, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/222/gamingexcellence/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "GamingExcellence", "num_reviews": 719, "url": "http://www.gamingexcellence.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamingexcellence.com/ps3/games/2330/review.shtml"}, {"citation": "Algunos conceptos como la repetici\u00f3n de determinados puzles y exigencias o pocas opciones en cooperativo no le dejan convertirse en la obra maestra que los m\u00e1s seguidores de Valve no tardar\u00e1n en ver en \u00e9l. Pese a esto, es un juego estilizado y absoluto como pocos, un ejemplo m\u00e1s de que la diversi\u00f3n que propone esta industria a veces llega a cotas inimaginables, aternativas a la marea de juegos habitual y aptas para todos los p\u00fablicos. Uno de los nombres del a\u00f1o que ha conseguido hacer de la marca Portal un fetiche rotundo en la industria y una demostraci\u00f3n de c\u00f3mo enfrentarse a un proyecto que desde siempre ha usado su propuesta diferente como el arma principal capaz de dotarle del \u00e9xito que ha acabado consiguiendo y que no es m\u00e1s que un regalo para sus seguidores y todos los jugadores en general.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45669147", "grade": null, "id": 218867, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218867", "language": "es", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "es", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f789a9a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 20, "name": "Spain"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252540", "first_year": 1997, "id": 2