eople who wanted to do more with the elements from the first title, and succeeded in every way. The world of Portal has expanded, the characters are given more depth, and the story pulls you back and forth in many unexpected ways with a climactic finale that might leave you breathless. Fantastic writing, excellent gameplay, and a level of polish and playtesting so high that you know it\u0027s got to be a Valve title, Portal 2 is simply a game that can not be missed.", "date": "2011-05-04", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45669150", "grade": null, "id": 218879, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218879", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "ca", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9fa117cc-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 5, "name": "Canada"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258088", "first_year": 2000, "id": 222, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/222/gamingexcellence/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "GamingExcellence", "num_reviews": 719, "url": "http://www.gamingexcellence.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamingexcellence.com/pc/games/2330/review.shtml"}, {"citation": "To reiterate, Portal 2 is fantastic.  Its single-player provides ample amounts of genuinely funny and compelling narrative and some great puzzles, while the co-op takes the game\u0027s mechanics and pushes them to their absolute, playable limit.  You\u0027re only getting around 10-12 hours after delving into both halves of the game, but it\u0027s a concentrated thrill, where its weakest moments are still standards that most developers can barely reach in the first place.", "date": "2011-05-08", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45669284", "grade": null, "id": 218967, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218967", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252524", "first_year": 2002, "id": 1462, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1462/cpu-gamer/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "CPU Gamer", "num_reviews": 47, "url": "http://www.cpugamer.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.cpugamer.com/reviews/portal-2-review"}, {"citation": "W roku 2011 Portal jest mark\u0105 z prawdziwego zdarzenia, opieraj\u0105c\u0105 si\u0119 na solidnym fundamencie i por\u00f3wnywan\u0105 z innymi du\u017cymi tytu\u0142ami firmy Valve. Jest on gwarantem znakomitej zabawy, jak r\u00f3wnie\u017c powiewem \u015bwie\u017co\u015bci w skostnia\u0142ej bran\u017cy elektronicznej rozrywki, kt\u00f3r\u0105 od zjedzenia w\u0142asnego ogona powstrzymuj\u0105 ci\u0105gle tw\u00f3rcy gier niezale\u017cnych. Druga ods\u0142ona cyklu doskonale wpisuje si\u0119 w ten nurt, cho\u0107 niezale\u017cn\u0105 nazwa\u0107 j\u0105 w \u017cadnym wypadku nie mo\u017cna. To tytu\u0142 zrobiony za du\u017ce pieni\u0105dze, ale jednocze\u015bnie na tyle interesuj\u0105cy i oryginalny, \u017ce mo\u017cemy m\u00f3wi\u0107 o zupe\u0142nie nowej jako\u015bci. Naprawd\u0119.", "date": "2011-04-22", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45669287", "grade": null, "id": 218968, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218968", "language": "pl", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "pl", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f71242c-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 17, "name": "Poland"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259570", "first_year": 1999, "id": 648, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/648/gry-online/", "languages": [{"code": "pl", "id": 112, "name": "Polish", "ordering": 1120}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gry OnLine", "num_reviews": 587, "url": "http://www.gry-online.pl/s015.asp"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gry-online.pl/S020.asp?ID=7397"}, {"citation": "If you can get the PC version, do so, as the combination of pricing and mouse control make the title just that little bit better. Portal 2 manages to exceed expectations without compromising any of the core gameplay that made the original so popular, and should easily be considered one of the best titles available so far this year.", "date": "2011-04-26", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45669288", "grade": null, "id": 218969, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218969", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "nz", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/b258face-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 29, "name": "New Zealand"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257757", "first_year": 2000, "id": 239, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/239/gameplanet/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gameplanet", "num_reviews": 723, "url": "http://www.gameplanet.co.nz/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gameplanet.co.nz/pc/games/165748.Portal-2/reviews/136922/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2\u2019s high points rival \u201cthe cake is a lie,\u201d though they\u2019re perhaps less quotable (which is honestly fine \u2013 repeating GLaDOS lines stopped being funny a long time ago). You\u2019ll never forget the moments that accompany some of the achievements/trophies. The game\u2019s quality stays consistently outstanding throughout; there isn\u2019t a minute of filler content to be found anywhere in single-player or co-op. I would have loved to see something unique done with the story, which doesn\u2019t end anywhere interesting despite a reasonably satisfying ending. I would adore seeing Portal stretch its wings beyond being a series of puzzles that almost always have one correct solution waiting to be found. That said, the next game I want to play is a second run through of Portal 2, because the existing formula is excellent and brilliantly executed.", "date": "2011-04-18", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667796", "grade": null, "id": 218854, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218854", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258109", "first_year": 1991, "id": 47, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/47/game-informer-magazine/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Game Informer Magazine", "num_reviews": 5963, "url": "http://www.gameinformer.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gameinformer.com/games/portal_2/b/ps3/archive/2011/04/18/the-sequel-you-were-hoping-for.aspx"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 non \u00e8 un gioco per tutti i palati. Ma non \u00e8 sempre dall\u0027universalit\u00e0 che si riconosce l\u0027eccellenza. Anzi, la forza dell\u0027ultimo nato in casa Valve dipende proprio da questo suo totale rigetto dei canoni, dal coraggio insuperabile di mantenere il contatto con una community fatta di nerd e cervelloni. L\u0027opera prima di una delle migliori software sulla piazza \u00e8 indubbiamente ricchissima, originale, audace, raffinata. Abbracciando valori produttivi che sembravano scomparsi, ci sazia e ci appaga con una longevit\u00e0 esuberante, un comparto artistico che unisce ricercatezza e minimalismo, e dinamiche profonde, varie, stratificate. Nella sua compiuta perfezione, Portal 2 ci ricorda -stanza dopo stanza- qual\u0027\u00e8 il brivido per cui noi tutti continuiamo a giocare.", "date": "2011-04-20", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667751", "grade": null, "id": 218833, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218833", "language": "it", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "it", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f5b5804-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 12, "name": "Italy"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259386", "first_year": 2006, "id": 423, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/423/everyeyeit/", "languages": [{"code": "it", "id": 64, "name": "Italian", "ordering": 640}], "last_year": null, "name": "Everyeye.it", "num_reviews": 1063, "url": "http://www.everyeye.it/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.everyeye.it/ps3/articoli/portal-2_recensione_13695"}, {"citation": "The first game introduced such great technology with the portal gun and laid down a solid framework from which to gain further inspiration; the sequel simply had to be even better. The good news is that Portal 2 doesn\u2019t disappoint; in fact it\u0027s exceeded our expectations. From the captivating storyline and the casting of the brilliant Stephen Merchant as Wheatley, to the sheer volume of puzzles and the ingenuity that has gone into their design, Portal 2 is everything it promised to be and much more.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667647", "grade": null, "id": 218765, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218765", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258043", "first_year": 2005, "id": 947, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/947/playstation-universe/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "PlayStation Universe", "num_reviews": 1886, "url": "http://www.psu.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.psu.com/Portal-2-Review--a011371-p0.php"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 \u2014 \u0438\u0433\u0440\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u043e\u0434\u0438\u043d \u0440\u0430\u0437. \u0417\u0430\u0442\u043e \u043a\u0430\u043a\u043e\u0439! \u041e\u0442\u0442\u043e\u0447\u0438\u0432 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u044c\u044f \u0438 \u043b\u043e\u0433\u0438\u043a\u0443 \u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u0447\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438, Valve \u0432\u044b\u043f\u0443\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043b\u0430 \u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0446\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0439 \u0441\u0438\u043a\u0432\u0435\u043b, \u043a \u043a\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043c\u0443 \u043f\u043e\u0447\u0442\u0438 \u043d\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0434\u0440\u0430\u0442\u044c\u0441\u044f. \u041b\u043e\u043a\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u0448\u0442\u0430\u0431\u043d\u0435\u0435 \u0438 \u0440\u0430\u0437\u043d\u043e\u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0435, \u0433\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u2014 \u0442\u0435\u0445\u043d\u0438\u0447\u043d\u0435\u0435, \u043f\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u2014 \u0433\u043b\u0443\u0431\u0436\u0435. \u041e\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u043e\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0432 \u2014 \u043f\u043e-\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0436\u043d\u0435\u043c\u0443 \u043f\u0443\u0448\u043a\u0430, \u0441\u043e\u0437\u0434\u0430\u044e\u0449\u0430\u044f \u0434\u0432\u0430 \u0432\u0437\u0430\u0438\u043c\u043e\u0441\u0432\u044f\u0437\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0430, \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0434\u0430, \u043c\u0435\u0445\u0430\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0430 \u0433\u043e\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0434\u043e \u0441\u043b\u043e\u0436\u043d\u0435\u0435. \u0420\u0430\u043d\u044c\u0448\u0435 \u043c\u044b \u043f\u0440\u043e\u044