7\u043a\u0438, \u043d\u043e \u0431\u0435\u0437 \u0443\u043a\u043b\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0432 \u0441\u0430\u0434\u0438\u0437\u043c.", "date": "2011-04-25", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45573578", "grade": null, "id": 211050, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-211050", "language": "ru", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 95.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "ru", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/b1f886a8-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 19, "name": "Russia"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259429", "first_year": 1998, "id": 105, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/105/absolute-games-agru/", "languages": [{"code": "ru", "id": 119, "name": "Russian", "ordering": 1190}], "last_year": 2015, "name": "Absolute Games (AG.ru)", "num_reviews": 1923, "url": "http://www.ag.ru/"}, "submitter": {"id": 171231, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/171231/gtramp/", "name": "GTramp"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.ag.ru/reviews/portal_2"}, {"citation": "Mora se dodu\u0161e re\u0107i da replay value ovdje nije pretjerano visok. Prvi prolazak igre je klju\u010dan, a kasnije nismo sigurno ho\u0107ete li sve to po\u017eeljeti ponovno iskusiti kada ve\u0107 znate \u0161to \u0107e se desiti u pri\u010di i kako se odre\u0111ene zagonetke rije\u0161avaju. Gledajte na Portal 2 stoga kao iskustvo od sveukupno 12 do 15 sati. Jedno koje \u0107ete pamtiti kao vrlo zabavno i vrijedno novca koji morate ulo\u017eiti da bi ga iskusili.", "date": "2011-11-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=4297593861", "grade": null, "id": 580281, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-580281", "language": "hr", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 95.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "hr", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/e956ef22-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 6, "name": "Croatia"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=160091345", "first_year": 2006, "id": 1876, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1876/hclhr-gaming-portal/", "languages": [{"code": "hr", "id": 31, "name": "Croatian", "ordering": 310}], "last_year": null, "name": "HCL.hr Gaming Portal", "num_reviews": 435, "url": "https://www.hcl.hr/"}, "submitter": {"id": 180419, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/180419/plok/", "name": "Plok"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "https://www.hcl.hr/recenzija/portal-2-pc-mac-x360-ps3-62307/"}, {"citation": "If you\u0027ve been waiting a long time in eager anticipation for Portal 2 then it\u0027s hard to see how you\u0027d be disappointed. The single-player campaign doubles the length of the original, and is crammed with even more hilarity and devious puzzles than ever before, as well as extending the concept with the introduction of larger environments and new mechanics like the gels. The co-op is amazingly fun, and while the story is less complex, the gameplay is even more concentrated insanity than the single player. If you have an affinity for the series, Valve, puzzle games, funny games, or just awesome games in general, you must not miss out on Portal 2. GLaDOS won\u0027t let you.", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667586", "grade": null, "id": 218710, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218710", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "au", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/b24379d8-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 3, "name": "Australia"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252871", "first_year": 2003, "id": 70, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/70/pal-gaming-network-palgn/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "PAL Gaming Network (PALGN)", "num_reviews": 798, "url": "http://palgn.com.au/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://palgn.com.au/playstation-3/18725/portal-2-review/"}, {"citation": "Wenn der Kuchen redet, haben die Kr\u00fcmel Pause - doch was ist, wenn der Kuchen eine L\u00fcge ist? In Portal 2, der Fortsetzung des \u00dcberraschungshits aus der Orange Box von Valve, zeigt sich GLaDOS wieder von ihrer perfidesten Seite. Ein t\u00f6dliches R\u00e4tsel-Labyrinth voller fieser Fallen und physikalischen Kettenreaktionen wartet nur darauf, euer Gehirn zu martern.", "date": "2014-06-07", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=4299186912", "grade": null, "id": 657392, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-657392", "language": "de", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "de", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f8eb00a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 9, "name": "Germany"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257821", "first_year": 2012, "id": 1402, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1402/ign-deutschland/", "languages": [{"code": "de", "id": 47, "name": "German", "ordering": 470}], "last_year": null, "name": "IGN Deutschland", "num_reviews": 135, "url": "http://de.ign.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 1121630, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/1121630/rocket55/", "name": "Rocket"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "https://de.ign.com/portal-2/74721/review/portal-2-test?p=2"}, {"citation": "Jede Minute, die Sie mit Portal 2 verbringen, garantiert Knobelunterhaltung der Extraklasse. Dazu kommt der exzellente Koop-Modus, der qualitativ mit dem Hauptspiel locker mith\u00e4lt. Kritikpunkte gibt es dagegen wenige. Portal 2 ist ein Juwel, das in keiner Spielesammlung fehlen darf.", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=4299187278", "grade": null, "id": 657399, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-657399", "language": "de", "max_score": 6.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 1.25, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "de", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f8eb00a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 9, "name": "Germany"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252840", "first_year": 1992, "id": 601, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/601/pc-games-hardware/", "languages": [{"code": "de", "id": 47, "name": "German", "ordering": 470}], "last_year": null, "name": "PC Games Hardware", "num_reviews": 5, "url": "http://www.pcgameshardware.de/"}, "submitter": {"id": 1121630, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/1121630/rocket55/", "name": "Rocket"}, "type": {"id": 5, "name": "Numeric (Lowest score is best)"}, "url": "https://www.pcgameshardware.de/Portal-2-Spiel-28233/Tests/Portal-2-im-Test-Knobelunterhaltung-der-Extraklasse-821445/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is one of the best games I\u2019ve played so far this year. Unique gameplay, witty dialogue, a simple yet satisfying story, and a well polished game. There\u2019s so much that this puzzle game got right. The flow of the game is perfect and the difficulty of each puzzle is just right. Most games out now are somewhat similar or familiar in certain ways and you hardly find a game that provides something new for us gamers to experience. Portal 2 is a perfect example of how game developers can still wow us with something completely out of our comfort zones. I recommend even non-gamers to experience this game if they can. This is one title you should not ignore.", "date": "2011-05-30", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=4299187535", "grade": null, "id": 657410, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-657410", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 95.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "ph", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/e96557c4-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 43, "name": "The Philippines"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=4296017508", "first_year": 2010, "id": 3551, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/3551/too-much-gaming/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Too Much Gaming", "num_reviews": 26, "url": "https://www.toomuchgaming.net/"}, "submitter": {"id": 1121630, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/1121630/rocket55/", "name": "Rocket"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "https://www.toomuchgaming.net/archive/tag/Portal+2+Review"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 isn\u2019t just one of the best games of the year \u2013 it\u2019s two of them.", "date": "2011-04-18", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45737991", "grade": null, "id": 230358, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-230358", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258109", "first_year": 1991, "id": 47, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/47/game-informer-magazine/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Game Informer Magazine", "num_reviews": 5963, "url": "http://www.gameinformer.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 103984, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/103984/cantillon/", "name": "Cantillon"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gameinformer.com/games/portal_2/b/xbox360/archive/2011/04/18/the-sequel-you-were-hoping-for.aspx"}, {"citation": "The original Portal benefitted from its brevity. It had a concise story paired with inventive first-person puzzle mechanics that challenged you to be creative while pulling the trigger. Portal 2 makes the original look like the prototype it was. It\u0027s filled with a larger cast of characters vividly brought to life through brilliant writing and some of the best voice acting in video games. Its puzzles are challenging without being unreasonable, and, once you\u0027re finished with the single-player mode, one of the best co-operative experiences on the market awaits. Valve cuts no corners and finds ways to make you care about everything from the major characters to the cubes used to solve puzzles. From the beginning of the single-player story to the end of the co-op mode, Portal 2 is a novel, unforgettable experience.", "date": "2011-04-18", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45484292", "grade": null, "id": 210093, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-210093", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252812", "first_year": 1996, "id": 2, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/2/ign/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "IGN", "num_reviews": 13592, "url": "https://www.ign.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://xbox360.ign.com/articles/116/1162433p1.html"}, {"citation": "Dans ses m\u00e9caniques autant que dans son \u00e9criture, Portal 2 est tout simplement brillant, intelligent et terriblement dr\u00f4le. Un constat qui vaut aussi bien pour son mode solo que pour son mode coop qui convertira m\u00eame les allergiques au multijoueur. Un titre r\u00e9solument incontournable dot\u00e9 d\u0027un gameplay sans cesse renouvel\u00e9 et de r\u00e9pliques qui ne tarderont pas \u00e0 devenir cultes.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45616410", "grade": null, "id": 210091, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-210091", "language": "fr", "max_score": 20.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 19.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "fr", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f4ebb9e-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 8, "name": "France"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257699", "first_year": 1997, "id": 142, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/142/jeuxvideocom/", "languages": [{"code": "fr", "id": 42, "name": "French", "ordering": 420}], "last_year": null, "name": "Jeuxvideo.com", "num_reviews": 14578, "url": "http://www.jeuxvideo.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 42009, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/42009/jaxen/", "name": "jaXen"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.jeuxvideo.com/articles/0001/00014723-portal-2-test.htm"}, {"citation": "In closing what I think makes Portal 2 such a great game is that is has a little bit of every kind of emotion crammed in to the game, whether it\u2019s humor (which there is quite a bit of), anger, frustration, relief, joy and much more.  You also have all these puzzles that get harder and harder but in the end you almost always find out how to solve them.  This makes Portal 2 challenging and rewarding at the same time which considering the style of this unique puzzle game a great title.  You can\u2019t really beat that and to top it off it is rated \u2018E\u2019 for Everyone making this a game that everyone can enjoy.  If you have never experienced the world of Portal, you are with out a doubt missing out.", "date": "2011-04-20", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45657342", "grade": null, "id": 217541, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-217541", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257959", "first_year": 2009, "id": 1554, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1554/gamingbolt/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "GamingBolt", "num_reviews": 669, "url": "http://gamingbolt.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://gamingbolt.com/portal-2-xbox-360-review"}, {"citation": "I thought Valve would have a tough time making this something other than Portal with a bunch of different levels, but I was very wrong. Without having the player fire a single bullet, it has produced one of the best FPS\u2019s to date.", "date": "2011-04-26", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45635573", "grade": null, "id": 218871, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218871", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "uk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f7e9f08-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 22, "name": "United Kingdom"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259520", "first_year": 2006, "id": 917, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/917/middle-east-gamers-megamers/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Middle East Gamers (MEgamers)", "num_reviews": 133, "url": "http://tbreak.com/megamers"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://tbreak.com/megamers/25904/reviews/portal-2-review/"}, {"citation": "Dans ses m\u00e9caniques autant que dans son \u00e9criture, Portal 2 est tout simplement brillant, intelligent et terriblement dr\u00f4le. Un constat qui vaut aussi bien pour son mode solo que pour son mode coop qui convertira m\u00eame les allergiques au multijoueur. Un titre r\u00e9solument incontournable dot\u00e9 d\u0027un gameplay sans cesse renouvel\u00e9 et de r\u00e9pliques qui ne tarderont pas \u00e0 devenir cultes.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45616414", "grade": null, "id": 210089, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-210089", "language": "fr", "max_score": 20.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 19.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "fr", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f4ebb9e-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 8, "name": "France"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257699", "first_year": 1997, "id": 142, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/142/jeuxvideocom/", "languages": [{"code": "fr", "id": 42, "name": "French", "ordering": 420}], "last_year": null, "name": "Jeuxvideo.com", "num_reviews": 14578, "url": "http://www.jeuxvideo.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 42009, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/42009/jaxen/", "name": "jaXen"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.jeuxvideo.com/articles/0001/00014722-portal-2-test.htm"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is a lot of fun and very entertaining. I think this release will be one of the hottest titles to be released this year. I found it to be as much, and often a lot more fun, then many of the games I have had an opportunity to try. The puzzles are thought provoking and the interactions and story line are very entertaining. The cooperative aspect of Portal 2 lets you play with friends and has a story all its own. The graphics in this game are frankly stunning! I highly recommend spending your precious gaming cash on this game. It is well worth the price and will provide hours of entertaining game play.", "date": "2011-06-06", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45679534", "grade": null, "id": 220109, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-220109", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 74, "name": "Macintosh"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259519", "first_year": 1993, "id": 95, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/95/inside-mac-games-img/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Inside Mac Games (IMG)", "num_reviews": 573, "url": "http://www.insidemacgames.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 183114, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/183114/alsy/", "name": "Alsy"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.insidemacgames.com/reviews/view.php?ID=1131"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 d\u00fcrfte eines der besten Spiele dieses Jahres sein, wie unser Test verr\u00e4t. Das Spiel hat uns \u00fcberragend gefallen, Kritikpunkte musste man mit der Lupe suchen.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667781", "grade": null, "id": 218844, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218844", "language": "de", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "de", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f8eb00a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 9, "name": "Germany"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258053", "first_year": 2006, "id": 600, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/600/games-aktuell/", "languages": [{"code": "de", "id": 47, "name": "German", "ordering": 470}], "last_year": null, "name": "Games Aktuell", "num_reviews": 47, "url": "http://www.gamesaktuell.de/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamesaktuell.de/Portal-2-PC-213930/Tests/Portal-2-im-Test-fuer-PC-PS3-und-Xbox-360-Das-beste-Valve-Spiel-aller-Zeiten-820597/"}, {"citation": "You\u2019re not going to find better writing, dialogue, and perfect voice acting anywhere else. The script is so brilliant and was the single reason I kept playing. The wit and humor is so amazing that you\u2019ll be laughing out loud at some of the one liners thrown your way. I\u2019m elated that it wasn\u2019t just a longer drawn out Portal experience and has its own merits to be a game all of its own. If you enjoyed Portal, you\u2019re going to love Portal 2 that much more for a number of reasons. Even if you weren\u2019t the biggest Portal fan, I still suggesting owning one of the better puzzle games with charm you\u2019ll play all year. I\u2019ve got my plushy companion cube, now I need a plushy Wheatley!", "date": "2011-05-03", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45670652", "grade": null, "id": 219018, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-219018", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259390", "first_year": 2001, "id": 420, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/420/xboxaddict/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": 2025, "name": "XboxAddict", "num_reviews": 453, "url": "http://www.xboxaddict.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.xboxaddict.com/Staff-Review/13356/Portal-2.html"}, {"citation": "Algunos conceptos como la repetici\u00f3n de determinados puzles y exigencias o pocas opciones en cooperativo no le dejan convertirse en la obra maestra que los m\u00e1s seguidores de Valve no tardar\u00e1n en ver en \u00e9l. Pese a esto, es un juego estilizado y absoluto como pocos, un ejemplo m\u00e1s de que la diversi\u00f3n que propone esta industria a veces llega a cotas inimaginables, aternativas a la marea de juegos habitual y aptas para todos los p\u00fablicos. Uno de los nombres del a\u00f1o que ha conseguido hacer de la marca Portal un fetiche rotundo en la industria y una demostraci\u00f3n de c\u00f3mo enfrentarse a un proyecto que desde siempre ha usado su propuesta diferente como el arma principal capaz de dotarle del \u00e9xito que ha acabado consiguiendo y que no es m\u00e1s que un regalo para sus seguidores y todos los jugadores en general.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45669144", "grade": null, "id": 218868, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218868", "language": "es", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "es", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f789a9a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 20, "name": "Spain"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252540", "first_year": 1997, "id": 295, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/295/meristation/", "languages": [{"code": "es", "id": 133, "name": "Spanish", "ordering": 1330}], "last_year": null, "name": "Meristation", "num_reviews": 1525, "url": "https://as.com/meristation/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.meristation.com/v3/des_analisis.php?pic=360\u0026idj=cw4b915e789cde3\u0026id=cw4daeac5244585"}, {"citation": "It\u0027s an excellent game. It is clearly a product of people who wanted to do more with the elements from the first title, and succeeded in every way. The world of Portal has expanded, the characters are given more depth, and the story pulls you back and forth in many unexpected ways with a climactic finale that might leave you breathless. Fantastic writing, excellent gameplay, and a level of polish and playtesting so high that you know it\u0027s got to be a Valve title, Portal 2 is simply a game that can not be missed.", "date": "2011-05-04", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45669170", "grade": null, "id": 218880, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218880", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "ca", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9fa117cc-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 5, "name": "Canada"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258088", "first_year": 2000, "id": 222, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/222/gamingexcellence/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "GamingExcellence", "num_reviews": 719, "url": "http://www.gamingexcellence.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamingexcellence.com/xbox360/games/2330/review.shtml"}, {"citation": "Valve took a great concept, and turned it into an interesting, intellectual marvel that stopped the gaming world. They then took that marvel and made it better again. Portal 2 is an achievement in writing, and I\u0027ll be stunned should it be robbed of appropriate accolades. Not many games this year will be as funny, charming and intellectually puzzling as Portal 2, and that\u0027s no surprise \u2013 because it\u0027s so damn good.", "date": "2011-05-14", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45670651", "grade": null, "id": 219017, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-219017", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 95.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "au", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/b24379d8-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 3, "name": "Australia"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254207", "first_year": 2002, "id": 247, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/247/xbox-world-australia-xwa/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Xbox World Australia (XWA)", "num_reviews": 193, "url": "http://www.xboxworld.com.au/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.xboxworld.com.au/games/xbox-360/portal-2/review.htm"}, {"citation": "While Portal 2 might not live quite up to the legend that was the first one, it is kind of hard for any sequel of such an innovative game to meet that kind of criteria. Portal 2 is still a fun game that provides much more content than the original, even though the game, both Single Player and Co-Op can be finished in 10 hours or so. Most likely you will find yourself compelled to play through the game\u0027s entire experience (minus the commentary track, of course) in as few sittings as possible.", "date": "2011-05-06", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45670657", "grade": null, "id": 219022, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-219022", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 95.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254963", "first_year": 1997, "id": 110, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/110/game-vortex/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Game Vortex", "num_reviews": 1095, "url": "http://www.gamevortex.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamevortex.com/gamevortex/soft_rev.php/5452/portal-2-xbox-360.html"}, {"citation": "I thought Valve would have a tough time making this something other than Portal with a bunch of different levels, but I was very wrong. Without having the player fire a single bullet, it has produced one of the best FPS\u2019s to date.", "date": "2011-04-26", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45753738", "grade": null, "id": 218872, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218872", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "uk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f7e9f08-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 22, "name": "United Kingdom"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259520", "first_year": 2006, "id": 917, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/917/middle-east-gamers-megamers/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Middle East Gamers (MEgamers)", "num_reviews": 133, "url": "http://tbreak.com/megamers"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://tbreak.com/megamers/25904/reviews/portal-2-review/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is an absolutely amazing title. Everyone was disappointed when it was delayed earlier this year, but it was more than worth the wait. Portal 2 is a masterpiece that I can see myself playing for years. The only downside for console gamers is that Valve seems to have put more into the PC version. The PC version allows you to customize your co-op bots by buying them different gear, gestures and things of that nature. It should be noted that the gestures PC players purchase will not be seen by Playstation 3 gamers if a PS3 gamer is playing co op with a PC gamer. Portal 2 is one of those titles that needs to be in every gamer\u0027s library. You owe it to yourself to experience this masterpiece and revel in the joy that is brought about by playing it. I can\u0027t wait to see what Valve comes up with next within the Portal universe.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45739791", "grade": null, "id": 219048, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-219048", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "ww", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/d74880f2-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.png", "id": 56, "name": "Worldwide"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257788", "first_year": 2005, "id": 777, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/777/totally-gaming-network/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Totally Gaming Network", "num_reviews": 245, "url": "http://www.totallygn.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.totallygn.com/2011/04/19/portal-2-review/"}, {"citation": "Overall, Portal 2 is (yet another) milestone pinnacle in design. It\u2019s a near-perfect example of how an old dog can learn new tricks. I only hope that Valve can continue this level of professionalism with Half-Life 3 because a sequel to Portal 2 is implausible and unnecessary. Which is exactly what I said at the end of Portal 1.", "date": "2011-05-03", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45680171", "grade": null, "id": 220261, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-220261", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259555", "first_year": 2004, "id": 1568, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1568/omgn-online-multiplayer-games-network/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "OMGN: Online Multiplayer Games Network", "num_reviews": 195, "url": "http://www.omgn.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.omgn.com/review/2011/05/03/portal-2-review"}, {"citation": "The gameplay, while brilliant and innovative, can drag a bit at times, but the writing carries the game through those times, and the mostly great graphics and perfect audio seal the deal. There\u0027s a lot more content than most may be expecting, too. On the whole, it\u0027s an amazing game from a company known for making amazing games. It\u0027s a truly worthwhile sequel that lives up to its predecessor, and that alone is rare enough that the game is worth checking out.", "date": "2011-04-25", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45701776", "grade": null, "id": 234281, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-234281", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254981", "first_year": 2001, "id": 425, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/425/ms-xbox-world/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "MS Xbox World", "num_reviews": 400, "url": "http://www.msxbox-world.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.msxbox-world.com/xbox360/reviews/718/portal-2/review.html"}, {"citation": "In the end, if you liked the original Portal, you should buy this game. If you like puzzle games, you should buy this game. If you like gaming at all, why are you even still reading this?  You should be playing portal 2.", "date": "2011-04-24", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45737957", "grade": null, "id": 218709, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218709", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 95.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258116", "first_year": 2007, "id": 651, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/651/ripten/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "ripten", "num_reviews": 54, "url": "http://www.ripten.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.ripten.com/2011/04/24/ripten-review-portal-2-xbox360/"}, {"citation": "Really, don\u2019t miss Portal 2. Even if you\u2019ve never played the first game, the sheer brilliance that has gone into this game\u2019s design shouldn\u2019t be missed. It\u2019s wonderfully fun and creative, while looking and sounding like a true sequel should. Don\u2019t be surprised if this one pops up on our best of 2011 list. Even if there\u2019s still no cake. (Damn it!)", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45670656", "grade": null, "id": 219020, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-219020", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 94.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.4, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257970", "first_year": 2006, "id": 586, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/586/planet-xbox-360/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Planet Xbox 360", "num_reviews": 243, "url": "http://www.planetxbox360.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.planetxbox360.com/article_13421/Portal_2"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 \u00e8 un prodotto come al momento ce ne sono pochi. Anche se non amate i puzzle game, una volta provato, difficilmente non sentirete l\u0027impulso di terminare la stanza di test nella quale siete, per poi trovarvi a provarne un\u0027altra ancora. La cura maniacale con cui ogni aspetto \u00e8 stato affinato e ottimizzato \u00e8 da applausi e dovrebbe servire da esempio per molti. La progressione delle \"missioni\", \u00e8 perfettamente bilanciata, e ci restituisce dei livelli dal game design raffinato e vario, che non ci daranno mai quel senso di gi\u00e0 visto e che tradiscono il divertimento e il piacere del team di sviluppo nell\u0027idearli. A chiudere l\u0027idilliaco quadretto c\u0027\u00e8 un comparto grafico di spessore, accompagnato da musiche, effetti sonori e doppiaggio di grandissimo livello. Il gioco non \u00e8 ovviamente perfetto, ma non saranno i tempi di caricamento forse eccessi, una seconda met\u00e0 lievemente meno curata della prima, e un boss finale non all\u0027altezza a impedirci di consigliarvi senza riserve Portal 2.", "date": "2011-05-18", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667626", "grade": null, "id": 218721, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218721", "language": "it", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 94.0, "platform": {"id": 74, "name": "Macintosh"}, "score": 9.4, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "it", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f5b5804-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 12, "name": "Italy"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254606", "first_year": 1996, "id": 1084, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1084/spazio-games/", "languages": [{"code": "it", "id": 64, "name": "Italian", "ordering": 640}], "last_year": null, "name": "Spazio Games", "num_reviews": 1213, "url": "http://www.spaziogames.it/index.aspx"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.spaziogames.it/recensioni_videogiochi/console_multi_piattaforma/11646/portal-2.aspx"}, {"citation": "Is Portal 2 worth your money? Absolutely. It is engaging, clever, genuinely funny, and all-around unique. The puzzles are always a challenge, but none of them go into the realm of the impossible \u2013 clever thinking and analysis is always enough to solve them, and gives a sense of accomplishment when you get it right.", "date": "2011-04-23", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45736430", "grade": null, "id": 218782, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218782", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 94.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.4, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257933", "first_year": 2001, "id": 193, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/193/teamxbox/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "TeamXbox", "num_reviews": 791, "url": "http://www.teamxbox.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://reviews.teamxbox.com/xbox-360/1915/Portal-2/p1/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is a memorable, challenging, beautifully designed sci-fi story. The developers walk the line between overly frustrating and underwhelming; most every puzzle will tax your problem-solving abilities, but none will cause you to throw your arms up in despair. They introduce awesome new mechanics and combine them in later puzzles, so you never feel blindsided or unprepared. The control is rock solid and smooth, the campaign is of an agreeable length, the co-op is a gimongous bonus, the audio and voice acting is some of the best you\u2019ll ever hear, and the rewards are great. I still think some of the puzzles could be a little too obscure, especially in the second half, and I\u2019m not the biggest fan of the plot. There\u2019s also the fact that, once solved, a puzzle is never so much fun again. Therefore, replay-ability takes an unavoidable hit. Still, this ranks right up there with the most accomplished and satisfying productions of this generation.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45745379", "grade": null, "id": 218764, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218764", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 94.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.4, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257693", "first_year": 1998, "id": 196, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/196/psx-extreme/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "PSX Extreme ", "num_reviews": 1401, "url": "http://www.psxextreme.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.psxextreme.com/ps3-reviews/480.html"}, {"citation": "Der Vorg\u00e4nger war schon ein kleiner Meilenstein, obwohl man ihn bei drei Stunden Spielzeit ehrlicherweise auch nicht als Vollpreistitel ansehen konnte. Entsprechend hoch war allerdings meine Erwartungshaltung bez\u00fcglich des zweiten Teils. Dass Portal 2 mich dann jedoch derma\u00dfen umhaut, h\u00e4tte ich niemals auch nur ansatzweise gedacht. Hier stimmt einfach alles: Humor, Story, Gameplay, Technik. Auch die Liebe zum Detail merkt man dem Spiel in jeder Sekunde an. Eine Anspielung auf Portal hier, ein Half-Life-Insider-Witzchen da \u2013 gro\u00dfartig! Valve hat alle Trademarks des ersten Teils beibehalten, um einige sinnvolle Neuerungen angereichert, das Spiel auf die beinahe dreifache L\u00e4nge aufgeblasen und dabei sogar noch die Qualit\u00e4t gesteigert. Und als w\u00e4re all das noch nicht genug, packt man noch einen ebenso genialen Koop-Modus obendrauf. Portal 2 ist schlicht und ergreifend ein Meisterwerk. Wer das verpasst, ist selber schuld.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45739760", "grade": null, "id": 218877, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218877", "language": "de", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 94.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 94.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "de", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f8eb00a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 9, "name": "Germany"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252811", "first_year": 2001, "id": 1263, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1263/videogameszone/", "languages": [{"code": "de", "id": 47, "name": "German", "ordering": 470}], "last_year": null, "name": "Videogameszone", "num_reviews": 157, "url": "http://www.videogameszone.de/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.videogameszone.de/Portal-2-PS3-213933/Tests/Portal-2-im-Test-fuer-PS3-und-Xbox-360-Gefaehrlich-nah-an-der-Perfektion-820996/"}, {"citation": "Der Vorg\u00e4nger war schon ein kleiner Meilenstein, obwohl man ihn bei drei Stunden Spielzeit ehrlicherweise auch nicht als Vollpreistitel ansehen konnte. Entsprechend hoch war allerdings meine Erwartungshaltung bez\u00fcglich des zweiten Teils. Dass Portal 2 mich dann jedoch derma\u00dfen umhaut, h\u00e4tte ich niemals auch nur ansatzweise gedacht. Hier stimmt einfach alles: Humor, Story, Gameplay, Technik. Auch die Liebe zum Detail merkt man dem Spiel in jeder Sekunde an. Eine Anspielung auf Portal hier, ein Half-Life-Insider-Witzchen da \u2013 gro\u00dfartig! Valve hat alle Trademarks des ersten Teils beibehalten, um einige sinnvolle Neuerungen angereichert, das Spiel auf die beinahe dreifache L\u00e4nge aufgeblasen und dabei sogar noch die Qualit\u00e4t gesteigert. Und als w\u00e4re all das noch nicht genug, packt man noch einen ebenso genialen Koop-Modus obendrauf. Portal 2 ist schlicht und ergreifend ein Meisterwerk. Wer das verpasst, ist selber schuld.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45745394", "grade": null, "id": 218876, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218876", "language": "de", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 94.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 94.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "de", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f8eb00a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 9, "name": "Germany"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252811", "first_year": 2001, "id": 1263, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1263/videogameszone/", "languages": [{"code": "de", "id": 47, "name": "German", "ordering": 470}], "last_year": null, "name": "Videogameszone", "num_reviews": 157, "url": "http://www.videogameszone.de/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.videogameszone.de/Portal-2-PS3-213933/Tests/Portal-2-im-Test-fuer-PS3-und-Xbox-360-Gefaehrlich-nah-an-der-Perfektion-820996/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 may be the best game of 2011. It may be the best game of all-time. It is certainly the best game you can play right now. I loved every moment I spent with Portal 2. I\u2019m even enjoying looking at the game sitting on my shelf knowing how much fun I will have again someday when I revisit Aperture Science, alone or hopefully with a friend who may not have played the game. Portal 2 proves that you don\u2019t have to kill things to make a great game and more importantly\u2026science is fun!", "date": "2011-04-22", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45669293", "grade": null, "id": 218965, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218965", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 94.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.4, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259516", "first_year": 1998, "id": 108, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/108/game-chronicles/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Game Chronicles", "num_reviews": 2355, "url": "http://www.gamechronicles.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamechronicles.com/reviews/360/portal2/portal2.htm"}, {"citation": "Considering the success of the original game, there were high expectations for Portal 2 and at the end of the day it has it all. A great story, great characters, awesome presentation, addictive multiplayer, and overall great gameplay. Portal 2 is a first class experience and has significant legs that will keep you coming back. It is definitely one of this year\u2019s best games.", "date": "2011-05-07", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45882702", "grade": null, "id": 246656, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-246656", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 94.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 94.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "ca", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9fa117cc-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 5, "name": "Canada"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259338", "first_year": 2011, "id": 1720, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1720/cogconnected-canadian-online-gamers-network/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "COGConnected / Canadian Online Gamers Network", "num_reviews": 1561, "url": "http://cogconnected.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://canadianonlinegamers.com/review/portal-2/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is one of those rare games that you can point to as a stellar product. Valve went above and beyond to ensure that the fans of the first game would be pleased with the sequel. Being the first full-length game in the series, Portal 2 is an ambitious project that succeeds even more so than the original. Adding several hours\u2019 worth of gameplay, co-op missions, and the promise for free downloadable content all make this an incredible package. It\u2019s hard to see replaying a ton of times, but as a rental, Portal 2 is a must-play. Without a doubt one of Valve\u2019s finest works.", "date": "2011-05-01", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45755756", "grade": null, "id": 211550, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-211550", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 94.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.4, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259365", "first_year": 2000, "id": 340, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/340/game-freaks-365/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Game Freaks 365", "num_reviews": 1394, "url": "http://gamefreaks365.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 8375, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/8375/jeanne/", "name": "Jeanne"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://gamefreaks365.com/review.php?artid=1853"}, {"citation": "A challenging, hilarious, and mind-expanding puzzle experience for one or two\u2014treasure your first time through.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45556753", "grade": null, "id": 211102, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-211102", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 94.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 94.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259440", "first_year": 1994, "id": 22, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/22/pc-gamer/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "PC Gamer", "num_reviews": 2226, "url": "http://www.pcgamer.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 55856, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/55856/scaryfun/", "name": "Scaryfun"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.pcgamer.com/2011/04/19/portal-2-review/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 \u00e8 una perla rara nel panorama videoludico attuale. Curato fino all\u2019inverosimile, divertente, ironico, longevo, tante sono le qualit\u00e0 che i ragazzi di Valve sono riusciti a donare alla loro ultima creazione. Una produzione eccezionale, che non mancher\u00e0 di divertire tutti coloro che sono alla ricerca di un gioco diverso dai canoni classici, dove non si uccidono alieni o zombie, ma si usano i propri riflessi e si fa funzionare il cervello per trovare l\u2019uscita dagli esperimenti pi\u00f9 folli che mente umana possa concepire. Un cast di personaggi divertenti e carismatici completa il quadro, la cui classica ciliegina sulla torta \u00e8 rappresentata da un comparto sonoro di livello e una canzoncina finale che fischietteremo a lungo. I\u2019m making a note here: HUGE SUCCESS.", "date": "2011-04-20", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667616", "grade": null, "id": 218719, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218719", "language": "it", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 94.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.4, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "it", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f5b5804-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 12, "name": "Italy"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254606", "first_year": 1996, "id": 1084, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1084/spazio-games/", "languages": [{"code": "it", "id": 64, "name": "Italian", "ordering": 640}], "last_year": null, "name": "Spazio Games", "num_reviews": 1213, "url": "http://www.spaziogames.it/index.aspx"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.spaziogames.it/recensioni_videogiochi/console_multi_piattaforma/11525/portal-2.aspx"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is a top notch experience throughout. Whether you\u0027re a fan of the first game, looking for a grade A title, or simply looking for an experience other than the myriad of shooters out there today which, with Portal 2, you can\u0027t go wrong here. If the story doesn\u0027t keep you coming back the cooperative multiplayer or puzzle based gameplay will. Portal 2 is another great title from Valve and definitely worth the price of admission.", "date": "2011-05-07", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45670667", "grade": null, "id": 219024, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-219024", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 94.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.4, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "ca", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9fa117cc-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 5, "name": "Canada"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257668", "first_year": 1990, "id": 234, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/234/da-gameboyz/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Da Gameboyz", "num_reviews": 320, "url": "http://www.game-boyz.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.game-boyz.com/content/node/17974"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 \u00e8 un prodotto come al momento ce ne sono pochi. Anche se non amate i puzzle game, una volta provato, difficilmente non sentirete l\u0027impulso di terminare la stanza di test nella quale siete, per poi trovarvi a provarne un\u0027altra ancora. La cura maniacale con cui ogni aspetto \u00e8 stato affinato e ottimizzato \u00e8 da applausi e dovrebbe servire da esempio per molti. La progressione delle \"missioni\", \u00e8 perfettamente bilanciata, e ci restituisce dei livelli dal game design raffinato e vario, che non ci daranno mai quel senso di gi\u00e0 visto e che tradiscono il divertimento e il piacere del team di sviluppo nell\u0027idearli. A chiudere l\u0027idilliaco quadretto c\u0027\u00e8 un comparto grafico di spessore, accompagnato da musiche, effetti sonori e doppiaggio di grandissimo livello. Il gioco non \u00e8 ovviamente perfetto, ma non saranno i tempi di caricamento forse eccessi, una seconda met\u00e0 lievemente meno curata della prima, e un boss finale non all\u0027altezza a impedirci di consigliarvi senza riserve Portal 2.", "date": "2011-05-18", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45501416", "grade": null, "id": 218720, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218720", "language": "it", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 94.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.4, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "it", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f5b5804-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 12, "name": "Italy"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254606", "first_year": 1996, "id": 1084, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1084/spazio-games/", "languages": [{"code": "it", "id": 64, "name": "Italian", "ordering": 640}], "last_year": null, "name": "Spazio Games", "num_reviews": 1213, "url": "http://www.spaziogames.it/index.aspx"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.spaziogames.it/recensioni_videogiochi/console_multi_piattaforma/11646/portal-2.aspx"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is a strong contender for 2011\u0027s game of the year. If you loved the first Portal, you absolutely must pick this one up. And even if you\u0027re brand new to the series, Portal 2 includes groundbreaking gameplay, a collection of deep and nuanced characters, a completely insane story, and some incredible gaming moments you\u0027ll probably never forget.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667742", "grade": null, "id": 218830, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218830", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 94.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 4.7, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254219", "first_year": 1999, "id": 12, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/12/cheat-code-central/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Cheat Code Central", "num_reviews": 2674, "url": "http://www.cheatcc.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://cheatcc.com/ps3/rev/portal2review.html"}, {"citation": "Sentido del humor, rompecabezas tremendamente ingeniosos y h\u00e1bil mezcla de destreza cerebral con habilidad... \u00bfImposible de combinar? En absoluto. Valve demuestra una vez m\u00e1s su incre\u00edble maestr\u00eda con uno de los mejores videojuegos en lo que va de a\u00f1o. Portal 2 es, al mismo tiempo, imaginativo, estimulante, adictivo y cargado de momentos hilarantes, y como tal puede ser recomendado a cualquier tipo de p\u00fablico (sin importar edad ni condici\u00f3n) con la seguridad del acierto.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45737951", "grade": null, "id": 218697, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218697", "language": "es", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 94.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.4, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "es", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f789a9a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 20, "name": "Spain"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257761", "first_year": 2004, "id": 444, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/444/3d-juegos/", "languages": [{"code": "es", "id": 133, "name": "Spanish", "ordering": 1330}], "last_year": null, "name": "3D Juegos", "num_reviews": 1031, "url": "http://www.3djuegos.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.3djuegos.com/juegos/analisis/8275/0/portal-2/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is an outstanding sequel that did everything it needed to do to transition a bonus game into a full-fledged franchise. The series definitely has life in it and, if the developers continue to put this much love and effort into sequels, I could easily see it becoming one of the staples of the industry. If you enjoyed the original, this is a must-own title. If you enjoy puzzle games, go buy it now. Needless to say, I cannot recommend this game enough to anyone who enjoys a uniqu