tates"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254219", "first_year": 1999, "id": 12, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/12/cheat-code-central/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Cheat Code Central", "num_reviews": 2674, "url": "http://www.cheatcc.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://cheatcc.com/pc/rev/portal2review.html"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is an outstanding sequel that did everything it needed to do to transition a bonus game into a full-fledged franchise. The series definitely has life in it and, if the developers continue to put this much love and effort into sequels, I could easily see it becoming one of the staples of the industry. If you enjoyed the original, this is a must-own title. If you enjoy puzzle games, go buy it now. Needless to say, I cannot recommend this game enough to anyone who enjoys a unique and entertaining experience.", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45669172", "grade": null, "id": 218882, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218882", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 94.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.4, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259346", "first_year": 2001, "id": 618, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/618/ztgamedomain/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "ZTGameDomain", "num_reviews": 1448, "url": "http://www.ztgamedomain.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.ztgd.com/reviews/7997/portal-2-rev/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 \u00e8 una perla rara nel panorama videoludico attuale. Curato fino all\u2019inverosimile, divertente, ironico, longevo, tante sono le qualit\u00e0 che i ragazzi di Valve sono riusciti a donare alla loro ultima creazione. Una produzione eccezionale, che non mancher\u00e0 di divertire tutti coloro che sono alla ricerca di un gioco diverso dai canoni classici, dove non si uccidono alieni o zombie, ma si usano i propri riflessi e si fa funzionare il cervello per trovare l\u2019uscita dagli esperimenti pi\u00f9 folli che mente umana possa concepire. Un cast di personaggi divertenti e carismatici completa il quadro, la cui classica ciliegina sulla torta \u00e8 rappresentata da un comparto sonoro di livello e una canzoncina finale che fischietteremo a lungo. I\u2019m making a note here: HUGE SUCCESS.", "date": "2011-04-20", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45737963", "grade": null, "id": 218718, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218718", "language": "it", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 94.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.4, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "it", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f5b5804-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 12, "name": "Italy"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254606", "first_year": 1996, "id": 1084, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1084/spazio-games/", "languages": [{"code": "it", "id": 64, "name": "Italian", "ordering": 640}], "last_year": null, "name": "Spazio Games", "num_reviews": 1213, "url": "http://www.spaziogames.it/index.aspx"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.spaziogames.it/recensioni_videogiochi/console_multi_piattaforma/11525/portal-2.aspx"}, {"citation": "If you enjoyed the original Portal, getting the sequel is a no-brainer.  I have enjoyed the single and multiplayer campaigns thoroughly and can\u2019t recommend this game enough.  Even though the tests are similar in nature to the original game, the character development is what makes this sequel truly stand out.  While my kids enjoy the original Portal, I\u2019m a little hesitant on loading this on their machines due to the mild language.  My kids are 6 and under so I\u2019ll hold off until they\u2019re a little older.  After all, it is rated E10+.", "date": "2011-05-24", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667620", "grade": null, "id": 218727, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218727", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 94.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 94.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257934", "first_year": 2002, "id": 400, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/400/christ-centered-gamer-christ-centered-game-reviews/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Christ Centered Gamer / Christ Centered Game Reviews", "num_reviews": 499, "url": "http://www.christcenteredgamer.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.ccgr.org/index.php/reviews/18-computer/5262-portal-2-pc"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is a strong contender for 2011\u0027s game of the year. If you loved the first Portal, you absolutely must pick this one up. And even if you\u0027re brand new to the series, Portal 2 includes groundbreaking gameplay, a collection of deep and nuanced characters, a completely insane story, and some incredible gaming moments you\u0027ll probably never forget.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667741", "grade": null, "id": 218831, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218831", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 94.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 4.7, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254219", "first_year": 1999, "id": 12, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/12/cheat-code-central/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Cheat Code Central", "num_reviews": 2674, "url": "http://www.cheatcc.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://cheatcc.com/xbox360/rev/portal2review.html"}, {"citation": "Valve\u0027s sequel is another fantastic display of no-filler design; gameplay is relentlessly imaginative and evolves seamlessly from effortless hurdle to mind-boggling physics test - and we\u0027d throw ourselves through the ceiling for more. Imaginative, challenging, hilarious and sometimes a bit exhausting, Portal 2 is one of 2011\u0027s most interesting, challenging blockbusters. Just make sure you take your sweet, sweet time with it - because you\u0027ll probably feel a hole in your head once it\u0027s done and dusted.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667734", "grade": null, "id": 218829, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218829", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 93.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.3, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "uk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f7e9f08-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 22, "name": "United Kingdom"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259537", "first_year": 1981, "id": 78, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/78/computer-and-video-games-cvg/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Computer and Video Games (CVG)", "num_reviews": 6620, "url": "http://www.computerandvideogames.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.computerandvideogames.com/298682/reviews/portal-2-review/"}, {"citation": "Valve has worked its magic yet again with Portal 2, creating a mind-blowing game that\u0027s simply superb in both single-player and co-op. In other words, it\u0027s hole-ly essential.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45576545", "grade": null, "id": 211345, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-211345", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 93.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 93.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254125", "first_year": 2007, "id": 902, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/902/xboxachievements/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "XboxAchievements", "num_reviews": 837, "url": "http://www.xboxachievements.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 64986, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/64986/yearman/", "name": "Yearman"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.xbox360achievements.org/game/portal-2/review/"}, {"citation": "Witzige Neuerung, deutlich mehr Umfang, 1A-Koop-Modus - so muss ein zweiter Teil aussehen. Hei\u00dfer Kandidat zum Spiel des Jahres.", "date": "2011-04", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=4295392100", "grade": null, "id": 489001, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-489001", "language": "de", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 93.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.3, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "de", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f8eb00a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 9, "name": "Germany"}, "description": "\u003cp\u003e360 Live was a German print magazine which exclusively covered the Xbox 360. It was published by Airmotion Games Verlags GmbH between November 2005 (issue 01/2006) and December 2013 (issue 01/2014). \u003c/p\u003e", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=58133265", "first_year": 2005, "id": 1834, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1834/360-live/", "languages": [{"code": "de", "id": 47, "name": "German", "ordering": 470}], "last_year": 2013, "name": "360 LIVE", "num_reviews": 977, "url": "http://www.360-live.de/"}, "submitter": {"id": 136314, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/136314/patrick_b/", "name": "Patrick Bregger"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": null}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is, in some ways, the raw essence of a game. Its puzzle-solving gameplay manages to be challenging but accessible. Every time you solve a room, you are filled with satisfaction, while at the same time thinking \u2018How could I not see that?\u2019 Even if it didn\u2019t have a plot, it still would be fantastic, and the fact that it actually gets engaging is a bonus. Add to that one of the most satisfying co-op game experiences out there and an endearingly geeky sense of humour, and you have one of the most complete games of recent years. While it does not push boundaries of graphics or sound, it innovates in terms of intelligent, challenging gameplay. My only complaint is that the game has to end, but with rumours of a map-maker coming out in the near future, its appeal could well extend on to infinity.", "date": "2011-05-26", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667581", "grade": null, "id": 218703, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218703", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 93.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.3, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257800", "first_year": 2005, "id": 697, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/697/hooked-gamers/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Hooked Gamers", "num_reviews": 2431, "url": "http://www.hookedgamers.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.hookedgamers.com/ps3/portal_2/review/article-727.html"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is the shining example and standard for \"AAA\" gaming. The only problem is games like this are very few and far between. Very nice work, Valve.", "date": "2011-05-25", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=4299175168", "grade": null, "id": 657228, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-657228", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 93.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 93.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "au", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/b24379d8-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 3, "name": "Australia"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=4295876597", "first_year": 2007, "id": 3457, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/3457/tweaktown/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "TweakTown", "num_reviews": 6, "url": "https://www.tweaktown.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 1121630, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/1121630/rocket55/", "name": "Rocket"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "https://www.tweaktown.com/gaming/4111/portal_2_pc_review/index.html"}, {"citation": "Valve has once again released a top-notch game. The story and characters are engaging, new features are intriguing and the co-op is an amazing edition. Fans of the first game will not be disappointed here. This game is definitely worth checking out.", "date": "2011-05-05", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45582849", "grade": null, "id": 211447, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-211447", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 93.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.3, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257854", "first_year": 2006, "id": 1010, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1010/411maniacom/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "411mania.com", "num_reviews": 1762, "url": "http://www.411mania.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 8375, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/8375/jeanne/", "name": "Jeanne"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.411mania.com/games/reviews/184841/Portal-2-(Xbox-360)-Review.htm"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is, in short, a terrific game, throwing you headfirst into a realm of intense and brain-teasing puzzles and great humor. The story is richer this time around too. The trademark Half-Life style atmosphere is there... we feel it, oh yes we do, as much as we felt the magic that made the previous Portal game so exciting to play. Things were spiced up with the robot-flavored coop mode, which we highly recommend to any gamers who are on the lookout for a decent challenge in addition to some serious giggling. Some may miss more competitive aspects such as leaderboards, but that doesn\u0027t mean they should sit this one out. If anybody had something bad to say about this game, well, don\u0027t be misled by it. You should buy this game. It\u0027s worth every penny.", "date": "2011-04-27", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45505333", "grade": null, "id": 218726, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218726", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 93.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.3, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259527", "first_year": 2000, "id": 113, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/113/actiontrip/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "ActionTrip", "num_reviews": 872, "url": "http://www.actiontrip.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.actiontrip.com/reviews/portal-2.phtml"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 stands on it\u2019s own as an amazing puzzle shooter that it makes me wonder if Valve has enough magic left to make a third in the series. Valve has gone far above and beyond expectations with this game that as of right now it could be a Game of the Year contender. If you\u2019re looking for something other than your average gaming experience then give Portal 2 a try. You will not be disappointed.", "date": "2011-05-28", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=1969701719", "grade": null, "id": 358571, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-358571", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 92.5, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.25, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=1959470425", "first_year": 2011, "id": 2249, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/2249/gamegravy/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gamegravy", "num_reviews": 593, "url": "http://gamegravy.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 37485, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/37485/alaka/", "name": "Alaka"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://gamegravy.com/review/portal-2/"}, {"citation": "Als Portal een experiment was, dan is Portal 2 een succesvolle toepassing daarvan. De grappige dialogen en unieke gameplay sleuren je vanaf de eerste minuut mee. De intimiteit en verbazing van Portal zijn verminderd, maar er is meer dan genoeg in de plaats gekomen. Een unieke game die perfect belichaamt waar het medium toe in staat is.", "date": "2011-04-27", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=4298039169", "grade": null, "id": 609704, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-609704", "language": "nl", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 92.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 92.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "be", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/e95f04a0-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 4, "name": "Belgium"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252885", "first_year": 2005, "id": 975, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/975/gamequarter/", "languages": [{"code": "nl", "id": 34, "name": "Dutch", "ordering": 340}], "last_year": null, "name": "GameQuarter", "num_reviews": 2313, "url": "http://www.gamequarter.be/"}, "submitter": {"id": 1002357, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/1002357/blasterjack/", "name": "Blasterjack"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "https://www.gamequarter.be/reviews/portal-2/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is a finely polished experience that you should not miss. It is also fairly short but ultimately that isn\u0027t the biggest issue - the chronic lack of challenge for those of us that already know how to \"think with portals\" is. A lot is saved by the excellent co-op mode but I weep for the missed opportunities. Still, you really can\u0027t have difficulty settings for puzzles and everyone has to be able to complete the game. Definitely a masterpiece, but could have been so much more.", "date": "2011-04-27", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45652925", "grade": null, "id": 217216, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-217216", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 92.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 92.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258081", "first_year": 2007, "id": 596, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/596/yougamers/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "YouGamers", "num_reviews": 146, "url": "http://www.yougamers.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 133029, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/133029/calaisianmindthief/", "name": "CalaisianMindthief"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.yougamers.com/reviews/31152_portal_2/"}, {"citation": "Waarschuwing: van zodra je Portal 2 in je leven toelaat, is er geen weg meer terug. Je zult denken in portalen, dromen van portalen en lachen met portalen. Valve levert nogmaals een meesterwerk af.", "date": "2011-04-29", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45789100", "grade": null, "id": 241752, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-241752", "language": "nl", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 92.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 92.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "be", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/e95f04a0-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 4, "name": "Belgium"}, "description": "\u003cp\u003eGameplay was launched in 1994 as PC Gamepro. As the name implies, it focused on PC games. During the second year, the name was changed to PC Gameplay.\u003c/p\