, die sich aber (fast) immer logisch l\u00f6sen lassen. Der Humor ist ebenfalls eine Klasse f\u00fcr sich, denn sowohl die Quasselstrippe Wheatley als auch GlaDOS zaubern mir mit ihren lustigen, bissigen, fiesen und trockenen Spr\u00fcchen immer wieder ein L\u00e4cheln ins Gesicht. Wenn man Portal 2 \u00fcberhaupt etwas vorwerfen kann, dann ist es der etwas zu z\u00e4he Mittelteil, in dem sich die Spielwelt zwar etwas \u00f6ffnet, aber den Spieler mangels \u00dcbersicht zu sehr in vermeintliche Sackgassen man\u00f6vriert - ein optionales Hilfesystem h\u00e4tte dem vorgebeugt.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=373395162", "grade": null, "id": 292732, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-292732", "language": "de", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 92.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 92.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "de", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f8eb00a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 9, "name": "Germany"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257867", "first_year": 2000, "id": 395, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/395/4playersde-4p-das-spielemagazin/", "languages": [{"code": "de", "id": 47, "name": "German", "ordering": 470}], "last_year": null, "name": "4Players.de / 4P: Das Spielemagazin", "num_reviews": 12789, "url": "https://www.4p.de"}, "submitter": {"id": 136314, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/136314/patrick_b/", "name": "Patrick Bregger"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.4players.de/4players.php/dispbericht/Allgemein/Test/21603/71752/0/Portal_2.html"}, {"citation": "Portal besitzt auch in der Fortsetzung den Charme eines Independent-Titels, schafft es aber gleichzeitig, mit einem erheblich gr\u00f6\u00dferen Umfang zu \u00fcberzeugen. Die R\u00e4tsel sind schlicht und einfach grandios ausgefuchst und die gro\u00dfe St\u00e4rke des Spiels. Fast gleichauf steht der gro\u00dfartige Humor. Zu GlaDOS zynischen Spr\u00fcchen gesellt sich diesmal unter anderem der slapstickartige Witz eures Begleiters Wheatley und des Kooperativduos Atlas und P-body hinzu. Die neuen Figuren f\u00fcgen sich genauso nahtlos ins Portal-Universum ein wie die neuen Spielelemente. Hier wurde nicht k\u00fcnstlich aufgeblasen, sondern sinnvoll erg\u00e4nzt, was das Portalerlebnis erheblich bereichert. Kurz gesagt: Portal 2 ist noch gro\u00dfartiger als der ohnehin schon geniale Vorg\u00e4nger.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667625", "grade": null, "id": 218724, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218724", "language": "de", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 92.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 92.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "de", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f8eb00a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 9, "name": "Germany"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259332", "first_year": 2000, "id": 364, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/364/gameswelt/", "languages": [{"code": "de", "id": 47, "name": "German", "ordering": 470}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gameswelt", "num_reviews": 640, "url": "http://gameswelt.de/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gameswelt.de/articles/reviews/7048-Portal_2/index.html"}, {"citation": "In the end, Portal 2 went extremely close to knocking my socks off and living up the immense amount of hype I\u0027d heard about it. The puzzles are taxing, and new elements are deftly thrown into the mix to keep things interesting. There is a definite feeling of satisfaction when you complete some of the trickier puzzles that may just border on euphoria. The voice-acting and script are top-notch, perhaps the best I\u0027ve ever heard. The game does lose its way a little bit during the middle, but that aside it\u0027s hard to find fault with it. If you have any interest in puzzle games, or games that ooze humour Portal 2 comes highly recommended.", "date": "2011-06-01", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45669302", "grade": null, "id": 218979, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218979", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 92.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 92.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "au", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/b24379d8-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 3, "name": "Australia"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254943", "first_year": 1999, "id": 233, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/233/futuregameznet/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Futuregamez.net", "num_reviews": 380, "url": "http://www.futuregamez.net/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.futuregamez.net/ps3games/portal2/review.html"}, {"citation": "Ein Pflicht-Programm f\u00fcr Fans des Vorg\u00e4ngers - und generell so ziemlich jeden Spieler, der eine schlaue, spa\u00dfige und originelle Herausforderung sucht. Wenn man Schritt f\u00fcr Schritt einen Level entr\u00e4tselt, knistert der Spielspa\u00df konstant, bis hin zum erheblichen Wohlgef\u00fchl bei der letztendlichen Meisterung. Die Gels sind der Hit, die anderen neuen Puzzle-Elemente bereichern ebenfalls das Portal-Spielprinzip. Auch wenn ich mitunter kr\u00e4ftig gegr\u00fcbelt und auch mal geflucht habe - das Level-Design ist fair und die Motivation bis zum Finale hoch.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45558379", "grade": null, "id": 211138, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-211138", "language": "de", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 91.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 91.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "de", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f8eb00a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 9, "name": "Germany"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257644", "first_year": 1997, "id": 72, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/72/gamestar-germany/", "languages": [{"code": "de", "id": 47, "name": "German", "ordering": 470}], "last_year": null, "name": "GameStar (Germany)", "num_reviews": 6676, "url": "http://www.gamestar.de/"}, "submitter": {"id": 136314, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/136314/patrick_b/", "name": "Patrick Bregger"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamestar.de/spiele/portal-2/test/portal_2,45983,2322268.html"}, {"citation": "Fans auf der ganzen Welt lechzten seit 2007 nach einer Fortsetzung, und hier ist mehr als das: Nicht nur ein w\u00fcrdiger Nachfolger, sondern ein Spiel, das Ma\u00dfst\u00e4be neu setzt! \u201ePortal 2\u201c ist definitiv ein Must have-Titel f\u00fcr s\u00e4mtliche Plattformen, denn w\u00e4hrend das Portal-Shooter-Gameplay schon 2007 auf dem PC f\u00fcr einen Wahnsinns-Hype gesorgt hat, spielt es sich auch auf der PS3 mehr als nur hervorragend. Eine tiefe Verneigung vor Valve, die Entscheidung, \u201ePortal 2\u201c auf PC, Mac, PS3 und Xbox 360 zu bringen, war goldrichtig! Nun steht dem Siegeszug von GLaDOS endg\u00fcltig nichts mehr im Wege, und die Suchtgefahr ist imminent...", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667797", "grade": null, "id": 218855, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218855", "language": "de", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 91.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 91.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "at", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f3755d0-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 25, "name": "Austria"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257983", "first_year": 2001, "id": 696, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/696/gamingxp/", "languages": [{"code": "de", "id": 47, "name": "German", "ordering": 470}], "last_year": null, "name": "GamingXP", "num_reviews": 505, "url": "http://www.gamingxp.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamingxp.com/bericht-4666-valve_corporation-valve_software-ps3-portal_2.htm"}, {"citation": "Con Portal 2 Valve dimostra per l\u0027ennesima volta come deve essere strutturato un sequel per essere inequivocabilmente giudicato migliore del suo predecessore. Il titolo \u00e8 curato in modo maniacale in ogni suo aspetto: \u00e8 pi\u00f9 longevo e vario, ha una storia pi\u00f9 corposa e come da tradizione dello sviluppatore di Seattle, piena di sfaccettature, rimandi ed easter eggs. Persino la gestione dell\u0027aumento di difficolt\u00e0 \u00e8 impeccabile. Tuttavia non mancano delle sbavature che possono acquistare valore diverso in base alle esigenze del giocatore: dall\u0027aspetto tecnico sottotono a una sezione centrale troppo stiracchiata e povera di mordente.\nUna nota a margine: se state prendendo in considerazione la versione PC del gioco, che pu\u00f2 essere acquistata a meno di 40 euro, aggiungete 3 punti decimali al voto.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45739793", "grade": null, "id": 219052, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-219052", "language": "it", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 91.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.1, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "it", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f5b5804-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 12, "name": "Italy"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254195", "first_year": 2003, "id": 1072, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1072/multiplayerit/", "languages": [{"code": "it", "id": 64, "name": "Italian", "ordering": 640}], "last_year": null, "name": "Multiplayer.it", "num_reviews": 1712, "url": "http://www.multiplayer.it/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://multiplayer.it/recensioni/87706-portal-2-portali-al-quadrato.html"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 had a lot to live up to, but it doesn\u2019t feel like it\u2019s living in its predecessor\u2019s shadow. Portal has rightfully earned its place in pop culture, and that frees Valve to expand on the franchise in ways they see fit. Portal 2 is a bigger and more organic experience, and even if it\u2019s not as perfect as its predecessor was, that\u2019s part of what makes it so much more human.", "date": "2011-04-25", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45670665", "grade": null, "id": 219028, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-219028", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259353", "first_year": 1998, "id": 181, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/181/honestgamers-staff-reviews-only/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "HonestGamers (Staff reviews only)", "num_reviews": 1736, "url": "http://www.honestgamers.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.honestgamers.com/reviews/9364.html"}, {"citation": "Perhaps if I\u2019m honest, Portal 2 is not the most instantly re-playable game in the world (Valve are working on some downloadable content which is due for release in the summer, though), and loading times are a little longer than most would like, but this is still a truly excellent sequel that is witty, satisfying, clever, and bigger and bolder than the petite original game. If Portal was a mini masterpiece, then Portal 2 is one of mega proportions.", "date": "2011-05-08", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45670662", "grade": null, "id": 219025, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-219025", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "uk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f7e9f08-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 22, "name": "United Kingdom"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257783", "first_year": 2002, "id": 617, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/617/console-obsession/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Console Obsession", "num_reviews": 291, "url": "http://www.consoleob.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.consoleob.com/reviews/portal-2-xbox-360-review/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 ist ein nahezu perfektes Spiel f\u00fcr das, was es ist. Es gibt Kleinigkeiten wie nun v\u00f6llig unbewegliches Interior, was sich anfangs komisch anf\u00fchlt, weil alles auf mysteri\u00f6se Art und Weise am Boden klebt. Vielleicht haben sie bei Valve in Tests herausgefunden, dass einige Spieler sich einfach zu lange damit besch\u00e4ftigt haben, das Zeug durch die Level zu schleppen auf der Suche nach der L\u00f6sung... wer wei\u00df. Richtig schade ist nur, dass die Kampagne - je nach nach F\u00e4higkeiten - in sieben bis zehn Stunden erledigt ist. Dazu gesellen sich vier bis sechs Stunden Koop-Material. Das ist eigentlich genug, aber man will einfach nicht, dass es endet. Und hatte mir GLaDOS nicht am Anfang versprochen, dass ich hier f\u00fcr immer testen darf? Verdammte L\u00fcgnerin! Anderseits: Das war sie doch schon immer, oder etwa nicht!?!", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45507221", "grade": null, "id": 218798, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218798", "language": "de", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "dk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/c4d8fa64-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 26, "name": "Denmark"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257965", "first_year": 2009, "id": 1559, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1559/gamereactor-germany/", "languages": [{"code": "de", "id": 47, "name": "German", "ordering": 470}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gamereactor (Germany)", "num_reviews": 51, "url": "http://www.gamereactor.de/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamereactor.de/Kritiken/5850/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is in the business of defying players\u2019 expectations. Valve never wants you to predict what\u2019s going to happen at any moment, and delights in subtly setting those pins up and knocking them down. Even more than the clever gameplay mechanics and sharply written story, the smiles and laughter that such a carefully crafted game can extract from you mean this one will stay with you for years to come.", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45669157", "grade": null, "id": 218875, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218875", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259359", "first_year": 1994, "id": 1078, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1078/wired/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Wired", "num_reviews": 78, "url": "http://blog.wired.com/games/reviews/index.html"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://www.wired.com/gamelife/2011/04/portal-2-review/all/1"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 delivers, and it does it in style, creating one of the most meticulously designed, thrilling and delightful playgrounds we\u2019ve ever seen. It\u2019s a game with a magical take on momentum, where single bounds over tall buildings are business as usual, where every surface is a potential launchpad, and the entire experience is a belly laugh. Valve has a pretty good record with the number two, but attempting to inflate Portal\u2019s perfectly formed package could easily have been a disaster. Naturally, the sequel doesn\u2019t feel as bracingly fresh as the 2007 game, but it\u2019s precisely the sort of dizzying follow-up the original deserves.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45739769", "grade": null, "id": 218972, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218972", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "uk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f7e9f08-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 22, "name": "United Kingdom"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252876", "first_year": 1993, "id": 129, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/129/edge/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Edge", "num_reviews": 1477, "url": "http://www.edge-online.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.next-gen.biz/reviews/portal-2-review"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 definitely won\u2019t be everyone\u2019s cup of tea, but then, what game is? Thanks mainly to Wheatley and GLaDOS\u2019s cuttingly witty dialog, its solo story feels less lonely than the original and the new co-op mode means that problems can be shared, often with hilarious results. If you want a game to test both your hand/eye coordination and your grey matter while simultaneously keeping you genuinely amused with some sharp humour, look no further.", "date": "2011-05-06", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45739782", "grade": null, "id": 219023, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-219023", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "uk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f7e9f08-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 22, "name": "United Kingdom"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259490", "first_year": 2002, "id": 199, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/199/gamecell-uk/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "GameCell UK", "num_reviews": 470, "url": "http://www.gamecell.co.uk/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamecell.co.uk/360/Portal_2.htm"}, {"citation": "From gloriously glib opening to predictably musical finale, Portal 2 is a genuine delight and a game of rare quality. A well-judged sense of humour meets with some truly ingenious puzzle design to create a gaming experience that will linger long in the memory. But look at us, still talking when there\u2019s science to do\u2026", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45670675", "grade": null, "id": 219032, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-219032", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "uk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f7e9f08-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 22, "name": "United Kingdom"}, "description": "\u003cp\u003eGamesTM was a multi-format product running 2002 -2018. \nIt was originally owned by Imagine Publishing, but the entire Imagine portfolio was acquired by Future in 2016.\u003c/p\u003e", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258075", "first_year": 2002, "id": 650, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/650/games-tm/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": 2018, "name": "Games TM", "num_reviews": 3528, "url": null}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamestm.co.uk/reviews/portal-2-review/"}, {"citation": "Una sceneggiatura raffinata e dei giochi di logica che solleticheranno la nostra mente e ci terranno incollati allo schermo: ecco quello che Portal in definitiva \u00e8. Un titolo artisticamente raffinato e ricco di scorci surreali, che premier\u00e0 la notra intelligenza e capacit\u00e0 di adattamento ad un universo paradossale e intrigante. Consiglio a tutti questo Puzzle Game unico nel suo genere, che vi terr\u00e0 impegnati, a seconda della vostra abilit\u00e0 col \u201cpensiero laterale\u201d, dalle 8-10 ore per la campagna in singolo e ad altre 6-8 ore per la campagna cooperativa. Perdersi in questo mondo governato dalle macchine e dalla Scienza sfrenata \u00e8 un\u2019esperienza da provare. Come dicevo in principio, una perla rara, un titolo fuori dagli schemi in un periodo in cui troppo spesso l\u2019obiettivo di una Software House \u00e8 puntare al blockbuster e al profitto ad ogni costo, rinunciando all\u2019originalit\u00e0 e all\u2019azzardo.", "date": "2011-04-25", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45992995", "grade": null, "id": 261733, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-261733", "language": "it", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "it", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f5b5804-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 12, "name": "Italy"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258027", "first_year": 2007, "id": 837, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/837/gamescollection/", "languages": [{"code": "it", "id": 64, "name": "Italian", "ordering": 640}], "last_year": null, "name": "GamesCollection", "num_reviews": 613, "url": "http://www.gamescollection.it/"}, "submitter": {"id": 183114, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/183114/alsy/", "name": "Alsy"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamescollection.it/reviews/show/560"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 on loistava taidonn\u00e4yte Valvelta. Peli ei aliarvioi pelaajia ja t\u00e4ytt\u00e4\u00e4 fanien odotukset 100-prosenttisen varmasti. Pikkuasioista voi valittaa, mutta en ep\u00e4ile v\u00e4itt\u00e4\u00e4, ett\u00e4 kyseess\u00e4 on yksi vuoden parhaimpia pelej\u00e4. Peli tarjoaa makeaa mahan t\u00e4ydelt\u00e4 ja j\u00e4tt\u00e4\u00e4 silti toivomaan entist\u00e4 enemm\u00e4n lis\u00e4\u00e4. Onneksi peli, saavutuksineen ja salaisuuksineen, tarjoaa uudelleenpelattavuutta ruhtinaallisesti.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667690", "grade": null, "id": 218792, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218792", "language": "fi", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "fi", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f553136-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 7, "name": "Finland"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257962", "first_year": 2007, "id": 918, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/918/gamereactor-finland/", "languages": [{"code": "fi", "id": 41, "name": "Finnish", "ordering": 410}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gamereactor (Finland)", "num_reviews": 204, "url": "http://www.gamereactor.fi/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamereactor.fi/arviot/80399/"}, {"citation": "If you\u2019re still reading this review and aren\u2019t yet convinced you need to play this game, then there is little hope for you. Between the marvellous story, perfect pacing, evolving/subtle soundtrack, challenging but not frustrating puzzles, and one of the absolute best ending sequences the likes of which may never be seen again, there is literally nothing to complain about this game. And the social gamers amongst us will be completely satisfied after running through the co-op story with a friend (or even complete stranger!). While it could be argued that Portal 2 has little replay value, that will become a moot point as user-generated levels are produced, which are expected to be deliverable to the PlayStation 3, as well as traditional DLC. Portal 2 will go down in history as one of the best lunacy-inducing sequels ever made, and if you didn\u2019t get that last reference then you need to play one of the greatest games ever crafted in the gaming industry.", "date": "2011-04-28", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667730", "grade": null, "id": 218822, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218822", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "uk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f7e9f08-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 22, "name": "United Kingdom"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258033", "first_year": 2008, "id": 1259, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1259/playstation-lifestyle/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "PlayStation Lifestyle", "num_reviews": 583, "url": "https://www.playstationlifestyle.net/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://playstationlifestyle.net/2011/04/28/ps3-review-portal-2/"}, {"citation": "There\u0027s no real way around it, Portal 2 is simply one of the best games of this generation. It\u0027s creative, wonderfully detailed and most importantly, a complete blast to play. Valve has taken the formula from the original game and expanded upon it with a great follow up. To put it most simply, Portal 2 is not to be missed.", "date": "2011-05-03", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45806718", "grade": null, "id": 237734, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-237734", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254978", "first_year": 2008, "id": 1650, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1650/cheat-happens/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Cheat Happens", "num_reviews": 215, "url": "http://www.cheathappens.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.cheathappens.com/reviews/portal2.asp"}, {"citation": "There is little reason not to experience Portal 2, especially for fans of the original. The graphics may not be of the same caliber of other AAA titles, and the story may falter from time to time, but those are paltry excuses not to experience one of the best current generation games around.", "date": "2011-10-06", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45745941", "grade": null, "id": 231037, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-231037", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257887", "first_year": 2002, "id": 85, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/85/thunderbolt-games/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Thunderbolt Games", "num_reviews": 1741, "url": "http://www.thunderboltgames.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 183114, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/183114/alsy/", "name": "Alsy"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.thunderboltgames.com/reviews/article/portal-2-review-for-ps3-xbox-360-pc.html"}, {"citation": "At its core, Portal 2 very much feels like a science experiment where you\u2019re the test subject. It holds nothing back, particularly with its dark and dry humour, and expands on mechanics and physics that helped define the original. Dark, mysterious, funny and entertaining, Portal 2 will challenge you in all the right ways.", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45720969", "grade": null, "id": 225615, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-225615", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "au", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/b24379d8-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 3, "name": "Australia"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259577", "first_year": 2006, "id": 1610, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1610/mmgn/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "MMGN", "num_reviews": 75, "url": "http://mmgn.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://pc.mmgn.com/Reviews/Portal-2-Review"}, {"citation": "Apr\u00e8s avoir fini le solo et le coop, la premi\u00e8re chose qu\u0027on se dit est que le jeu est trop court. Mais au final il est dans la moyenne des productions actuelles. Ce qui le rend trop court, c\u0027est surtout parce qu\u0027on voudrait qu\u0027il se prolonge encore et toujours. Allant \u00e0 contre-courant des jeux actuels, Valve a cr\u00e9\u00e9 une exp\u00e9rience de jeu unique qui mise sur l\u0027intelligence et l\u0027humour des joueurs plut\u00f4t sur leur aptitude \u00e0 massacrer le bouton de gauche de la souris en jouant au petit soldat. On applaudit, on en redemande et on compte sur eux pour faire vivre le titre.", "date": "2011-05-03", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45706011", "grade": null, "id": 226807, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-226807", "language": "fr", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "fr", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f4ebb9e-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 8, "name": "France"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252753", "first_year": 2001, "id": 131, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/131/factornews/", "languages": [{"code": "fr", "id": 42, "name": "French", "ordering": 420}], "last_year": null, "name": "Factornews", "num_reviews": 605, "url": "http://www.factornews.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 183114, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/183114/alsy/", "name": "Alsy"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.factornews.com/test-529-Portal_2.html"}, {"citation": "Not as perfectly formed as the original, but close enough - with some of the best story-telling and voiceover work in all gaming.", "date": "2011-04-20", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667783", "grade": null, "id": 218849, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218849", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "uk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f7e9f08-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 22, "name": "United Kingdom"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259540", "first_year": 2010, "id": 1421, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1421/metrocouk/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Metro.co.uk", "num_reviews": 1121, "url": "http://www.metro.co.uk/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.metro.co.uk/tech/games/861440-portal-2-review-open-your-mind"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 delivers, and it does it in style, creating one of the most meticulously designed, thrilling and delightful playgrounds we\u2019ve ever seen. It\u2019s a game with a magical take on momentum, where single bounds over tall buildings are business as usual, where every surface is a potential launchpad, and the entire experience is a belly laugh. Valve has a pretty good record with the number two, but attempting to inflate Portal\u2019s perfectly formed package could easily have been a disaster. Naturally, the sequel doesn\u2019t feel as bracingly fresh as the 2007 game, but it\u2019s precisely the sort of dizzying follow-up the original deserves.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45669289", "grade": null, "id": 218973, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218973", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "uk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f7e9f08-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 22, "name": "United Kingdom"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252876", "first_year": 1993, "id": 129, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/129/edge/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Edge", "num_reviews": 1477, "url": "http://www.edge-online.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.next-gen.biz/reviews/portal-2-review"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is in the business of defying players\u2019 expectations. Valve never wants you to predict what\u2019s going to happen at any moment, and delights in subtly setting those pins up and knocking them down. Even more than the clever gameplay mechanics and sharply written story, the smiles and laughter that such a carefully crafted game can extract from you mean this one will stay with you for years to come.", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45669148", "grade": null, "id": 218873, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218873", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259359", "first_year": 1994, "id": 1078, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1078/wired/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Wired", "num_reviews": 78, "url": "http://blog.wired.com/games/reviews/index.html"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://www.wired.com/gamelife/2011/04/portal-2-review/all/1"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 on loistava taidonn\u00e4yte Valvelta. Peli ei aliarvioi pelaajia ja t\u00e4ytt\u00e4\u00e4 fanien odotukset 100-prosenttisen varmasti. Pikkuasioista voi valittaa, mutta en ep\u00e4ile v\u00e4itt\u00e4\u00e4, ett\u00e4 kyseess\u00e4 on yksi vuoden parhaimpia pelej\u00e4. Peli tarjoaa makeaa mahan t\u00e4ydelt\u00e4 ja j\u00e4tt\u00e4\u00e4 silti toivomaan entist\u00e4 enemm\u00e4n lis\u00e4\u00e4. Onneksi peli, saavutuksineen ja salaisuuksineen, tarjoaa uudelleenpelattavuutta ruhtinaallisesti.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667683", "grade": null, "id": 218794, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218794", "language": "fi", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "fi", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f553136-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 7, "name": "Finland"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257962", "first_year": 2007, "id": 918, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/918/gamereactor-finland/", "languages": [{"code": "fi", "id": 41, "name": "Finnish", "ordering": 410}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gamereactor (Finland)", "num_reviews": 204, "url": "http://www.gamereactor.fi/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamereactor.fi/arviot/80399/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is in the business of defying players\u2019 expectations. Valve never wants you to predict what\u2019s going to happen at any moment, and delights in subtly setting those pins up and knocking them down. Even more than the clever gameplay mechanics and sharply written story, the smiles and laughter that such a carefully crafted game can extract from you mean this one will stay with you for years to come.", "date": "2011-04-21", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45669158", "grade": null, "id": 218874, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218874", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259359", "first_year": 1994, "id": 1078, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1078/wired/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Wired", "num_reviews": 78, "url": "http://blog.wired.com/games/reviews/index.html"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://www.wired.com/gamelife/2011/04/portal-2-review/all/1"}, {"citation": "En cualquier caso Portal 2 es un videojuego excelente. Pierde el uppercut de derecha que te lanzaba el primero, porque en el fondo y a mi entender son juegos muy distintos, pero su planteamiento es sobrecogedor, inteligente y mordaz. No te pierdas uno de los mejores guiones \u2013entre otras tantas virtudes- del a\u00f1o y ve a jugarlo.", "date": "2011-04-22", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667681", "grade": null, "id": 218787, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218787", "language": "es", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "es", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f789a9a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 20, "name": "Spain"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257951", "first_year": 2008, "id": 1060, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1060/eurogameres/", "languages": [{"code": "es", "id": 133, "name": "Spanish", "ordering": 1330}], "last_year": null, "name": "Eurogamer.es", "num_reviews": 190, "url": "http://www.eurogamer.es/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.eurogamer.es/articles/analisis-portal-2"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 er for det meste en v\u00e6sentlig forbedring i forhold til det f\u00f8rste spil. Historien g\u00f8r en stor forskel, og selvom det af og til g\u00e5r ind og p\u00e5virker spillets hovedkerne \u2013 legen med portalerne, s\u00e5 er det bestemt til at leve med, for det er velskrevet og hylemorsomt. Valve Software har m\u00e5ske ladet Half-Life 2: Episode 3 vente p\u00e5 sig i alt for lang tid nu, men med godbidder som Portal 2 s\u00e5 er det alt for nemt at tilgive dem.", "date": "2011-04-20", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667682", "grade": null, "id": 218789, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218789", "language": "da", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "dk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/c4d8fa64-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 26, "name": "Denmark"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254231", "first_year": 2010, "id": 1314, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1314/eurogamerdk/", "languages": [{"code": "da", "id": 33, "name": "Danish", "ordering": 330}], "last_year": null, "name": "Eurogamer.dk", "num_reviews": 33, "url": "http://www.eurogamer.dk/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.eurogamer.dk/articles/2011-04-20-portal-2-anmeldelse"}, {"citation": "If there\u2019s a bad mark on Portal 2\u2019s amazing score sheet, it\u2019d be the fact that this is in every sense of the word a sequel: anybody jumping straight into this game without knowledge of what happened in or how to play the first game, would quickly find themselves on the receiving end of some mercy-killing neurotoxin. Portal 2 is dense and rich in both flavour and complexity, but it only really works as a companion piece to the original game and relies heavily on you caring deeply about the prequel events. If the original game didn\u2019t really grab you, this isn\u2019t a sequel that\u2019ll \u201cfix all the mistakes\u201d and make a believer out of you - this is a game for the fans, and nobody else. That said, if you are one of those fans: this is the game you\u2019ve been waiting for. It\u2019s bigger, better and smarter in nearly every way, with the same ingenious puzzle design and signature Valve quality that make it a pleasure to play. Don\u2019t miss out on what is easily one of the funniest, most clever games of 2011.", "date": "2011-04-20", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667629", "grade": null, "id": 218753, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218753", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 4.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "au", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/b24379d8-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 3, "name": "Australia"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252805", "first_year": 2010, "id": 1412, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1412/games-on-net/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Games On Net", "num_reviews": 9, "url": "http://games.on.net/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://games.on.net/article/12276/ber_Review_Portal_2_PC"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is pure genius. With gameplay growing ever more addictive and new characters always threatening to steal the spotlight, Portal 2 is one of the best games of 2011. A perfect and true sequel to the 2007 hit, Portal 2 provides everything that a fantastically designed sequel needs. The graphics and style are noticeably better, the writing is top-notch, the gameplay is as enthralling as before, the developer commentary keep players entertained, and the rest is tied nicely together with beloved characters. With \u201cstill alive\u201d quotes and cake references kept to a minimum, Portal 2 steps the franchise out from the small tech demo with a neat story and into a work Valve can proudly place next to its Half-Life franchise.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667606", "grade": null, "id": 218750, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218750", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259491", "first_year": 1991, "id": 5, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/5/gamezone/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": 2021, "name": "GameZone", "num_reviews": 4569, "url": "http://www.gamezone.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://pc.gamezone.com/reviews/item/portal_2"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 se podr\u00eda considerar como una revoluci\u00f3n si no fuese porque la sombra del original era muy larga, pero s\u00ed que ha conseguido consolidarse como uno de los mejores juegos de los \u00faltimos tiempos. Hoy uno echa un vistazo a la estanter\u00eda de la tienda y ocho de cada diez juegos son de disparos o mata-mata gen\u00e9ricos sin ninguna innovaci\u00f3n. Portal 2 entra en la otra divisi\u00f3n sin duda alguna. Es algo fresco, estimulante, novedoso. Valve ha sabido aprovechar el tanteo llevado a cabo con la primera entrega para ofrecer una experiencia completa y mucho m\u00e1s compleja, y lo ha hecho de manera excelente.", "date": "2011-05-04", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667562", "grade": null, "id": 218693, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218693", "language": "es", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 90.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "es", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f789a9a-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 20, "name": "Spain"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257812", "first_year": 2003, "id": 496, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/496/viciojuegoscom-uvejuegoscom/", "languages": [{"code": "es", "id": 133, "name": "Spanish", "ordering": 1330}], "last_year": null, "name": "VicioJuegos.com / uVeJuegos.com", "num_reviews": 738, "url": "http://www.viciojuegos.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.viciojuegos.com/analisis/Portal-2/El-colmo-de-Isaac-Asimov/5796/39677"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 er utfordrende, og balanserer h\u00e5rfint mellom \u00e5 gi deg inntrykk av \u00e5 v\u00e6re djevelsk glup og fryktelig teit om hverandre. Vet du l\u00f8sningen p\u00e5 en g\u00e5te s\u00e5 er den for det meste overkommelig \u00e5 utf\u00f8re, og begrensningene ligger mellom \u00f8rene heller enn hvor treffsikker eller kjapp du er med styrestikka. Dette spillet skaper neppe like mye oppstyr som forgjengeren, men er noen gode hakk bedre. Inkluderingen av en fungerende historie er bare en av mange ting som gj\u00f8r at alle burde pr\u00f8ve en av \u00e5rets virkelige storspill.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45666008", "grade": null, "id": 218743, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218743", "language": "no", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "no", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/d7733c3e-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 34, "name": "Norway"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259472", "first_year": 2006, "id": 1132, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1132/gamerno/", "languages": [{"code": "no", "id": 102, "name": "Norwegian", "ordering": 1020}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gamer.no", "num_reviews": 629, "url": "http://www.gamer.no/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamer.no/artikler/82540/anmeldelse-portal-2/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is a creative and engaging little slice of gaming heaven that can truly appeal to all kinds of people. It is one of the best games I have played all year, and it will probably become one of your favourites soon enough if you give it a chance. If you are concerned about value for money then, by all means wait for a price drop. The moment that price hits a level you\u2019re comfortable with though, make sure you purchase it. Portal 2 is a game that you will not regret playing in any sense of the word.", "date": "2011-04-20", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45656018", "grade": null, "id": 217540, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-217540", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257959", "first_year": 2009, "id": 1554, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1554/gamingbolt/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "GamingBolt", "num_reviews": 669, "url": "http://gamingbolt.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://gamingbolt.com/portal-2-pc-review"}, {"citation": "What they say about sequels not holding up the original is often enough true, however it doesn\u2019t apply to Portal 2. Everything about Portal 2 is \u201cbigger and better\u201d than the original. You can clearly see that the developers made sure to keep the core of the gameplay from Portal intact, while enhancing every bit of the experience into a deeper, more fulfilling experience for Portal 2. With 2-player co-op and cross-platform gameplay thanks to Steam being brought over to the PS3 console, Valve is essentially \u201cchanging the game\u201d and we all thank them for it. Whether you pick up the Xbox 360, PC or PS3 version of the game, you will have a rich and rewarding experience seldom few bring to the table.", "date": "2011-06-20", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45637843", "grade": null, "id": 214646, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-214646", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257723", "first_year": 2004, "id": 388, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/388/gamingevolution/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "GamingEvolution", "num_reviews": 138, "url": "http://www.gamingevolution.info/"}, "submitter": {"id": 170000, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/170000/mprunty/", "name": "Matthew Prunty"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://gamingevolution.info/?id=12614"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 ist ein nahezu perfektes Spiel f\u00fcr das, was es ist. Es gibt Kleinigkeiten wie nun v\u00f6llig unbewegliches Interior, was sich anfangs komisch anf\u00fchlt, weil alles auf mysteri\u00f6se Art und Weise am Boden klebt. Vielleicht haben sie bei Valve in Tests herausgefunden, dass einige Spieler sich einfach zu lange damit besch\u00e4ftigt haben, das Zeug durch die Level zu schleppen auf der Suche nach der L\u00f6sung... wer wei\u00df. Richtig schade ist nur, dass die Kampagne - je nach nach F\u00e4higkeiten - in sieben bis zehn Stunden erledigt ist. Dazu gesellen sich vier bis sechs Stunden Koop-Material. Das ist eigentlich genug, aber man will einfach nicht, dass es endet. Und hatte mir GLaDOS nicht am Anfang versprochen, dass ich hier f\u00fcr immer testen darf? Verdammte L\u00fcgnerin! Anderseits: Das war sie doch schon immer, oder etwa nicht!?!", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45745385", "grade": null, "id": 218799, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218799", "language": "de", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "dk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/c4d8fa64-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 26, "name": "Denmark"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257965", "first_year": 2009, "id": 1559, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1559/gamereactor-germany/", "languages": [{"code": "de", "id": 47, "name": "German", "ordering": 470}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gamereactor (Germany)", "num_reviews": 51, "url": "http://www.gamereactor.de/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamereactor.de/Kritiken/5850/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 er et spill som skiller seg fra mengden. Det gir en tilfredsstillende f\u00f8lelse \u00e5 l\u00f8se de intrikate g\u00e5tene, som takket v\u00e6re str\u00e5lende brettdesign holder seg utfordrende og interessante gjennom hele spillet. Valve leverer dialog og humor i s\u00e6rklasse, og for meg var det helt umulig \u00e5 ikke la seg bli sjarmert s\u00f8nder og sammen av robotenes personlighet. Sleng p\u00e5 en str\u00e5lende samarbeidsdel p\u00e5 toppen av det hele, og Portal 2 lever opp til forventningene. Hvem liker vel ikke roboter med f\u00f8lelser?", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45616438", "grade": null, "id": 210110, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-210110", "language": "no", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "no", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/d7733c3e-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 34, "name": "Norway"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257793", "first_year": 2000, "id": 1310, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1310/gamereactor-norway/", "languages": [{"code": "no", "id": 102, "name": "Norwegian", "ordering": 1020}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gamereactor (Norway)", "num_reviews": 168, "url": "http://www.gamereactor.no/"}, "submitter": {"id": 55154, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/55154/disco-sounds-2088/", "name": "lights out party"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamereactor.no/anmeldelser/124260/Portal+2/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is more of the same, but only in the best of ways. Valve didn\u0027t mess with a winning formula, and the end result is that Portal 2 is a better game than its excellent predecessor. It keeps the same witty humor and high-quality level design but adds a few new tricks to turn the interesting puzzles into exceptional ones. The co-op campaign is a boatload of fun and adds extra value to the package \u2014 especially if you\u0027re a PS3 owner, who gets the PC/Mac version along with the console copy. Portal 2\u0027s only problem is that it\u0027s a hair short and lacks replay value. Despite this, it\u0027s some of the best gaming I\u0027ve had in recent memory, and it still manages to be worth the full price. If you remotely enjoyed the original Portal, you\u0027ll absolutely love the sequel.", "date": "2011-04-20", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45745390", "grade": null, "id": 218850, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218850", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257907", "first_year": 2001, "id": 57, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/57/worth-playing/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Worth Playing", "num_reviews": 3217, "url": "http://www.worthplaying.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://worthplaying.com/article/2011/4/20/reviews/80959/"}, {"citation": "Valves topchef Gabe Newell har sagt, at Portal 2 sandsynligvis er det bedste spil Valve nogensinde har lavet. Det er et udsagn der er sv\u00e6rt at bed\u00f8mme, fordi n\u00e6sten hvert eneste af udviklerens spil har v\u00e6ret skels\u00e6ttende. Af samme grund giver det heller ikke rigtig mening at kalde det for et af deres bedste spil. I stedet vil jeg sige dette: Portal 2 har overg\u00e5et mine temmelig h\u00f8je forventninger, og er den perfekte efterf\u00f8lger til det klassiske Portal. Det g\u00f8r alting rigtigt, og s\u00e6tter ikke en eneste fod forkert undervejs. Det er et spil alle burde pr\u00f8ve, og f\u00e5r min varmeste anbefaling.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45616437", "grade": null, "id": 210107, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-210107", "language": "da", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "dk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/c4d8fa64-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 26, "name": "Denmark"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257795", "first_year": 1998, "id": 845, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/845/gamereactor-denmark/", "languages": [{"code": "da", "id": 33, "name": "Danish", "ordering": 330}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gamereactor (Denmark)", "num_reviews": 775, "url": "https://www.gamereactor.dk/"}, "submitter": {"id": 55154, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/55154/disco-sounds-2088/", "name": "lights out party"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamereactor.dk/anmeldelser/83540/Portal+2/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 delivers, and it does it in style, creating one of the most meticulously designed, thrilling and delightful playgrounds we\u2019ve ever seen. It\u2019s a game with a magical take on momentum, where single bounds over tall buildings are business as usual, where every surface is a potential launchpad, and the entire experience is a belly laugh. Valve has a pretty good record with the number two, but attempting to inflate Portal\u2019s perfectly formed package could easily have been a disaster. Naturally, the sequel doesn\u2019t feel as bracingly fresh as the 2007 game, but it\u2019s precisely the sort of dizzying follow-up the original deserves.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45745395", "grade": null, "id": 218971, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218971", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "uk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f7e9f08-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 22, "name": "United Kingdom"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252876", "first_year": 1993, "id": 129, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/129/edge/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Edge", "num_reviews": 1477, "url": "http://www.edge-online.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.next-gen.biz/reviews/portal-2-review"}, {"citation": "As you journey through the massive Aperture facility, it becomes clear that Portal 2 does not merely come after Portal. Instead, it radiates outward from its predecessor, simultaneously illuminating the world that gave rise to Portal and continuing the adventure that began there. The sense of novelty is diminished, but the thrill of exploration and puzzle-solving is still intoxicating, and it\u0027s amazing how Portal 2 manages to tell a better story with disembodied voices and spherical robots than most games can with full-on humans. Your return to Aperture Science is a joyful one in this immensely appealing, laugh-out-loud funny, and thoroughly satisfying sequel.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45556771", "grade": null, "id": 211108, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-211108", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258112", "first_year": 1995, "id": 1, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1/gamespot/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "GameSpot", "num_reviews": 11888, "url": "http://www.gamespot.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 55856, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/55856/scaryfun/", "name": "Scaryfun"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamespot.com/pc/action/portal-2/review.html"}, {"citation": "Over half a year after release, Portal 2 has not culturally exploded in the way that its predecessor did; but, in many ways, that\u2019s a good thing. Far be it for us to suggest that the first Portal represented a false start, but its sequel nonetheless makes it feel like more of a prologue. Free from the bonds of jokes made insipid by overuse (\u2018the cake is a lie\u2019 is thankfully nowhere to be seen here), Portal 2 feels like Portal born anew; not a reinvention, but a rejuvenation\u2014and expansion\u2014of everything that made its predecessor so loved. Thus, while we may indignantly assume that Valve is merely twiddling its thumbs in the agonising years between releases, Portal 2 serves to legitimise their chronic procrastination by refiguring it as the unpredictable ebb and flow of a collective genius mind at work.", "date": "2012-02-16", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=3072619680", "grade": null, "id": 389602, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-389602", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257887", "first_year": 2002, "id": 85, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/85/thunderbolt-games/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Thunderbolt Games", "num_reviews": 1741, "url": "http://www.thunderboltgames.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 103984, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/103984/cantillon/", "name": "Cantillon"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.thunderboltgames.com/review/portal-2"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is more of the same, but only in the best of ways. Valve didn\u0027t mess with a winning formula, and the end result is that Portal 2 is a better game than its excellent predecessor. It keeps the same witty humor and high-quality level design but adds a few new tricks to turn the interesting puzzles into exceptional ones. The co-op campaign is a boatload of fun and adds extra value to the package \u2014 especially if you\u0027re a PS3 owner, who gets the PC/Mac version along with the console copy. Portal 2\u0027s only problem is that it\u0027s a hair short and lacks replay value. Despite this, it\u0027s some of the best gaming I\u0027ve had in recent memory, and it still manages to be worth the full price. If you remotely enjoyed the original Portal, you\u0027ll absolutely love the sequel.", "date": "2011-04-20", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45556754", "grade": null, "id": 211104, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-211104", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257907", "first_year": 2001, "id": 57, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/57/worth-playing/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Worth Playing", "num_reviews": 3217, "url": "http://www.worthplaying.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 55856, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/55856/scaryfun/", "name": "Scaryfun"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://worthplaying.com/article/2011/4/20/reviews/80959/"}, {"citation": "What they say about sequels not holding up the original is often enough true, however it doesn\u2019t apply to Portal 2. Everything about Portal 2 is \u201cbigger and better\u201d than the original. You can clearly see that the developers made sure to keep the core of the gameplay from Portal intact, while enhancing every bit of the experience into a deeper, more fulfilling experience for Portal 2. With 2-player co-op and cross-platform gameplay thanks to Steam being brought over to the PS3 console, Valve is essentially \u201cchanging the game\u201d and we all thank them for it. Whether you pick up the Xbox 360, PC or PS3 version of the game, you will have a rich and rewarding experience seldom few bring to the table.", "date": "2011-06-20", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45645011", "grade": null, "id": 214644, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-214644", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257723", "first_year": 2004, "id": 388, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/388/gamingevolution/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "GamingEvolution", "num_reviews": 138, "url": "http://www.gamingevolution.info/"}, "submitter": {"id": 170000, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/170000/mprunty/", "name": "Matthew Prunty"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://gamingevolution.info/?id=12616"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is more of the same, but only in the best of ways. Valve didn\u0027t mess with a winning formula, and the end result is that Portal 2 is a better game than its excellent predecessor. It keeps the same witty humor and high-quality level design but adds a few new tricks to turn the interesting puzzles into exceptional ones. The co-op campaign is a boatload of fun and adds extra value to the package. Portal 2\u0027s only problem is that it\u0027s a hair short and lacks replay value. Despite this, it\u0027s some of the best gaming I\u0027ve had in recent memory, and it still manages to be worth the full price. If you remotely enjoyed the original Portal, you\u0027ll absolutely love the sequel.", "date": "2011-04-20", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45738008", "grade": null, "id": 218851, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218851", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257907", "first_year": 2001, "id": 57, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/57/worth-playing/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Worth Playing", "num_reviews": 3217, "url": "http://www.worthplaying.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://worthplaying.com/article/2011/4/20/reviews/80959/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is pure genius. With gameplay growing ever more addictive and new characters always threatening to steal the spotlight, Portal 2 is one of the best games of 2011. A perfect and true sequel to the 2007 hit, Portal 2 provides everything that a fantastically designed sequel needs. The graphics and style are noticeably better, the writing is top-notch, the gameplay is as enthralling as before, the developer commentary keep players entertained, and the rest is tied nicely together with beloved characters. With \u201cstill alive\u201d quotes and cake references kept to a minimum, Portal 2 steps the franchise out from the small tech demo with a neat story and into a work Valve can proudly place next to its Half-Life franchise.", "date": "2011-04-20", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45737972", "grade": null, "id": 218751, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218751", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259491", "first_year": 1991, "id": 5, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/5/gamezone/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": 2021, "name": "GameZone", "num_reviews": 4569, "url": "http://www.gamezone.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://xbox.gamezone.com/reviews/item/portal_2"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 je stejn\u011b skv\u011bl\u00fd jako prvn\u00ed d\u00edl, nav\u00edc je v\u011bt\u0161\u00ed a propracovan\u011bj\u0161\u00ed. Stav\u00ed na z\u00e1bavn\u00e9m sv\u011bt\u011b pln\u00e9m \u0161\u00edlen\u00fdch robot\u016f a absurdn\u00edch v\u011bdeck\u00fdch pokus\u016f. P\u0159\u00edjemn\u011b plyne hratelnost, kter\u00e1 je prost\u00e1 p\u0159ehnan\u011b t\u011b\u017ek\u00fdch \u00fakol\u016f, p\u0159esto je pro hr\u00e1\u010de v\u00fdzvou. Skv\u011bl\u00e1 je kooperativn\u00ed kampa\u0148, vynikaj\u00edc\u00ed je dabing postav a ve sv\u00e9 podstat\u011b i p\u0159\u00edb\u011bh, kter\u00fd je sice o ni\u010dem, ale Valve ono nic um\u00ed velmi dob\u0159e podat. Jedin\u00fdm v\u011bt\u0161\u00edm m\u00ednusem bude asi mal\u00e1 znovuhratelnost, proto\u017ee po prvn\u00edm dokon\u010den\u00ed u\u017e v\u00edte, jak v\u0161echny h\u00e1danky splnit.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45737970", "grade": null, "id": 218790, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218790", "language": "cs", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "cz", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/b21b1808-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 30, "name": "Czechia"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259513", "first_year": 2009, "id": 1321, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1321/eurogamercz/", "languages": [{"code": "cs", "id": 32, "name": "Czech", "ordering": 320}], "last_year": null, "name": "Eurogamer.cz", "num_reviews": 347, "url": "http://www.eurogamer.cz/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.eurogamer.cz/articles/portal-2-recenze"}, {"citation": "Portal 2\u2032s clearly aimed at fans of the original, and rightly so \u2013 Valve have made no concessions to the uninitiated beyond the first hour or so: the puzzles might be a tad easier, but there\u2019s much more of them (the game takes between 10 and 12 hours to get through) and there\u2019s huge sections well outside the white walls of the labs that take real concentration. The biggest disappointment is realising that, once you\u2019re done, Valve Time will mean we\u2019ll be without the warm bosom of GLaDOS for \u2013 presumably \u2013 years. Regardless, games like this don\u2019t come around very often, and if you miss out on this one you\u2019ll be skipping one of the finest examples of the medium the industry has to offer: Portal 2 is compelling, exciting, wildly capricious and, most importantly, laugh out loud funny.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45737966", "grade": null, "id": 218756, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218756", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "uk", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f7e9f08-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 22, "name": "United Kingdom"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257856", "first_year": 2007, "id": 1148, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1148/thesixthaxis/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "TheSixthAxis", "num_reviews": 1283, "url": "http://www.thesixthaxis.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.thesixthaxis.com/2011/04/19/review-portal-2/"}, {"citation": "As you journey through the massive Aperture facility, it becomes clear that Portal 2 does not merely come after Portal. Instead, it radiates outward from its predecessor, simultaneously illuminating the world that gave rise to Portal and continuing the adventure that began there. The sense of novelty is diminished, but the thrill of exploration and puzzle-solving is still intoxicating, and it\u0027s amazing how Portal 2 manages to tell a better story with disembodied voices and spherical robots than most games can with full-on humans. Your return to Aperture Science is a joyful one in this immensely appealing, laugh-out-loud funny, and thoroughly satisfying sequel.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45737923", "grade": null, "id": 218783, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218783", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 9.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49258112", "first_year": 1995, "id": 1, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1/gamespot/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "GameSpot", "num_reviews": 11888, "url": "http://www.gamespot.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamespot.com/xbox360/action/portal-2/review.html"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is outstanding, really, a top-to-bottom success from one of our best developers, and 90 percent of me is completely delighted I got to take the journey. But in the process of falling in love with Portal 2, I lost something kind of magical about Portal 1.", "date": "2011-04-20", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45670719", "grade": null, "id": 219051, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-219051", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 90.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 4.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257743", "first_year": 2007, "id": 1403, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1403/joystiq/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": 2015, "name": "Joystiq", "num_reviews": 182, "url": "http://www.joystiq.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://www.joystiq.com/2011/04/20/portal-2-review/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 riesce a coniugare la 