malized_score": 89.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 89.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "at", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f3755d0-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 25, "name": "Austria"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257767", "first_year": 1989, "id": 269, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/269/gamersat/", "languages": [{"code": "de", "id": 47, "name": "German", "ordering": 470}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gamers.at", "num_reviews": 674, "url": "http://www.gamers.at/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamers.at/articles/portal_2-995/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is one of those rare games that makes its predecessor completely obsolete. There are more puzzles, more characters, better graphics and sound, more variables in the puzzles, and a surprising story that went above and beyond my expectations. Unfortunately, once you\u2019ve beaten both campaigns, there\u2019s nothing left to do. Even with that shortcoming, however, Portal 2 is one of the most enjoyable gaming experiences I\u2019ve had for quite a while.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45669299", "grade": null, "id": 218976, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218976", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 88.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 8.8, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257859", "first_year": 2008, "id": 1116, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1116/gamrreview/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "gamrReview", "num_reviews": 116, "url": "http://www.gamrreview.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://gamrreview.vgchartz.com/review/43866/portal-2/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 slips through its own series of tests to be a genuine follow-up to the now cult classic original. Akin to the original, puzzling in the first-person isn\u0027t going to be for everyone, so if testing the waters means you pick up the older, yet priceless \u0027The Orange Box\u0027 or dive right into Portal 2, it\u0027s worth a look. Even with its high praise, Portal 2 isn\u0027t perfect, but it\u0027s imaginative, it\u0027s sophisticated, and one of the best puzzlers we\u0027ve played in years. Thinking has never been so much fun.", "date": "2011-04-27", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667643", "grade": null, "id": 218810, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218810", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 87.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 8.7, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "ca", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9fa117cc-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 5, "name": "Canada"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259469", "first_year": 2002, "id": 202, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/202/extreme-gamer/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Extreme Gamer", "num_reviews": 706, "url": "http://www.extremegamer.ca/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.extremegamer.ca/multi/reviews/portal2.php"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 slips through its own series of tests to be a genuine follow-up to the now cult classic original. Akin to the original, puzzling in the first-person isn\u0027t going to be for everyone, so if testing the waters means you pick up the older, yet priceless \u0027The Orange Box\u0027 or dive right into Portal 2, it\u0027s worth a look. Even with its high praise, Portal 2 isn\u0027t perfect, but it\u0027s imaginative, it\u0027s sophisticated, and one of the best puzzlers we\u0027ve played in years. Thinking has never been so much fun.", "date": "2011-04-27", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667555", "grade": null, "id": 218809, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218809", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 87.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 8.7, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "ca", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9fa117cc-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 5, "name": "Canada"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49259469", "first_year": 2002, "id": 202, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/202/extreme-gamer/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Extreme Gamer", "num_reviews": 706, "url": "http://www.extremegamer.ca/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.extremegamer.ca/multi/reviews/portal2.php"}, {"citation": "The real beauty of Portal 2 this time is what is said. There\u0027s a meta-game clearly at play here. Those who played Portal will notice an improvement in the quality of the puzzles in Portal 2. This is because your role in Portal was more than just Chell - you were the test subject. GLaDOS tells you this over and over - and Portal 2 demonstrates it to be true. Of course heatmaps and stat tracking can\u0027t tell you how to sufficiently nail humour, so Portal slips in those areas. It\u0027s more Portal, not a better Portal. Regardless, if you\u0027re looking for a challenging puzzle game and a great coop experience, Portal 2 is a must buy.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667702", "grade": null, "id": 218811, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218811", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 85.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 8.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "au", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/b24379d8-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 3, "name": "Australia"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257993", "first_year": 2004, "id": 730, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/730/game-arena/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Game Arena", "num_reviews": 85, "url": "http://www.gamearena.com.au/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://www.gamearena.com.au/ps3/games/title/portal-2/reviews.php?id=5093350"}, {"citation": "Valve have managed to buck most of the standard norms while still delivering one of the best games you will play this year. The game by itself would be awesome enough, but Cross Game Play/Chat with Steam just takes it to a whole other level bringing the world of consoles and PC together in a way that hasn\u2019t been done until now. For all those who appreciate a real challenge, this is the game for you. To chess players who thrive on the games that demand that you be able to see several moves ahead, this is for you as well. Portal 2 isn\u2019t the kind of game that everyone will like and that is ok. I respect the fact that Valve refused to dumb their game down for fear it wouldn\u2019t be accepted by the masses. I still don\u2019t know if the masses will take to it. All I can say is if you want a truly challenging game to take up some time, pick up Portal 2. Valve did a hell of a job in delivering a sequel that captures the spirit of the original while creating a bit of magic that is all its own.", "date": "2011-05-02", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667592", "grade": null, "id": 218705, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218705", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 85.0, "platform": {"id": 81, "name": "PlayStation 3"}, "score": 8.5, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252410", "first_year": 2010, "id": 1419, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1419/zoknowsgaming/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "ZoKnowsGaming", "num_reviews": 4, "url": "http://zoknowsgaming.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://zoknowsgaming.com/2011/05/02/portal-2-review/"}, {"citation": "This is a great game. It takes what makes the first Portal game and upgrades it to provide a much more full gaming experience. Some areas can be a bit more annoying than others, but that is probably the only real complaint I have with the game. Graphics are great with how environments are laid out and the audio is also nicely done mostly thanks to the voice acting and effects. So, I\u2019d say this is a great game overall.", "date": "2025-05-09", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=4299186790", "grade": null, "id": 657389, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-657389", "language": "en", "max_score": 100.0, "normalized_score": 84.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 84.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "ca", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9fa117cc-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 5, "name": "Canada"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=4295330295", "first_year": 2013, "id": 3226, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/3226/freezenet/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "FreezeNet", "num_reviews": 76, "url": "https://www.freezenet.ca/"}, "submitter": {"id": 1121630, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/1121630/rocket55/", "name": "Rocket"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "https://www.freezenet.ca/review-portal-2-pc-steam/"}, {"citation": "Ultimately, the biggest problem with Portal 2 is Portal 1, which was a lean mean meme machine driven by one of videogaming\u0027s most unforgettable characters. So when the sequel has a minor negative space problem, and closes with a credit sequence that I can\u0027t hum for the life of me, is Portal 2 ever so slightly disappointing, or was Portal 1 just flat-out ingenious? I suspect a little of both. But with this much awesome Stephen Merchant, and with my status as a frickin\u0027 genius puzzle solver reaffirmed, and with a unique co-op experience, it\u0027s like complaining that I was promised the moon and the stars, but I only got the moon.", "date": "2011-04-25", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667700", "grade": "B+", "id": 218815