iption": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254215", "first_year": 2009, "id": 1162, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1162/gamer-limit/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gamer Limit", "num_reviews": 221, "url": "http://gamerlimit.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://gamerlimit.com/2011/04/gamer-limit-review-portal-2/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 is the best sequel we could have expected. The levels just plain aren\u0027t as challenging, but the new toys and characters manage to distract enough from the cracks in the paint to keep the whole ride breezing along. It astounds in some ways and disappoints in others, which, while not perfect, is good enough for science. Newcomers to \"portal science\" will find Portal 2 easy to pick up and perhaps more rewarding than long-time fans. Both, however, will find plenty to love and more than enough to justify the price of purchase.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667701", "grade": null, "id": 218818, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218818", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 80.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 4.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254232", "first_year": 2009, "id": 1399, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1399/escapist-the/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Escapist, The", "num_reviews": 306, "url": "http://www.escapistmagazine.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 2, "name": "Star System"}, "url": "http://www.escapistmagazine.com/articles/view/editorials/reviews/8806-Portal-2-Review"}, {"citation": "Probleml\u00f6sningen med portaler och f\u00e4rger som ger ytor vissa egenskaper \u00e4r briljant och h\u00e5lls varierade spelet igenom. Jag gillar \u00e4ven den enkla, men effektiva handlingen och framf\u00f6r allt dialogerna i ber\u00e4ttandet. \u00c4ven samarbetsl\u00e4get g\u00f6r Portal 2 k\u00f6pv\u00e4rt f\u00f6r alla som gillar probleml\u00f6sning. Men det blir tjatigt i l\u00e4ngden med rum efter rum med pussel som ska l\u00f6sas och n\u00e4r sluttexten rullar k\u00e4nner jag mig lite \u00f6verm\u00e4tt.", "date": "2011-04-19", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667699", "grade": null, "id": 218814, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218814", "language": "sv", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 80.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 8.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "se", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f3d1a06-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 21, "name": "Sweden"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49257943", "first_year": 2001, "id": 1343, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1343/level-7/", "languages": [{"code": "sv", "id": 137, "name": "Swedish", "ordering": 1370}], "last_year": null, "name": "Level 7", "num_reviews": 176, "url": "http://level7.nu/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://level7.nu/spel/spel.php?id=5363\u0026show=text\u0026part=review\u0026aid=204061"}, {"citation": "Does Portal 2 outshine its predecessor? That\u2019s a difficult question to answer. It is a longer, fuller experience to be certain, but having previously seen and experienced what made Portal so interesting and unique, Portal 2 doesn\u2019t quite feel so new or exciting. Some frustrating decisions and an underwhelming second act aside, the central premise is as brilliant as ever and Valve has enough tricks up their sleeves to keep it challenging, interesting, and hilarious as always.", "date": "2011-04-27", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45667708", "grade": null, "id": 218805, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-218805", "language": "en", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 80.0, "platform": {"id": 69, "name": "Xbox 360"}, "score": 8.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "us", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f436050-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 1, "name": "United States"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49254215", "first_year": 2009, "id": 1162, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1162/gamer-limit/", "languages": [{"code": "en", "id": 36, "name": "English", "ordering": 360}], "last_year": null, "name": "Gamer Limit", "num_reviews": 221, "url": "http://gamerlimit.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 163111, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/163111/cavalary/", "name": "Cavalary"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://gamerlimit.com/2011/04/gamer-limit-review-portal-2/"}, {"citation": "Portal 2 est un jeu assez unique en son genre. Proposant des m\u00e9caniques inhabituelles, et un humour constant, ce titre se r\u00e9v\u00e8le tr\u00e8s prenant et garanti une aventure rythm\u00e9e sans presque aucun temps mort.", "date": "2011", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45688953", "grade": null, "id": 234024, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-234024", "language": "fr", "max_score": 10.0, "normalized_score": 80.0, "platform": {"id": 3, "name": "Windows"}, "score": 8.0, "source": {"country": {"country_code": "fr", "flag": "https://cdn.mobygames.com/9f4ebb9e-ab5e-11ed-b6d6-02420a000150.gif", "id": 8, "name": "France"}, "description": null, "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=46\u0026oid=49252872", "first_year": 2004, "id": 1547, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/critic/1547/jeuxpocom/", "languages": [{"code": "fr", "id": 42, "name": "French", "ordering": 420}], "last_year": null, "name": "Jeuxpo.com", "num_reviews": 252, "url": "http://www.jeuxpo.com/"}, "submitter": {"id": 183114, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/user/183114/alsy/", "name": "Alsy"}, "type": {"id": 1, "name": "Numeric (Highest score is best)"}, "url": "http://jeuxpo.com/game_test-8849.html"}, {"citation": "All things considered, Portal 2 is one superb offering. I\u2019m glad I bought it, and I really enjoyed playing it. From the tone of this review, you might\u2019ve gotten a sense that I\u2019m not really hyperventilating over its awesomeness, but that\u2019s only because we all knew it was going to be great. It\u2019s still quite awesome, though, and definitely a game that everyone should play. If, for some reason, you haven\u2019t played the original, drop everything and go get both games; you\u2019re missing out on some of the best experiences that gaming has to offer. Portal veterans who are tight on cash at the moment might want to grab the second installment on sale, or wait for a permanent price drop. But make no mistake\u2014skipping Portal 2 should not be an option for you.", "date": "2011-05-02", "edit_object_url": "/approval/edit-object?type=47\u0026oid=45993932", "grade": null, "id": 245482, "internal_url": "https://www.mobygames.com/game/51233/portal-2/reviews/#critic-score-245482", "language": "en", "max_score": 5.0, "normalized_score": 80.0, "platform": {"id": 74, "name": "Macintosh"},